name: Cape Cod Child Development Mashpee Preschool Rm 171
details: Our mission is to serve as a community resource that provides childcare, educational and developmental intervention, and family support services. We offer child-focused, family-centered programs that are affordable, accessible and of the highest quality. The agency staff and associated professionals work in partnership with families and others in the community to build on each child’s unique strengths, ensuring positive growth and development.

name: First Steps Early Learning Center
details: First Steps Early Learning Center was established to provide a fun, safe, nurturing learning environment to assist children in their developmental stages from infancy through Pre-Kindergarten.  The staff at First Steps believe that all children develop at different stages and learn through different methods. We believe in providing a nurturing family environment for our children so that they can feel safe and comfortable. We feel that once the child feels that he/she is part of a family, they can be confident and excel in their development. Our teachers encourage social, physical, language and cognitive development through reading, art, music, dramatic arts, math, science, dance and play. We believe that our children and parents are an extended family of our staff here at First Steps and hope that you feel the same as well.

name: Blossom Street Head Start Center
details: A preschool program for children ages 3-5, Head Start prepares children for kindergarten, to be ready physically, emotionally, cognitively and socially. With trained staff specialized in early education, children participate in individual and group activities. This free program is available for those who meet income eligibility and live in Lynn, Lynnfield, Marblehead, Nahant, Saugus or Swampscott and prioritizes the most urgent needs including homeless children, children in foster care, or children with disabilities, for example.

name: Bright Start After School @ Bishop
details: BRIGHT START offers children a unique blend of challenging activities within a warm, loving, secure setting. Director, Andrea Gingrande, who founded the school in 1991, manages Bright Start and teaches in the program along with her excellent staff. Previously, Andrea was director of Acton's K-6 Academically Talented program. Andrea has a M.Ed. in Gifted Education from Johns Hopkins University and was an Education Policy Fellow in Washington, D.C. She has taught in Massachusetts for over 26 years.

name: The Goddard School
details: Our approach is based on accepted research that clearly indicates the deepest, most genuine learning occurs for children through play and fun activities, lovingly guided by highly trained teachers. We deploy the talents of highly trained teachers and educational directors to prepare your child for social and academic success. Our Educational Advisory Board and Goddard Systems University ensure our faculty maintains the highest standards in early childhood education. Your child is offered ample opportunities to develop his or her natural curiosity and creativity through exploration and discovery, guided by caring teachers who cultivate these moments for lasting understanding. Every school is co-led by an on-site owner and education director who work together to make sure every family has a wonderful experience. This distinctive model also ensures children feel known and appreciated for their individual gifts and personalities.

name: First Step Child Care Center Inc.
details:
Philosophy
    First Step believes that each child is a unique individual with feelings, emotions and opinions.
    We believe that children should feel safe and loved when away from their parents.
    We encourage children to explore, learn and grow through activities and opportunities.
    First Step believes that children learn from a setting that is safe, educational, nurturing, structured as well as challenging.
    We encourage children to make their own choices. This process will help children build self-esteem and confidence. Every child is a unique individual who has the right to a happy childhood.
    At First Step, we believe that parents involvement  is a crucial part of a child’s emotional and social growth. We encourage parents to be involved in all aspects, recreational, educational and administrative.
    At First Step we believe a happy environment makes a happy child.

name: The Frances Jacobson Early Childhood Center
details: The FJECC is committed to providing the highest quality early childhood education in both secular and Judaic studies in a safe, nurturing and non-pressured environment under the guidance of well-trained and highly educated teachers. One of our primary goals is to meet the diverse needs of each child by paying close attention to his/her developmental needs, interests and strengths where a curiosity for and love of learning is fostered. Our philosophy is rooted in the need to foster respect for one another, individual dignity and self-worth. We support the integration of our parent body into all aspects of the school providing opportunity for them to serve as our close partners.

name: Here They Grow Nursery and Preschool, Inc.
details: ur daycare was founded in December 2008 by Kubryn Tiberio, a mother of four wonderful boys aged 6 months to 12 years. Kubryn encourages everyone to contact her as often as they would like regarding any comments concerns or even to give a special staff member a compliment.  Our staff members are dedicated professional teachers, who are committed to excellence in child-care and are here to provide your child with love, comfort and security. Our staff members are our most valuable resource and they are encouraged to continue their education in their chosen fields. We feel that a caring, nurturing, professional staff allows us to have a successful center. All our teachers meet or exceed the Dept of Early Education & Care. ECE requirements.  Our staff will work closely with parents to ensure a successful transition and stay at Here They Grow. Our team is available for conferences, to answer questions, address issues or respond to any concerns.

name: Early Childhood Learning Lab
details: The Preschool is part of the early childhood education program at Boston University. It provides a half-day program for children between the ages of 2 years 9 months and 5 years old. An extended day program is also offered until 2pm. Children may attend either 3 or 5 mornings each week. The school year runs from early September to mid-June. Affiliation with Boston University is not a requirement for enrollment.

name: Belmont Cooperative Nursery School
details:
Belmont Cooperative Nursery School (Belmont Co-op) promotes continuity between the child’s home and the school. Through its cooperative nature, families support and care about each other. Children, parents and teachers together create a warm community for
growing and learning.

name: Buds and Blossoms Early Education and Care Center
details: At Buds & Blossoms Early Education and Child Care Center, children learn Chinese Mandarin while developing all their natural gifts and talents.  Our child-centered philosophy and beautifully appointed classrooms enable children to grow and thrive as individuals, while learning the importance of being a caring member of a community.
business hours: Monday through Friday from 7:00 am to 6 pm

name: Children Nurturing Center
details:
Children Nurturing Center prepares children for future success by focusing on their individual needs. Children Nurturing Center stresses the comprehensive way of learning through daily experiences and by integrating this idea into all areas of their development, social interaction, personal growth, positive values and moral behavior. Our center aims at providing a warm, secure environment that promotes the fullest possible development of the whole child. Our goal is to prepare each individual to appreciate the richness of his or her life experiences. Our staff hopes to invoke the joy of learning through discovery. We partner with parents and families to help each child develop focus, the ability to concentrate, self-discipline, respect, dignity, self-confidence, and to understand freedom of choice by recognizing consequences of moral choices. We encourage independence combined with a sense of responsibility to a larger community, a love of service, an appreciation of order, a reverence for nature, and profound curiosity along with a sense of inquiry and wonder.
The mission of Children Nurturing Center is to providing quality and affordable early childhood care in a culturally diverse environment ensuring a climate for individual growth, comfort and security. Our focus is to provide a stimulating environment to help each child develop his/her own skills according to individual capabilities. We strive to provide a wide range of hands on activities and educational experiences that promote each child's social/emotional, physical and cognitive development. Our nurturing environment aims at strengthening the bridge between your work and family by having a place that supports both.
Children Nurturing Center offers a program that would help your child make a difference in learning. Our certified teachers are able to provide individualized instructions to meet the unique need and style of your child.

name: Haverhill YMCA Children's Learning Center
details:
MISSION
Our Y welcomes all. We strengthen communities, educate and nurture children, and promote healthy living in spirit, mind and body. 
Vision Statement
Where all children, adults and families are healthy, confident and connected.
Our Values
Caring, Honesty, Respect, and Responsibility.

name: Center for Martial Arts and Fitness
Learning Prep School Child Care Center
details:
The premise of LPS's Elementary, Middle, 8th Grade and High School Programs is that most language-challenged students do not learn incidentally from the environment as do non-impaired students. Language-impaired students demonstrate deficits in the acquisition of language as well as in their ability to access the competencies they have acquired. In addition, their ability to understand the social and non-literal meaning of language is often impaired. To address these problems, LPS provides language-impaired students with specially designed instructional programs within a safe, secure and highly structured classroom setting.

LPS students are taught in small classes of students with similar functional language levels, similar compensatory needs and similar academic skills. In each class, students work on the same subject, on the same level, simultaneously. Students and teachers work cooperatively and interact throughout the entire lesson. In this way, language is constantly stimulated and structured. Teachers use multi-sensory (i.e., visual, auditory and kinesthetic) teaching modalities to reinforce learning and to accommodate a variety of learning styles.

Teachers tailor instructional materials for all subjects to the reading levels of each student group. In all classes students work on their reading, writing and communication skills while they learn the basic content of a particular subject. This fosters the development of a student's responsibility for his or her own learning. Instruction ranges along a continuum from direct and teacher-controlled to independent activities, whether the class is Reading or Career Education. The program actively engages the student in the learning process. This includes teaching students to reflect on their ability to learn, to recognize their styles of learning, to recognize success and progress and to advocate for themselves. In addition, the faculty helps students access their prior knowledge in all learning situations and guides them to generalize, integrate and transfer new content and skills in a variety of contexts.

name: Learning Experience
details: The Learning Experience enhances the lives of children ages 6 weeks to 5 years. In each contemporary, colorful building children learn in a fun fashion starting with sign language for infants through preschool, technology, early literacy, math, sciences, music, theater, creative arts, dance, physical fitness, nutrition, etiquette and much more. Graduates of TLE are more than prepared to enter Kindergarten and first grade. All the curriculum is proprietary and has been designed, written and published especially for TLE children. At The Learning Experience early learning is an art. We believe that knowledge is like the sky, never ending. Parents dream of the best for their children and at TLE their dreams become reality making those important first years creative, productive, happy and most importantly filled with lots of love.

name: Brown Bear Children's Center
details:
At Brown Bear Children's Center our purpose is to provide a safe, health, emotionally secure environment which invites learning and affirms a child's self-worth. Growth and development are facilitated through discovery, creativity, stimulation and socialization in warm and nurturing classrooms.
Our child-centered program provides children with the opportunity to learn at their own pace with our developmentally age-appropriate curriculum and equipment as the basis of growth and learning. We encourage children to exercise self control, to learn through self-directed activities and to become independent and responsible.
At Brown Bear we foster positive attitudes, which, in turn builds self-esteem, self-reliance, and self-respect in young children. We provide personal attention to the special requirements of each and every child and create an atmosphere of genuine love and appreciation.
We are committed to the support network between parent and caregiver. Frequent communication between both parties is intrinsic to our program. We are always available to discuss any concerns, ideas, or questions in regard to your child and/or our program.

name: Children's Center of Weston @ the Woodland School
details:
The Children’s Center of Weston Inc., was established in 1974 by parents needing extended care for their elementary school children after the regular school day ended. The Center continues today serving the Weston community as a private, nonprofit after-school program for grades K through 5, staffed by professional teachers.


The Center is currently divided into three age groups: Kindergartners/1st graders; 2nd/3rd graders; and 4th/5th graders. The children arrive at the Center after a relatively rigorous academic day. We provide a safe, stimulating, and home-like environment in which children will feel relaxed and happy. We believe they need a non-competitive, supportive setting with choices of activities after their school day. Many activities may be occurring simultaneously, and the low (8:1) child:staff ratio enables us to give children individualized care and attention.


Teachers at the Children’s Center are chosen by their demonstrated skill and sensitivity working with children in groups, ability to thrive in a busy child-centered environment, and congeniality as members of a teaching team.

name: J.F.K. Head Start and Day Care Program
Burlington Montessori School
details:
We understand that sometimes applying to a school can be stressful, especially if this is your first time in the process. We try to make the whole process as simple as possible.

Burlington Montessori School is built upon the educational methods and philosophy of Dr Maria Montessori, where the hand is in direct connection with man’s soul. The whole environment is based on experiences Practical Life, Sensorial, Language, Math, Geography, Art and Science The teacher shows a child how to perform a task, but the child then chooses to practice that task until it is completely understood. The classroom environment is specially prepared to meet the child's needs creating an atmosphere of peace and beauty, rich with meaningful and varied activities; it abounds in love, security, understanding and consistency. Although the classroom is a non-sectarian classroom it will plant the spiritual roots of love, inner peace, peace in the classroom community and peace on earth.

Of course, the best way to learn about us is to visit!
business hours:
Half day:
Full day:
Extended day:  8:00 am - 11:30 am
8:00 am - 3:00 pm
8:00 am - 5:45 pm

name: Academy of Tae Kwon Do
details:
Tae Kwon Do is a Korean Martial arts that literally means Kick, Punch, Way of Life. It is one of the oldest forms of martial arts in the world with earliest records dating back to about 50 B.C. It is also the most practiced form of martial arts style in the world with over 30 million practitioners in over 126 counties.

      At our school, we embody the ancient spirit of Tae Kwon Do. We teach traditional forms and follow the five aims of Tae Kwon Do: Respect, Humility, Perseverance, Self-Control, and Honesty. These are key to help with the moral and physical development of our students. No matter what your personal goals are for learning Tae Kwon Do, we have ability to help you succeed at any age!

name: BASE-Flaherty School
details: The mission of the Braintree Public Schools, in partnership with parents and the community, is to prepare all students to become responsible and contributing members of a diverse and global society. We motivate and enable each student to develop intellect ually, physically, socially, and emotionally through a rigorous and supportive educational program within an inclusive and safe environment that nurtures creative and critical thinking, the development of values, and the pursuit of lifelong learning.

name: BASE-Hollis School
details: The mission of the Braintree Public Schools, in partnership with parents and the community, is to prepare all students to become responsible and contributing members of a diverse and global society. We motivate and enable each student to develop intellect ually, physically, socially, and emotionally through a rigorous and supportive educational program within an inclusive and safe environment that nurtures creative and critical thinking, the development of values, and the pursuit of lifelong learning.

name: BASE-Morrison School
details:
Braintree Public Schools Mission Statement

The mission of the Braintree Schools, in partnership with parents and the community, is to prepare students to become responsible and contributing members of a diverse and changing society.

We motivate and enable each student to develop intellectually, physically, socially, and emotionally through a rigorous educational program within an atmosphere that nurtures creative and critical thinking, the development of values, and the pursuit of lifelong learning.

name: Schoen Family Community Children's Center
details:
Our Mission
The mission of Horizons for Homeless Children is to improve the lives of young homeless children in Massachusetts and help their families succeed by providing high-quality early education, opportunities for play, and comprehensive family support services. To support our mission, we also advocate on behalf of young children, train educators and human services providers, and provide research on the impact of early education on homeless children.
Our Vision
Every homeless child will have the opportunity to learn, play, and thrive.

name: Elements Montessori School
details: Elements Montessori recognizes early childhood education as a means by which to prepare children to live peacefully as adults. Dedicated to the vision of a future marked by environmental stewardship and peaceful living, we offer our children the opportunity to mature with an appreciation for social, ecological, and global interconnectedness. We endeavor that as our children make their way into the world, they find harmony, joy, and peace in all their many relationships…from the classroom to the cosmos.

name: Charlestown Cooperative Nursery School
details:
Our goal is to cultivate the skills that are at the foundation of a life of happiness and success: cooperative and individual problem-solving, analytical thinking, emotional intelligence and empathy, cultural competence – as well as early literacy and math skills and real-world preparation.

To achieve that, our curriculum is built around a series of explorations that grow out of the children's authentic interests. They are playful, but far more than "play" – combining the power of the children's boundless curiosity with an expertly guided investigative approach that immerses the children in the process and joys of real discovery.

Research consistently supports that child-centered early education – emphasizing authentic interests rather than a rigid curriculum – leads to greater levels of information and skills acquisition, increased self-esteem and, ultimately, higher achievement. We have found this approach allows children to consistently exceed the usual educational standards, and to simultaneously develop a robust self-awareness and a joy in learning that will serve them for a lifetime.

name: First Baptist Church Nursery School
details: At First Baptist Church Nursery School, we believe that every child is unique and worthy. We provide a loving and safe environment where prekindergarten children thrive. Our curriculum has been carefully developed by our staff to be age appropriate and engaging. Our outdoor play area offers wonderful opportunities for learning, creative play, social interaction and more.  The First Baptist Church Nursery School's preschool education programs are based upon the principles of developmentally First Baptist Nursery Schoolappropriate practice. Our goal is to give each child a warm environment that encourages the development of socialization skills, independence, and a positive self-image while providing a strong early childhood education. Our experienced teaching staff embraces the view that each child is a unique person with an individual pattern and timing of social, physical, and intellectual development. Teachers manifest their respect for children by encouraging them to think for themselves, to make decisions, to work towards their own solutions, and express their own ideas and feelings.

name: The Belmont Nursery School
details:
We offer a variety of schedules - but, our total hours of operation are 8:00-5:30.  The school is open for a school year program plus an optional summer program.  We use the Belmont Public School calendar for vacations, holidays and snow days.

Children in the older group attend three, four or five days a week.  The children in the younger group choose a two-, three-, four-or-five day program.  If you need advice about which program would be best for your child, please ask the school for help with this decision.

name: Jack N' Jill Chid Care At Marina Bay
details: Choosing childcare is one of the most important decisions a family can make. We at Jack 'n' Jill believe that you can change the world when a high-quality childcare enriches not only your children; yet, entire families and the community. Jack 'n' Jill has a rich heritage of providing a personal touch while caring for children. Our traditions have brought us from 1943 until now. Jack 'n' Jill is committed to providing high quality care with core values that are met by utilizing communication while responding to the needs of children and families.

name: Clinton Path
details: Through study and experience, we as educators know that children learn best through play. This type of learning is salient and ultimately permanent. At CPP we endeavor to create an environment that fosters the development of the entire child as to their specific individual needs. With a distinct balance of teacher led and independent play times, we allow the children to grow their bodies, characters, and intellect, establishing a sense of self-confidence in their abilities. This also fosters cohesiveness as they work together as a group and helps them learn to love school.

name: Dovecrest Montessori Academy
details:
Welcome and thank you for taking the time to read about our school! 

Dovecrest Montessori Academy was founded in 2006. We offer programs for students in preschool, kindergarten and elementary levels (ages 2.9-10 years). As a private Montessori school, our curriculum and programs are designed to build a strong foundation in academics, as well as social, emotional, physical and moral development. This approach encourages a child’s independence, self-motivation, and decision-making skills. Our Montessori and state certified teachers receive continuing education and participate in ongoing training throughout the year. Supplemental teachers specialize in dance, music and art. Our classrooms are designed to stimulate the child’s natural curiosity to explore the world around them.


Our aim at Dovecrest is to create a place that inspires uninhibited exploration of each child's unique curiosity.  Montessori provides us with the tools to guide children through their education in a natural and joyous way.  The method allows for “Order, Self-Control and Independence”. 


We are open from 7:00 AM until 6:00 PM during the school year. The school year is from September to June, following, in general, the calendar for Brockton Public Schools with Summer program in July and August.


It gives us great satisfaction to see our children’s progress on daily basis and we invite new parents to set up a tour of our school to learn about our unique and effective program.

name: East Boston Montessori School
details:
East Boston Montessori School is a private, independent school accepting children from 2.9 to 6 years of age. East Boston Montessori School is a member of Montessori Schools of Massachusetts, North America Montessori Teachers Association and is licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care in Massachusetts.

EBMS is a one-room schoolhouse located in the Orient Heights section of East Boston. We are located next to a public playground (Noyes Park) which provides a safe and excellent outdoor green space for our students to play. We are within walking distance from public transportation on the MBTA’s Blue Line newly renovated Orient Heights Station. Our school’s location also provides a drop off area directly in front of the school building for those driving to school.

East Boston Montessori School is a bright classroom providing an exciting environment for learning.  Our program’s philosophy begins with a deep respect for each child as a unique individual and a deep concern for each child’s social, emotional, physical and cognitive development.  We are a warm and supportive community of students, educators and parents.  Our philosophy encourages and teaches children to be kind, respectful and peaceful.

One of the distinguishing features of a Montessori program is its mixed-age grouping of children rather than a class comprised of one age level.  Our classroom comprises a group of 29 children mixed in ages from 2.9 to 6 years, where younger children learn from older children and older children reinforce their learning by teaching concepts they have already mastered.  This arrangement also mirrors the real world, where individuals work and socialize with people of all ages and dispositions.

Ideally, each child will enjoy a three-year cycle program at EBMS.  When children have the opportunity to stay with the same educator for three years, it allows educators to develop close, long-term relationships with their students, allows them to know each child’s learning style very well, and encourages a strong sense of community among the children.  With a faculty of three to four educators in the classroom there are ample opportunities for each child to receive attention, guidance and support when necessary.

Operating on the principle of freedom within limits, EBMS inspires children to work at their own pace, alone or with others.  Children are encouraged to learn through active engagement with the wide range of materials.  There is also much learning by simply watching the work and behavior of others in the classroom.  East Boston Montessori’s learning environment fosters independence for even the youngest child.  It is our goal to make children independent and be able to do things for themselves.  This is achieved by giving children opportunities to move, dress themselves, to make work/play choices and to help with adult tasks.  Thus, children have many opportunities to experience the feeling of pride and accomplishment at having completed a task on their own, contributing in self-confidence and positive self-esteem.

name: A Place to Grow at Strawberry Hill
details: Our educational philosophy is based on the belief that a child who feels safe, valued and welcomed will develop into a self confident individual who will reach their full potential. We create classrooms that are safe, caring environments where children can learn and grow. At the heart of our philosophy is mutual respect between teachers, families and children. When children feel safe and cared for, then, they are ready to learn.

name: Blue Cross/Blue Shield Center for Children
Kinderhof
details:
Imagine a place where a child’s development is fostered by his/her natural surroundings.

Where movement, balance, and touch are met through nature.

Where the will to work is found in the home and on the land.

Where a social organism is formed and founded based on gratitude and respect for others.

Where families gather to celebrate festivals throughout the year.

Where food is prepared from organic/biodynamic grains and bread is baked from scratch.

Where voices ring out in song and rhyme.

Where children jump for joy!!

If you can imagine such a place then you can imagine Kinderhof Waldorf School.

name: Here We Grow Day Care, Inc. (Pembroke)
details: The purpose of Here We Grow Daycare, Inc. is to provide your child with a challenging environment while he/she is being cared for outside the home during the day. Here We Grow offers flexible programs to grow in independence and at the same time structured activities which are designed to help your child learn self-discipline. Here We Grow offers a wide selection of materials for developmental learning. The program includes active and quiet play, outdoor activities and scheduled field trips throughout the school year.

name: Happy Hollow School
details: Fundamental to Happy Hollow School's preschool and kindergarten philosophy is the belief that early childhood years represent the most vital period in a child's educative process and therefore every activity during this time is a unique opportunity to learn. Given this extraordinary opportunity to set the tone for a child's entire life, the preschool, pre-kindergarten and kindergarten programs at Happy Hollow School create a warm, nurturing and personal environment with structure and content that gently challenges students to explore the world and their own blossoming potential. By design, and for more than 50 years in Framingham Massachusetts, Happy Hollow School has been a small school focused on preschool, pre-kindergarten and kindergarten with a high teacher to student ratio that allows each student to feel appreciated, understood and loved. Most of all, students in our preschool through kindergarten programs are partners with faculty, parents and community in which we all work together building the foundation for a life and love of learning.

name: Bright Horizons Family Center at Landmark
details:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: Condon Community Center
details:
Mission Statement
The Mission of Boston Centers for Youth & Families is to enhance the quality of life for Boston's residents by supporting children, youth and families through a wide range of programs and services.

name: Champions @ Aitken
address: MILDRED AITKEN ELEMENTARY SCHOOL 165 NEWMAN AVE
details:
With more than 30 years experience in the design and delivery of engaging out-of-school-time programs, we know that Champions works – for kids, parents and teachers. Our dedicated team of early learning and school-age education experts have applied the very best in educational philosophies to the Champions approach to learning which focuses first on a quality education. Our programs, from our learning environment to our curriculum to our relationships with the kids, also reinforce 21st century learning goals.

We meet all aspects of a child’s development with fun activities like arts, sports, reading and science exploration, all while aligning our programming to meet your district objectives and even individual school goals. By organizing our programs around your needs, we make it easy to collaborate with Champions to deliver the best fun learning environment for families in your local community, while our operational expertise and responsive service gives you a hassle-free experience.

At the end of the day, everybody gets what they need. You can ensure that children continue to learn beyond the school bell, parents get a safe and convenient place for their child while they’re at work, and children enjoy fun activities with friends that help them learn in non-traditional ways.

name: Champions @ Martin
address: GEORGE MARTIN ELEMENTARY SCH 445 COLE ST
details:
With more than 30 years experience in the design and delivery of engaging out-of-school-time programs, we know that Champions works – for kids, parents and teachers. Our dedicated team of early learning and school-age education experts have applied the very best in educational philosophies to the Champions approach to learning which focuses first on a quality education. Our programs, from our learning environment to our curriculum to our relationships with the kids, also reinforce 21st century learning goals.

We meet all aspects of a child’s development with fun activities like arts, sports, reading and science exploration, all while aligning our programming to meet your district objectives and even individual school goals. By organizing our programs around your needs, we make it easy to collaborate with Champions to deliver the best fun learning environment for families in your local community, while our operational expertise and responsive service gives you a hassle-free experience.

At the end of the day, everybody gets what they need. You can ensure that children continue to learn beyond the school bell, parents get a safe and convenient place for their child while they’re at work, and children enjoy fun activities with friends that help them learn in non-traditional ways.

name: Children's Development Center
details: The school program intends to give each child an educational experience which is appropriate to his/her stage of development. The curriculum encourages each child to be actively involved in the learning process, to experience developmentally-appropriate activities and to pursue his/her own interests. The program encourages each child to become socially and emotionally confident. It will also provide challenging and rewarding experiences for the development of each child's creative abilities.

name: JCC Early Learning Center at Congregation Sha'aray Shalom
details:
The Hingham ELC curriculum is designed to value the child and honor his or her interests and capabilities.  Interpreted through the lens of Jewish wisdom and values, the curriculum encourages community-building, collaboration and mutual respect.

This philosophy guides every aspect of the daily routine, from programming to community involvement. Consistent with the JCC Early Learning philosophy, we believe that social-emotional development is as important as cognitive development. Our team will nurture your child’s intellectual exploration and competencies—and at the same time help him or her to understand his or her emotions, label them, and express them safely and positively.

Hingham is a diverse community. We are the only local Jewish preschool, and are passionate about exposing children to the rich traditions and resources of our culture. We celebrate the fullness of living in a multicultural world while celebrating our heritage through songs, holidays and festivals, blessings, story, dance and exposure to Hebrew language. However, there are no expectations or requirements of background, belief or practice in the ELC; all are welcome at the Center.

The JCC Early Learning Center at Congregation Sha’aray Shalom is licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts and accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC).
business hours:
Classroom Hours

Early Drop-off*

Extended Day
 1-2pm or 1-3pm

name: Hugs Plus Learning Center
details:
Hugs Plus is a learning center which emphasizes a positive approach to all learning.
The creative activities are designed by the classroom teachers to develop self esteem, recognizing each child as an individual. The whole child curriculum offers a multi-sensory, hands on, child centered approach to early childhood education. The vast resources of Hugs Plus foster creativity, independence and sociability.

name: Concord Montessori School
details: The Concord Montessori School was established in 1974, and is a member of the North American Montessori Teacher’s Association (NAMTA). We are located in Concord, Massachusetts. The school year is from September through May. Our school’s philosophy is to foster independence, love of learning, and a positive sense of self in a prepared environment. Every child is encouraged to function independently at his or her own developmental rate. We welcome but do not require parent participation in the classroom.

name: Cole-Harrington Early Learning Center
details:
Cole-Harrington is a private, non-profit community based child care system with child care options available in selected towns in Norfolk, Plymouth and Bristol counties. It operates under the supervision of Enable, Inc. whose mission is to demonstrate leadership in the development, provision and management of innovative social, educational, vocational and health services for children, adolescents and young adults.

Our child care system is dedicated to providing families and children quality child care and educational programs that are community based, developmentally appropriate, and flexible to meet the needs of working parents. Our degreed, professional staff is committed to developing collaborative relationships with parents, family child care providers, and other professionals in the community towards the goal of providing the optimal educational program for children.

name: Chaps Inc. Community Programs For Early Learning
ARC-EN-CIEL Day Care and Montessori School
Artisan Child Care Center for the Arts
details:
Welcome to Artisan Childcare Center provides high-quality childcare for children aged six weeks through six years. Artisan offers a singular curriculum that is well balanced while placing particular significance on artistic programs as valuable tools necessary to make learning fun and enhance academic performance. By honing in on the inherent curiosity of childhood, each student in our program will be introduced to a creative, interactive learning process that will foster both independent and collaborative thinking. Children of all ages will even receive daily music lessons as part of their schedule!

We have 2 convenient locations; on Washington Street (Route 16) in Newton, Massachusetts, and right off of Interstate 95/128 in Woburn, Massachusetts.

That is why at “KIDS CLUB” Childcare and Preschool Center, our unique curriculum gives children both the guidance and the freedom to learn in ways that are meaningful to them. It is more than just daycare — highly trained teachers and staff encourage a child's natural curiosity and wonder within a safe, homelike environment. Children leave “KIDS CLUB” empowered to be creative problem solvers, life-long learners and interesting, interested individuals.

details: The Trust Center for Early Education (TCEE) fosters the intellectual, social, emotional, physical and spiritual growth of small children in a safe, loving, nurturing environment infused with Jewish values. TCEE exists to impart a love of learning, to develop children’s skills, independence and self-confidence, and to engage families in our vibrant Jewish community. Our unique all-day early childhood program supports and contributes to our mission of lifelong Jewish learning – building and enhancing our extended Jewish community. Please visit the TCEE Website for more information.

name: Latchkey at the Wetherbee School
details: Since our inception in 1970, we have served children and families of Greater Lawrence with high quality, non-profit programs. From providing fun, developmentally appropriate learning experiences to healthy meals to physical activity and social learning experiences, we are dedicated to promoting the healthy development of children. Rich programming and caring, highly qualified staff offer peace of mind that students are in exceptional care with us.

name: Bird Street Cmty Ctr. ASP@ Higginson-Lewis K2-8 Before and After
ABC School Age Enrichment at Lanesboro
Hingham Community Nursery School
details: We are committed to providing a nurturing environment that fosters the growth and development of each child. In all that we do, we respect the individuality of our children, giving them the gift of time and the tools they need to grow into themselves. The philosophy of our school is based on the well-proven educational theory that a child interacting in a developmentally appropriate environment will develop socially and emotionally while learning cognitive readiness skills, which are the foundation of later school experience. Our curriculum is supported by classrooms whose configuration allows a child to explore all the areas, each with a variety of materials, appropriate for their age and stage of development. Our commitment is to facilitate a child’s learning through process-based, rather than product-based experience. We utilize the Massachusetts Department of Education’s Early Childhood Program Standards and the Guidelines for Preschool Learning Experiences.

name: Concord After School Program at Hunt Recreation Center
The Creation and Learning Station
details: The Creation & Learning Station provides children with an opportunity to grow, learn and develop in a fun and stimulating way. Our Purpose is to enhance the whole child socially, emotionally, cognitively, creatively, and physically. We focus on meeting every child's individual needs and help foster their unique abilities. We implement a combination of hands on learning and traditional practices. We are a non-denominational Christian Pre-School that enrolls children ages 2.9 - 5 years of age.

name: Good Shepherd Preschool
details:
Good Shepherd School is a community-based, Catholic preschool located at 20 Winthrop Street, Charlestown. We offer classes for ages 2.9-5 years old.
Here students are given the opportunity to work collaboratively and explore friendships but also be nurtured within their individual interests in a structured yet multi-sensory learning environment.

name: Children's Services of Roxbury Early Care & Education Center
Expressions After School Program
details: Expressions After School is an arts-based after school program in Needham, MA serving Kindergarten, Elementary and Middle School children. Our mission is to enrich the lives of our students through exploration of the arts and through artistic expression and sports.  We maintain a high quality series of programs: After School Program, Kindergarten Program and Extended Child Care Programs with a well trained staff who provides personal attention and exceptional care.

name: Belchertown Day School After School Program
details:
The goal of Belchertown Day School is to provide a happy homelike environment in an educational setting which develops the whole child through social awareness, in preparation for continued learning. We take pride in serving children whose families need a high quality child care program while they are at work. We welcome families of all backgrounds and ethnicities. We believe that true diversity is an asset to all who participate in our programs.

We further believe that adherence to principles of child development is crucial to the growth of each young child. Working collaboratively with parents, our teachers and staff create nurturing educational programs that allow children to learn through exploration and discovery, through interaction with a great variety of experiences.

We adhere to the principles of early childhood education as described by the Developmentally Appropriate Practices of the Nationally Association of the Education of Young Children (NAEYC).

Belchertown Day School's mission is to provide a safe, motivating and nurturing learning environment for all children. We are committed to support children's development, respect individual differences, help children to learn to live and learn to work cooperatively, and to promote health, self-awareness, competence, self-worth, and resiliency.

name: The Family After School Program
details: The Family After School Program is an intensive therapeutic program designed for seriously emotionally disturbed children ages six through twelve. The primary goal of the program is to prevent hospitalization and out of home placement for youth who require therapeutic services and cannot attend a regular after school setting. Participants are referred by the Department of Social Services and Department of Mental Health from the Cambridge and Somerville communities.

name: KIDSART!
details:
In the late 1980’s, KidsArts! Multicultural Afterschool Program was born in the old firehouse now home to JP Licks.  For many years, the building was occupied by a vibrant community center devoted to the arts – the JP Multicultural Arts Center, a creation of the Jamaica Plain Arts Council (which now runs JP Open Studios).  The Arts Center was also known as the “FirehouseArts Center”.   The old firehouse bustled with ballet dancers, samba drummers, photographers, jazz musicians, and….kids!   The Center was a multi-generational, open-door beehive of creativity – and it recognized that cuts in public art education mandated a grassroots after school arts program for JP’s children.

When the Center closed its doors in 1993, KidsArts! found a new home in the First Unitarian Church where it still lives to this day.  Many generations of children, staff and directors have helped build a long-standing KidsArts! community.  Scores of children have made monster masks, danced Capoeira, shot music videos, crafted shadow puppets, discussed social justice, and cooked empanadas (among other activities) – delving into deeply creative thinking that is increasingly marginalized in school.  Staff and children have developed countless personal relationships that recognize the unique creative powers of each child.  Over the years, hundreds of families have enjoyed the riches of a program that was ignited by the artists/activists of the old firehouse.

name: Busy Bee Pre-School's Babies
details:
Statement of Purpose
To educate is to lend knowledge, skills, abilities, experiences and variety in a warm, safe and fun-filled environment.

At Busy Bee Pre-School, our true desire is to educate all children in all ways. We believe our classroom is a combination of both old and new views and is full of creative motivating ideas. Our classroom is an environment that your child will remember for a lifetime.

Our goals are basic, yet essential:

Be Happy Be Creative Be Intelligent Be Nice
Be Yourself Be Expressive Be Confident Be Kind
Be Healthy Be Inquisitive Be Attentive Be Giving
Be Informed Be Polite Be Careful Be Helpful
Be Proud Be Fair Be Honest Be Your Best
Bee the Best You Can Be Be Fit Be Imaginitive

We provide a daily curriculum that encourages children to express themselves through creative dramatic play, while at the same time providing academic skills through hands-on experiences that are developmentally appropriate

name: After School Enrichment Program
details: The LEAP After-School Program provides homework assistance, computer literacy, library skills, and multicultural enrichment activities for school-age students in grades 1-12. LEAP is in operation after school on weekdays from September through June at Philadephia Free Library-Chestnut Hill branch. It's an open drop-in program, so no registration is necessary.

name: Bright Ideas Childcare
details:
The goal of Bright Ideas Childcare is to enhance the social development and readiness skills of children. By working together; parents, teachers and the children; we can provide many opportunities for children to grow and learn about the world around them in a safe and nurturing environment. We plan our day in such a way that we can ensure that the children in our care:

    Are safe
    Can feel good about themselves
    Learn to respect the feelings and property of others
    Can develop positive relationships with their peers and adults
    Can learn and play in a positive environment
    Can have fun

name: Bright Horizons Family Solution @ Beacon Hill
details:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: Early Minds Child Care, Inc.
details:
We at Early Minds Child Care understand the difficult decision each parent must face when choosing a daycare center for their child.  That is why we are a friendly, safe and inviting Center, dedicated to making a child's experience with us rewarding and positive.

We consider it our privilege to accompany a child as he/she embarks on a path of growth and exploration.  Through play, a loving staff, and friendships that begin in infancy, children who attend Early Minds build a strong foundation for a lifetime of learning.  If you choose us, we hope that you will soon feel that Early Minds Child Care is the best "home away from home" that you could provide for your child.

Early Minds knows that exceptional teachers are the cornerstone of any child care center. We hold special pride in our Center’s staff. All of our teachers have prior training in early childhood education and have a genuine love for children. Through a variety of activities, games, and learning centers, our staff ensures your child’s first learning experiences are positive ones.

name: Learn and Play Day Care Center
Compass Zone Program
details:
Our mission is to inspire and enable all young people, especially those who need us most, to realize their full potential as productive, responsible, and caring citizens.
  
We pursue our mission with purpose, passion, and patience.  There is neither a more basic nor more important reason for our purpose and passion to be challenged than for us to assist our members in becoming competitive in their basic skills, in their academics, in their ability to participate on the playground, and in their access to computers to overcome the "digital divide."  We approach the challenge with patience.
  
Founded in 1911 and chartered in 1915 by the then fledgling Boys Club of America, the Boys & Girls Club of Plymouth has served the town and its surrounding communities for over 100 years.  The Club's recent history mirrors that of the re-chartered Boys & Girls Clubs of America where "gym and swim" has been replaced with more academic pursuits (basic skills and homework help) - fitness and agility exercises for both the boys and girls are suited to individual and small group physical development.  The Club moved to its own new 17,000 square foot facility at 9 Resnik Road in 2003.  The Club is a 501(c)(3) non profit organization (EIN 04-2103926).
  
The Boys & Girls Club of Plymouth offers young people what they need and want most:  adults who respect and listen to them; a safe environment where they can have fun and be themselves; and interesting, constructive activities that channel youthful energy into challenging pursuits.
  
A youth development strategy underlies all Boys & Girls Club programs and fosters a sense of belonging, competence, usefulness, and upward influence in their Club that builds self-confidence and self-esteem.
  
The Boys & Girls Club of Plymouth is part of a nationwide affiliation of local, autonomous organizations and Boys & Girls Clubs of America working to help youth of all backgrounds develop the qualities needed to become responsible citizens and leaders.  It is facility-based, employs 3 full-time, 11 part-time, and 47 volunteers and offers daily access to a broad range of programs in five core program areas:  Character and Leadership Development; Education and Career Development; Health and Life Skills; The Arts; and Sports, Fitness and Recreation.
  
Today, over 800 boys and girls from all walks of life (and some at risk) are taking advantage of the programs, activities, and services provided by the Boys & Girls Club of Plymouth.  They benefit from trained, caring, professional staff and volunteers who help young people take control of their lives, envision productive futures, and reach their goals.

name: The Hathaway School
details:
Welcome to the Hathaway School !!!
The Hathaway School is presently providing educational programs for students in preschool through kindergarten as well as offering extensive afterschool, summer and school vacation programs for children in grades K-6.  We offer full and part time preschool-kindergarten programs servicing children 2.9 to 5 years of age.  Our preschool and kindergarten programs are nationally accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children ( NAEYC). The programs are designed for each child to develop all the necessary skills and understandings to succeed and thrive academically.  We also provide before and after school programs as well as a summer program for K-6 school age children.  Transportation packages are also available.   
The Department of Early Education and Care (ECC) is the state agency that oversees all licensed child care in Massachusetts and has reviewed, inspected and licensed the Hathaway School for sixty preschool and sixty after school age children. Our preschool classrooms are carefully planned environments where focus is placed on the process of learning.  Each child is encouraged to create, explore, problem solve and investigate through hands-on learning experiences.  Each classroom provides various developmentally appropriate learning centers including; math and manipulatives, reading, writing, sensory science exploration, dramatic play, creative art, cooking and a block construction area.  Children have the opportunity to participate in large and small group activities in addition to individual guided play and discovery.  Each child’s opportunity to participate in developmentally appropriate activities results in success leading to the growth of self-confidence. 
The Hathaway School is a pet friendly environment.  We have a variety of animals within the school such as dogs, fish, birds and hamsters etc. Please be advised of this environment particularly if your child has allergies.
Our curriculum is standards based.  This means, in part, that we utilize the Department of Elementary and Secondary Education’s Curriculum Frameworks as a benchmark in developing our curriculum as well as the Early Education and Care benchmarks for development. Our curriculum always meets but generally exceeds these standards upon completion of a program.  Our students are strongly prepared to confidently meet the challenges when place in any school environment.  We believe in setting high standards for all our students. All children love to learn. It is our goal to find the way to individually address their needs so that going to school is a fun and rewarding experience.  High standards are not just for the academic arena.  We also encourage and provide students the opportunities to develop a sense of pride in themselves, in their school and within their family and community environments.  We believe that this provides the individual child the best possible opportunity to meet with success in our increasingly more globalized world.

name: Grace Works Child Care
details:
GraceWorks is an outreach program of Grace Episcopal Church serving children from 15 months to 14 years of age and their families since 1998. Families are welcomed to our non-denominational, culturally responsive, family friendly environment where children grow socially and academically. We believe children are active participants in their learning and work to build upon their interests and natural curiosity. Oversight of GraceWorks is by the GraceWorks Oversight Committee, a Committee of the Vestry of Grace Episcopal Church.

For the Early Childhood Education classes, families are provided with developmentally appropriate year- round care from 8:00am-6:00pm. The After-School Program is open from 2:30pm -6:00pm after each Monday, Tuesday, Thursday and Friday school day, and from 1:30pm-6:00pm on Wednesdays. The Summer Program enrolls school age children (entering first grade through age 14) in one-week programs for the entire summer break. We offer part-time and full-time schedules for your child. Families may sign up for as few as two days or as many as five for the Early Childhood and After-School Programs.  For our school-age Vacation weeks families can sign up for 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5 days.

name: Christ Church Parish Day School
details: At Christ Church Parish Day School each child actively and creatively participates in their day, thus laying the foundation for the creative and critical thinking process so essential in today’s world. With acceptance for individuality and mutual trust, our teachers help each child develop the necessary self confidence so that he/she may explore and expand her world. Our carefully planned program allows the children to choose from a wide variety of activities and to progress at their pace. Christ Church Parish Day School was established over 50 years ago as an outreach mission of Christ Church. As such, the Day School promotes a harmonious and cooperative relationship between the two institutions. The Day School embraces the value of fostering Christian principles, and we attempt to model these behaviors on a daily basis.

name: Handprints Preschool, Inc
details:
Handprints Preschool is dedicated to providing children and their families with an enjoyable, nurturing preschool experience. We provide a happy environment of learning through play, where children are encouraged to explore, to learn, to question, to make choices, and to share. We offer diverse learning experiences to stimulate the child's creative and intellectual interests, as well as helping them to develop a healthy self-image and acquire independence.
Our program is well balanced, providing early learning experiences of language arts, number concepts, music, arts, science, motor skills, and nutrition in everyday living skills. The exposure to these concepts through playful activities gives the children a good base in preparation for kindergarten.

name: Highlands After School program
details:
The Highlands After-School Program serves Newton middle school children and their families, and provides a safe, supervised, enrichment program that meets the developmental and recreational needs of the middle schooler. Our program strives to provide support and foster independence in our students.

This exciting program brings the fun of Funtastic Friday to all the days of the month! We’re housed in three community centers in Newton Highlands, with a home base in the refurbished Brigham House and daily access to the Hyde Community Gym.

name: Early Minds Child Care, Inc
details:
We at Early Minds Child Care understand the difficult decision each parent must face when choosing a daycare center for their child.  That is why we are a friendly, safe and inviting Center, dedicated to making a child's experience with us rewarding and positive.

We consider it our privilege to accompany a child as he/she embarks on a path of growth and exploration.  Through play, a loving staff, and friendships that begin in infancy, children who attend Early Minds build a strong foundation for a lifetime of learning.  If you choose us, we hope that you will soon feel that Early Minds Child Care is the best "home away from home" that you could provide for your child.

Early Minds knows that exceptional teachers are the cornerstone of any child care center. We hold special pride in our Center’s staff. All of our teachers have prior training in early childhood education and have a genuine love for children. Through a variety of activities, games, and learning centers, our staff ensures your child’s first learning experiences are positive ones.

name: The Kids' Place
details:
The Kids’ Place utilizes the Creative Curriculum©, a nationally recognized curriculum, which you will see evident in all of our learning centers.  We at TKP believe that play is children’s work, so we emphasize learning through play.  Our classrooms are designed to be age and developmentally appropriate with clearly defined learning centers featuring blocks, manipulatives, art, math, science, and dramatic play.  Activity choices are set for children to choose, fostering a sense of independence by finding, using and putting away toys themselves. 

We use Teaching Strategies Gold©, a brand-new, on-going observational assessment tool that helps our Educators teach with intention by focusing on the individual child’s development and learning.

name: Growth Unlimited Preschool
details:
Growth Unlimited PreSchool serves children ages 3 to 5 and their families in the Kingston, Ma area. We are a naeyc accredited program.Our goal of becoming
"a friend of the family" keeps our parent involvement strong. We would like to welcome you to our website! We hope that this enables parents ease and accessibility to their children's Growth Unlimited experience. Since our founding in 1978, our goal has been to remain dedicated to serving each child and their family in a manner reflecting the highest quality in early childhood. Every year we aim at making our program a little better in some way than it was before. This keeps us progressive and contemporary in our field of early childhood education. Parents are supported with workshops, one-on-one consultations, events to meet other families and opportunities to be in the classrooms. We want each parent or caregiver to feel genuinely respected and feel that this is your program too. Together we make a great team that significantly impacts your child's early childhood years in the most positive ways, setting a strong foundation for life.

name: Asian Center Preschool
details:
The Asian Center Preschool,  is fully licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care. This year the school year runs from Sept. 3- June 6.  Children, between the ages of 2 years 9 months, and 5 years are welcome to attend.  The Center’s Preschool is lead by a very experienced lead teacher, Ms. Mai Pho, assisted by  an equally talented assistant teacher Ms. Heywon Lee.   The Preschool is open daily from 9:00 am – 12:00 noon.   

The Preschool classroom is large and airy with play areas for blocks, cars and trucks, a train table, a kitchen/home center, and a book corner. There is also an outdoor play space for balls, riding toys, and active games.

The Preschool curriculum is based on the Creative Curriculum model.  The teacher’s weekly lesson plans include English language development, number recognition and use, science concepts, music and rhythmic movement, arts and crafts, socialization, and large and small motor development.

The Preschool subscribes to The Weekly Reader series for this age group, and partners with Raising A Reader MA, a book-lending program.

The Asian Center’s focus is on teaching English to speakers of other languages, and this is true in the Preschool as well. Preschool families come from many countries, and for most, English is not the language they speak at home. It is our goal to prepare the children to succeed in  Kindergarten, and to that end we stress English language development. We find that children who arrive in September, often speaking no English, are communicating with each other in English by January.  Standardized testing has shown that, on average, the children gain 1+ years of English vocabulary yearly.

name: Devotion School Primary Extended Day Program
The International Child Care Center
details:
We strive to provide children with a strong educational beginning so that they may successfully transition to the school system. We believe that children learn through play and base our program on this. We also recognize that children learn at different rates and in different ways so we provide diversity to accommodate this.

ICCC provides a loving, healthy environment in which children may grow and develop a strong sense of self. Children learn best when they are confident, feel safe and loved by those caring for them, and are able to freely explore the world around them. We strive to provide children with love and security and to keep them active and healthy by providing nutritious meals and challenging activities.

name: Lextended Day Program Estabrook Site
details:
Lextended Day is a non-profit, tuition-supported after-school program serving children from all six elementary schools in Lexington.  The program operates from school dismissal until 6:00 p.m.  

Lextended Day provides a supportive after school environment designed to meet the varying needs of the participating children. Our professional staff is committed to quality child care.  In order to provide each child with adequate attention and supervision, we strive for a student/teacher ratio of 1:10 for children in grades 1-5, and 1:8 for the kindergarten children.

After a nutritious snack, children are given ample outdoor time for free play or to participate in teacher-directed activities.  The school facility and surrounding grounds provide the perfect setting for the variety of small group activities offered each day.

Dance, drama, fine art, crafts, story telling and cooperative games are all part of after-school fun at Lextended Day!

name: For Kids Only at The Whittier School
details: For Kids Only Afterschool (FKO) strives to support the needs of children and families through academic, recreational and social opportunities that enhance school day learning and build upon individual strengths and interests necessary for life long success. Our programs focus on the individual strengths and needs of each child in our care and aims to provide engaging and enriching activities for children in all areas of development: socio-emotional, cognitive, language and physical.

name: Capt Pal School
details:
C.A.P.T. PAL Preschool is an early childhood program that stresses the social, emotional, physical, and intellectual growth of each child. We have been located at the United Parish of Carver in Carver, Massachusetts for over 40 years.

Daily Activities include a free-choice period, a snack, followed by a structured  session that includes academic instruction, music, storytelling, learning games, art, drama, and physical exercise.

Staff
We have an excellent teacher to children ratio. The staff has an extensive background of early childhood education and experience, and is licensed by the MA Dept. of Early Education and Care.

name: Great Beginnings Learning School
details: The purpose of our school is to provide for learning experiences through a stimulating, caring environment, along with providing opportunities for each child to develop at his/her own pace. Our goal is to help children to become secure, sensitive, creative, independent persons striving to reach their full potential. Our program embodies many of the current proven developments in the fields of child growth and psychology. The school offers structured learning activites and an interest center orientated environment that allows children to make choices and to take an active and joyous part in learning. We strive to provide quality beginning education and care for your child. We provide "great beginnings" in your child's development.

name: After School at Little People's College - Fairhaven
details:
Mission
to provide the best possible program of early education, preschool and child care available. A program where children are loved and where children and families feel safe, secure and respected, enabling children to grow to their fullest potential: physically, emotionally, socially, cognitively and in language development.

details: The mission of Citizens for Citizens is to advocate on behalf of low-income residents and address the causes and effects of poverty through the provision of direct and integrated services, the promotion of self-sufficiency, and the advancement of social change.

name: Children's Happy Day School
details: CHDS strongly believes that children benefit most from a child centered environment designed to promote interaction with other children and adults, while providing both choice and structure for each child. Following the guidelines of the NAEYC, teachers create a curriculum that considers the age of the children, the individual child and the social and cultural context in which the children live. Children have the opportunity to work in large groups and small groups. Play and learning centers-such as block, drama, manipulatives, library, writing, art, music-enhance the curriculum and allow children ample time to play and work on social development. Routines are an important part of early childhood education and at CHDS routines give children the opportunity to work on their independence, self-help skills and self-esteem. Opportunities to interact and learn from nature are an important component of the CHDS philosophy. Ms. Helen believes that children benefit from daily interactions with nature. The process of planting tomatoes in the garden, observing the plant’s growth and then taking that first juicy bite is a hands on experience that cannot be reproduced outside the natural world. Watching a tadpole transform into a frog or a caterpillar emerge from a chrysalis show children the beauty and wonder of nature. Such interactions, when supported by caring and nurturing adults, have long lasting benefits for young children. The goal of CHDS is to develop and foster a child’s sense of wonder, to encourage his/her natural curiosity and to provide an environment that fosters each child’s social, emotional, physical and cognitive growth. Our school is staffed by professional and dedicated teachers with BA’s and MA’s in early childhood education. At CHDS, respect for the child is priority while he/she learns the concepts of sharing, fairness and respect for others. We are committed to eliminate social, religious, marital, sexual and disability discrimination.

name: Hawthorne Kids Club
details:
The Boys & Girls Club of Greater Salem engages a Formula for Impact that ensures that success is within reach of every young person who walks through our doors with all members promoted from one grade to the next and on track to graduate from high school with a plan for the future, demonstrating good character and citizenship, and living a healthy lifestyle.

This Formula is accomplished by employing caring adult professionals, utilizing nationally tested programs including those that are evidence-based, and understanding that we are “Powered by the Community.”

Every day we expand the minds and broaden the horizons of our youth while also developing their sense of belonging to the community.

We are committed to support children's development, respect individual differences, help children to learn to live and learn to work cooperatively, and to promote health, self-awareness, competence, self-worth, and resiliency.

details: The Day-After-Day After School Program (D.A.D.) is committed to providing safe, high-quality childcare for elementary school-aged children (K-6). name: Little Chelsea's Learning Center
details:
Greetings, and thank you for visiting our website. There’s a lot of things to check out. Feel free to poke around our Questions and Answers, where you can learn about the ins and outs of our center. You can browse through Life at Little Chelsea’s, which details some of the great programs and benefits of sending your child to our Center. And while we’re talking about sending your child… You can enroll for application online.
Once your child has been successfully enrolled, you can also use this site to pay for the child’s tuition online, using either PayPal or your credit card. Our goal is to provide you with the absolute highest level of service. Our staff is always ready to answer any questions you may have, so feel free to ask.

name: Bright Start Academy
details: Bright Start Academy is a preschool in Worcester, MA that offers nursery and kindergarten programs with the convenience of a day care center. Established in 1983, we have been preparing and shaping young minds through our developmentally appropriate instruction and holistic teaching methods while at the same time, helping children build self-confidence. We offer full- and part-time schedules from 7:30 AM to 4:00 PM, as well as after-school programs and tutoring for children ages 5 to 10 or MCAS preparation.

name: Kathy Corrigan Gymnastics Nurs & DCC
details: Kathy Corrigan’s offers a full Day Care Program. The hours are 7:00 am until 6:00 pm for infants through five years. The school is licensed by the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care. Our school continually maintains its reputation for quality and excellence in helping children develop not only physically but intellectually, socially, & emotionally. Kathy Corrigan’s School of Gymnastics, one of the first private schools of its kind to open in the United States, offers one of the largest and most modern Gymnastic & Day Care facilities available. In existence for 44 years, the school continually maintains its reputation for quality and excellence in helping children develop not only physically but intellectually, socially & emotionally. Our Philosophy at the school is that when the mind and the body are developed together in  an atmosphere of warmth and fun, a child’s readiness for learning is enhanced. Therefore, each fun filled day will include a half day Pre-School program, Gymnastics instruction, and Physical Education related games and activities. We quote the ancient philosopher Plato:  “A Sound Mind in a Sound Body.”

name: Crescent Day Nursery
details: Crescent Day Nursery began as a response to a need  in the community for child care for working parents. In June of 1959 Crescent Day Nursery was licensed as the first full time daycare in North Attleboro MA. Gertrude McCue knew the importance of fun and laughter as an integral part of learning.  Gertrude included Preschool and Kindergarten groupings into her daily routines and thus Crescent Day Nursery offered educational kindergarten before the state of Massachusetts mandated public school to provide kindergarten. Today we continue her basic philosophy of having fun while learning and reaching for the stars.

details: At Children's Express Learning Center, we recognize and respect the uniqueness of each child.  We believe it is extremely important to give every child a strong, educational foundation for their future, a positive self image, consistency, and a loving,warm environment.  We pride ourselves on our compassion and commitment to each family, and the long term relationships we have formed over the years.
