name: Conte Kid's Club
address: CONTE COMMUNITY SCHOOL 200 W UNION ST
details:
Berkshire Children and Families offers exceptional education and care for children from birth through pre-kindergarten in Pittsfield. BCF also offers before- and after-school care programs for older children.

In BCF’s infant, toddler and preschool programs, your child plays, learns and thrives with extraordinary early childhood professionals. Our full-day, year-round programs provide education and care tailored to your child’s unique personality, individual needs and style. When it’s time for kindergarten, your child will be ready to go, and ready to shine.

Our programs are accredited through the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) and licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

name: The Childrens Korner
details:
Here at The Children’s Korner we believe that the children learn best when they are in a warm, exciting, stimulating, and safe environment surrounded by love and happiness. We do promote pro social behavior here. Each child is encouraged to learn at their own pace both on their own and in a group. Our curriculum is based on each child’s individual abilities.

Our staff is all highly trained and licensed through the Department of Early Education and Care. Each staff person also is trained in First Aid and CPR by the American Red Cross as well as has nutrition and choking training. All staff must complete a minimum training hours per year.  Any staff member, volunteer, or intern must complete a background check in order to be in the facility and working with the children. Finally, all staff must have on file evidence of an 2 MMR vaccination’s, along with a physical which must be updated yearly.
 
We stress that every family stay involved in their children’s school life. We do have an open door policy allowing families to come in and visit at any time through out the day. Children always enjoy visits from Mom and Dad. We believe you, the parent or guardian, are the most important people in your child’s life and any parent participation is greatly appreciated. The Children’s Korner does not discriminate on a basis of religion, race, cultural heritage, sexual orientation, political beliefs, marital status, disability, or national origin. We do not discriminate against any child that is not toilet trained.  We do believe that everyone is equal!     

Our goals at The Children’s Korner are to provide children with a safe environment where they can feel at home. We pride ourselves on our relationships with parents and staff.
business hours: Monday–Friday, 7 a.m.–6 p.m. | Closed Saturday & Sunday

name: Growing Places Pre-School
details:
We believe…
Small groups lead to BIG results!
Growing Places embeds in its philosophy the unique concept of sub-grouping our already
small class sizes. Each child gets more direct access to the teacher, and the teacher gets
a greater opportunity to truly observe how that child learns.
Most importantly, small groups give us the opportunity to embrace who each child is
individually and help make each child feel valued, unique and part of a larger community.

name: A Place to Grow at the Stratton School
details: A Place To Grow Childcare at Strawberry Hill Rd, Concord MA. Founded in 2007, we offer care to Infants, toddlers, preschool and PreK aged children on a full and part time basis. All programs are licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care. Our educational philosophy is based on the belief that a child who feels safe, valued and welcomed will develop into a self confident individual who will reach their full potential. We create classrooms that are safe, caring environments where children can learn and grow. At the heart of our philosophy is mutual respect between teachers, families and children. When children feel safe and cared for, then, they are ready to learn.

name: Associated Early Care Education Inc. - Castle Square
Associated Early Care and Education /Children's of Cambridge
Brighter Beginnings Child Care LLC
details: We believe each individual child will unfold his or her personality and abilities in time. Our program encourages this unfolding in an environment that is rich in nurturing, understanding, and learning. Brighter Beginnings Preschool/Child Care Center offers an independent early childhood program packed with educational experiences for young children. Our program promotes the physical, emotional, and intellectual development of children. We carefully planned this program in such a way so as to enhance your child’s total development. Our program is based on monthly themes, webs, and emergent curriculum that encourage a wide variety of experiences and self-expression.

name: Cushman Scott Children's Center
details:
ushman Scott Children's Center is an independent, non-profit educational center serving children ages 15 months to 7 years old and their families. Located in the lovely Amherst, MA village of Cushman, the school is rich in history and beauty. Its bright, spacious classrooms create a home-like environment, with space for active play and quiet activities.

Our educational philosophy is based on the Reggio Emilia Approach. Teachers balance structured activities with free play in a program that helps children to develop emotionally, physically and intellectually as they learn about themselves and the world around them.

Our program offers the enriching educational opportunities of a traditional preschool, combined with optional summer and extended-day programs. We offer families flexibility in choosing which days their child attends and for how long, allowing each family to create the Cushman experience that is right for their child.

name: Bright Horizons @ Spring St.
details:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: Giving Tree School
details: Giving Tree School is a nonprofit educational organization, founded by Betsy Evans and Jeff Coulson, that has been providing programs for young children since 1976.  It is a preschool for children ages 2.9 through 5 years.  Children and teachers participate together in a developmental curriculum designed to foster social emotional, cognitive, and physical growth, as well as respect for individual expression and experience.  Giving Tree is accredited by both the National Association for the Education of Young Children and by the High Scope Educational Research Foundation, ensuring that the school meets the highest standards for early childhood educational programs.

name: The Learning Experience
details: The Learning Experience enhances the lives of children ages 6 weeks to 5 years. In each contemporary, colorful building children learn in a fun fashion starting with sign language for infants through preschool, technology, early literacy, math, sciences, music, theater, creative arts, dance, physical fitness, nutrition, etiquette and much more. Graduates of TLE are more than prepared to enter Kindergarten and first grade. All the curriculum is proprietary and has been designed, written and published especially for TLE children. At The Learning Experience early learning is an art. We believe that knowledge is like the sky, never ending. Parents dream of the best for their children and at TLE their dreams become reality making those important first years creative, productive, happy and most importantly filled with lots of love.

name: Kid's First Daycare and Learning Center Inc.
details:
Kids First Daycare and Learning Center, Inc. were established in January of 1999.  Kids First Daycare and Learning Center, Inc. is a Private School created to provide an alternative Learning environment for multicultural inner city children.  The Center offers a comprehensive range of services in addition to daycare.  Currently our enrollment can accommodate up 60 students ranging in age from infants to 7 yrs old.

Kids First Daycare and Learning Center, Inc. provides an array of programs and services that are designed to meet the family’s needs.  The program has a successful history of collaboration within the community and beyond.  Our daycare is currently involved with the following programs/services:

name: Salmon Centers for Early Education
details: SALMON Centers for Early Education strive to provide a joyful and supportive environment with a blend of fun and structured educational and social time for our children. Because social and emotional readiness are crucial to successful later accomplishments, our daily activities promote children’s active participation in a setting reinforcing a sense of security and self-esteem. Outdoor play, imaginative games, independent discovery, group experiences and intergenerational activities are all part of their days with us. In our healthy, loving environment, every child receives the appropriate nurturing, guidance and stimulation to reach his or her fullest potential.

name: Crosby Partnership Preschool
details:
Berkshire Children and Families offers exceptional education and care for children from birth through pre-kindergarten in Pittsfield. BCF also offers before- and after-school care programs for older children.

In BCF’s infant, toddler and preschool programs, your child plays, learns and thrives with extraordinary early childhood professionals. Our full-day, year-round programs provide education and care tailored to your child’s unique personality, individual needs and style. When it’s time for kindergarten, your child will be ready to go, and ready to shine.

Our programs are accredited through the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) and licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

name: Creative World Children's Learning Center
details:
Creative World Children's Learning Center is locally owned and operated. It has been incorporated since 1999 and there are two locations in Southern Massachusetts. The South Easton center is located at 130 Depot Street and our Raynham center at 84 Forge River Parkway.

 

The South Easton center accommodates 100 children ages 6 weeks to 8 years of age. The center consists of 8 classrooms all equipped with Internet viewing access, and a large indoor play area displaying 3 giant playhouses as well as 2 fenced playground areas. The building is bright with pastel colored doors, skylights and pitched ceilings. Programs are available for Infants, Toddlers, Preschool and Kindergarten. There is a choice of full time or part time schedules to meet the needs of all parents. Our Raynham location is similar in many ways but has 9 classrooms and is licensed for 111 children.

 

In a supportive and safe environment, where your child feels welcome and successful, our experienced, caring, and certified Early Education and Care Teachers guide children in developing their social, emotional, cognitive and physical skills. We provide your child with a natural, nurturing and stimulating setting that allows for learning, exploration, social interactions and lots of play.

 

Because children learn differently than adults, they need hands-on experiences and well trained teachers to provide warmth, enthusiasm and encouragement. Most of all, they need the joy and challenge of doing different things themselves. That's what helps children learn, grow and thrive and this is what we offer each any every child at one of our centers. We strive to make the child care experience rewarding and enjoyable for everyone.

name: Jack-n-Jill Child Care of Whitman
details: Choosing childcare is one of the most important decisions a family can make. We at Jack 'n' Jill believe that you can change the world when a high-quality childcare enriches not only your children; yet, entire families and the community. Jack 'n' Jill has a rich heritage of providing a personal touch while caring for children. Our traditions have brought us from 1943 until now. Jack 'n' Jill is committed to providing high quality care with core values that are met by utilizing communication while responding to the needs of children and families.

name: Busy Bees Preschool Center, Inc.
details:
Busy Bees Preschool Center, Inc.  Offers early education and care services to children ranging in ages from 2 months to 5 years old.

Busy Bees has been licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care (DEEC) of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts since 1975, and is NAEYC accredited through November 2017.
    

◊ The Center offers full-day and partial week (year round), Monday through Friday, 7:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.

◊ Busy Bees offers (USDA) breakfast, lunch, and snack at no cost to families.

◊ Languages spoken at Busy Bees include English and Spanish.

◊ Busy Bees develops curriculum using MA Guidelines for Preschool Learning Experiences (linked to MA Curriculum Frameworks) in the framework of Creative Curriculum®, and conferences with families using the CreativeCurriculum.net assessment tool.
business hours: Monday through Friday, 7:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.

name: Little Folks Community Day Care Center
The Grafton Children's Daycare and Preschool Center, Inc.
details: The Grafton Children's Daycare & Preschool Center located in Grafton, MA has been fully licensed to provide an early childhood education from the Commonwealth of Massachusetts since 1993.  We offer Toddler Programs, Preschool Programs, Pre-Kindergarten, Kindergarten and Before and After School Care.  We are dedicated to the many families in Grafton as well as the greater Blackstone Valley.  We are striving to provide an important first stepping stone in your child's early education through dedication, enrichment and a sincere love of children.

name: Learn and Grow Child Care Center
details: We offers high quality full day child care for infants, toddlers and preschoolers in a nurturing, classroom setting providing age appropriate curriculum and materials for each child to learn and grow at their own pace in each area of development meeting their social, emotional, physical, and cognitive needs.

name: Little Kids Inc
details:
Little Kids, Inc. is a family owned and operated business that has been serving families on the Upper Cape since 1982!  We have a Preschool program, a Pre-K program, and two Infant & Toddler (mixed age group) programs.  We are licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care, caring for children ages four weeks to 7 years.  Little Kids is well known for our "family like" atmosphere and friendly staff.  We take pride in our school and the work we do, so that we may offer families the highest quality care possible.  It's our goal to make our center a place where children are able to; learn, grow, explore, make friends, feel welcome and comfortable with their surroundings, and most of all be loved!
     Diane Gummow and her husband Cubby built the school in 1982, and were the owner and operators for just about 30 years!  Tammy Inman (formerly Gummow) and her husband Greg, bought the school from her parents in November of 2011 and hope to continue to run the business for another 30 years!!  Tammy and Greg aslo came to school here, where they first met in our Pre-K program, which makes their story even better!
     Tammy is the Onwer and Director.  She has worked at Little Kids, Inc. for over 17years!  She is Lead Teacher and Director certified, and has worked in every classroom. She spent her first 11 years at LKI in our Main I/T group, working as a loving teacher and caregiver.  She now has a daughter and son of her own, Fia and Ryder, who are students in both of our I/T groups!  Tammy is a hands on Director who likes to spend time in the classrooms, more so than in her office!  She focuses on; creating welcoming, clean, and safe learning environments, having open, honest and frequent communication between staff and families, and meeting the needs of each individual child and family we serve.  She strives to create long lasting, meaningful relationships with all our families, making LKI a great school and family to be a part of!

name: Gan Keshet
details:
During the early years, children form their basic attitudes towards learning, themselves and others. At Gan Keshet we strive to support a child’s development of self-confidence, respect and empathy for others, intellectual curiosity, creative expression, and a positive identity.

Gan Keshet offers a rich, nurturing, play-based learning environment where children, families and staff together explore “being a community.”   We strive to create an environment for children to explore, question and develop an authentic voice.  Families and staff, of diverse backgrounds, partner together as we introduce the Jewish community and its values. Our curriculum focuses on social, emotional, and physical development while fostering intellectual curiosity and cognitive growth.

Since children grow at different rates, individual and group activities are offered.  Children are encouraged to be actively involved in the learning process.
business hours:
Mon - Thu: 
8:30 am - 5:00 pm
Fri: 
8:30 am - 2:30 pm

name: Honey Tree Nursery School
details: Are you looking for a place for your children to blossom? For over 31 years, Honey Tree Nursery School Inc has been providing children in the Raynham, MA area and surrounding areas with quality early childhood development and preschool. We are State Licensed and Fully Insured with Certifications. We ready your children for Kindergarten, in a socially and developmentally appropriate program for children ages 3 - 5. Our teachers are educated and qualified under the Massachusetts Curriculum Frameworks. Give Honey Tree Nursery School Inc a call today!

name: Carew Street Head Start
details:
Our MISSION
Holyoke • Chicopee • Springfield Head Start, Inc. is committed to providing low-income children and their families with a Beacon of Hope and source of support for a brighter future. We strive to do so by providing high quality comprehensive child development services to enrolled children and empowering families to achieve stability in their home environment.

Our CORE VALUES
Excellence • Respect • Diversity • Communication Team Work • Flexibility • Dedication • Shared Vision

Our HISTORY
Since 1965 HCS Head Start Inc. has been providing high-quality early childhood education services for children and families in cities and towns located in Western Massachusetts, including Holyoke, Chicopee, Springfield, Ludlow, Palmer, and Granby. Head Start provides a solid foundation for children to gain necessary skills to enter kindergarten and to be successful in life. Our centers are fully licensed by the MA Department of Early Education and Care. For a complete list of the cities and towns we serve, contact us at (413)788-6522.

name: Christ Church Nursery School
details:
When you enter Christ Church during the week, the joyful sounds of children playing, singing and laughing. We love children and the children and families that make up the Christ Church Nursery School are no exception.  

From the three and four year old classes to the new 2.9  (two years and nine months) program, the Nursery School is constantly creating dynamic and developmentally appropriate programs for our children.

name: Crispus Attucks Children's Center
details:
At Crispus Attucks Children's Center, we nurture and care for each child individually, helping them grow up strong and smart. Every day, our trained teachers guide children through a range of multi-sensory activities that help them learn, share, and most of all enjoy their childhood. From babies as young as one month to boisterous pre-schoolers up to age six, Crispus Attucks Children's Center is there to guide your child through all stages of their development. Find out more about the diverse, caring, and enriching experience we can provide for your child.

Families come first at Crispus Attucks Children's Center, and our staff is happy to work with you to make sure we are meeting your needs. Another advantage of CACC is our experienced staff: most of our head teachers have been with the Center between five and 20 years.

name: HeadStart @ Meadow Lane
details:
It is our goal to work with families and assist children to develop socially, cognitively, physically, and emotionally while fostering a positive self-image and love for learning that will help them succeed in our program, in public school and later in life.

 

We are dedicated to ensuring that all children and their families have an opportunity for a significant Head Start experience through support and partnership with community and staff, while emphasizing positive child outcomes through family participation.

name: The Kids' Place
details:
The Kids' Place first opened in West Springfield, Massachusetts in 1982 with a  goal to provide quality child care services that were based in sound educational philosophies. Teacher selection, training, and curriculum planning are designed to create a warm, nurturing environment, where children are accepted for the unique individuals they are and to challenge them to develop socially, emotionally, and cognitively.

Since 1982, The Kids' Place has grown to include eight locations throughout western Massachusetts and Connecticut. Our staff is our most important resource in the success of The Kids' Place, both in the past and moving into the future. Many of our policies and practices have been a result of staff collaboration at all levels. Our staff enjoys seeing many of the children we taught come back - looking for the same quality of education they once received to provide now to their own children.

name: Citizens for Citizens Ext Day-Greene School Site
Carriage House Harvard Campus
details: The Carriage House Schools offer childcare, preschool, pre-kindergarten and kindergarten programs and services at three child-friendly centers conveniently located in Milton, MA.  We provide life skills learning programs that foster each child's growth and development, because we believe that, "play is a child's work, children play to learn, to grow and to experience the world around them." We have created an atmosphere that entices each child to play and learn, providing the age appropriate tools to reach his/her maximum potential in a safe, loving environment.

name: Curry Early Childhood Center
details: The Curry Early Childhood Center is an integral part of the Curry College Community. The Center provides a warm and nurturing educational experience for infants, toddlers, and preschool children. The Center also offers Curry College students an opportunity for authentic and integrative learning experiences. We reflect the mission of the College to value individual differences while promoting students' cognitive, social, physical and emotional development. The philosophy of the Curry Early Childhood Center is to provide a safe, nurturing, and cheerful educational setting where learning takes place everywhere and at all times. The curriculum is based on a child's natural curiosity and desire to learn; through play, practicing skills, and experimenting with materials, children learn about themselves and the world around them. We strive to foster individuality, creativity, and independence and create an environment where children feel free to explore and express themselves. The uniqueness of each family's composition and cultural traditions is valued as we strive to develop a relationship with each family where staff and parents work together to support the development of each child.

name: Agawam School Age Childcare Program - Middle School
details:
Agawam School Age Childcare is licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care (EEC, the Massachusetts licensing agency) and follows all EEC regulations. Our program was developed for school-aged children in grades K-6 and our staff is committed to providing them with a nurturing, constructive and happy environment. Enrolling your child in this program will prevent immature decision-making and also prevent behaviors that can occur when children go home to an empty house.

 

Children are our number one priority and are the reason we strive to meet all of their educational, physical and emotional needs. Our staff greets all students daily and ensures that each child is made to feel as an important part of the group. Children are given individual attention whenever possible, which we feel, is so crucial before and after a busy school day. Safety is a big concern and our goal is to improve socialization skills while building children’s self-esteem.

We encourage and guide children to become independent thinkers and offer a wide variety of small and large group activities to support child development. We offer homework assistance to students so families do not have to focus most of their quality time on school assignments in the evening. We also provide children with free time so that they can unwind at the end of their structured school day.

 The program will communicate with families frequently by the use of daily contact at arrival and dismissal times, phone calls when appropriate, and newsletters. If at any time you have a question, concern, or suggestion you are encouraged to share them with the staff. Please contact the Site Coordinator or the Director and remember that your input is always welcome.

name: Island Children's School, Inc
details:
Island Children’s School has changed and grown over the years. We are one of the oldest preschools on Martha’s Vineyard, begun in 1969 as a free school in the town of Gay Head. Eight children were enrolled that year. There was no tuition, and no salary was paid to the teachers. Although the school has been refined quite a bit from those early years, threads of the original philosophy, particularly an emphasis on creative arts, are still a part of our curriculum.

In 1993, Island Children’s School realized a longstanding dream. Under the guidance of long-time director Elaine Allen, and thanks to the efforts of many people, the program was moved to our own building located at 5 Halcyon Way, next to the West Tisbury School. In 2006, we completed the first stage of renovation/expansion inside the building.  In 2012, we completed the second stage of renovation with an massive upgrade to the playground.

name: Kidsborough @ Elmwood School
details:
At Kidsborough we aspire every day:
    To teach, practice and instill effective study habits and engage each child to become a lifelong learner.
    To support children in their social and emotional growth by creating an environment of inclusion, safety and respect for all.
    To encourage personal creativity through a variety of enrichment-based activities.
    To develop positive and dynamic relationships with families where communication is encouraged, comfortable and enhances the development of each child.
    To provide opportunities to build strong bodies through healthy eating choices and active, physical play.
    To pursue meaningful endeavors, that unite our Kidsborough population in serving our local communities.

name: Boys and Girls Club of Greater Westfield, Inc.
details:
Mission Statement 
To inspire and enable all young people, especially those that need us most, to reach their full potential as productive, caring and responsible citizens.
The Boys & Girls Clubs of Greater Westfield provides:
    A safe place to learn and grow
    Ongoing relationships with caring, adult professionals
    Life-enhancing programs and character development experiences
    Hope and opportunity

name: Bonnie's Program at the Ann T. Dunphy School
details:
We understand how important it is for working families to have quality school-aged child care. We strive to offer a program that meets the needs of our community.

Our goal is to help children feel good about themselves and their relationships with others. We feel that a well-rounded after school program can be instrumental in a child's development. To meet the needs of all children, we have developed a balanced program that offers opportunities for recreation, socialization and academic support.

Bonnie's Program has been in place at New Hingham Regional Elementary School, serving the towns of Chesterfield and Goshen since 2000, in Westhampton since 2003 and in Williamsburg at the Anne T. Dunphy school since 2005. All programs have great success with offering homework support, socialization, recreation and a structured environment for children.
business hours:
After school care: 3 pm- 6 pm Monday- Friday

Half day care: 11:45 am - 6 pm

name: Kids' Club Before School at Shawsheen
details:
The Before School programs open at 7:00 am. Enrollment is on
a rolling basis throughout the year. Drop in care is available once approved
by the Kid's Club office.
***Drop in care can not be an option on delayed openings because of
staffing ratios or unless approved by the Kid's Club office.
Before School is a quiet, relaxed time to enjoy:
• time with friends & teachers
• planned curriculum guided by teachers
• open exploration & play which includes:  art, building, reading, games, gym time & outdoor time
The children may bring breakfast if they wish.  At some schools, breakfast is available for a fee.  At approximately 8:20am, children may join friends on the playground as they arrive for school.
The overall philosophy, both Before School and After School, is to help children become independent, self-reliant, resourceful, capable of reasoning and thinking, able to problem solve and make good choices.  Kid's Club is a place to learn social skills, conflict resolution and problem solving; to be ready for the challenges that face them as they confront life's issues.

"Kid's Club After School is located at 65 Phillips St. The main childcare rooms are developmental in design, allowing children to make decisions within defined limits. The classrooms include the following areas: reading and group time, computer and homework, art, sensory, sand and water, science and writing, manipulative, games, blocks or construction and dramatic play. Activities outside of these areas are also offered, such as cooking, sports, music, movement, and carpentry. Programming allows for free play, homework choice, quiet time, snack and outdoor play.

The program follows the Andover Public School calendar. Kid's Club is closed during the summer (but has a summer program), most holidays and December vacation week. It is open during February and April school vacation weeks, based on the needs of the current user group. It will remain open on snow days (depending on the severity of the storm) and in-service days.

The Kid's Club program has 200 slots. Actual enrollment is based on the distribution of slots throughout the week. Group size varies depending on the activity; ratios are maintained at approximately 10:1. The staff reflects a diversity of training and experience in early childhood education and childcare. Staff development and training opportunities are offered throughout the year.

The teaching staff offers conference time (at parents request) for a more thorough discussion of a child's progress. Written progress reports will be maintained in each child's record and are available for parental review with a staff member. This communication between parents and teachers is essential in creating a program that not only meets parents' needs, but also provides an enriching and comfortable environment for the children."

name: The Goddard School
details: The Goddard School uses the most current, academically endorsed methods to ensure that children have fun while learning the skills they need for long-term success in school and in life. Our talented teachers also collaborate with parents to nurture children into respectful, confident and joyful learners.

name: Children's Circle Nursery School
details: Children's Circle Nursery School is a preschool program recognizing the "gifts" of children. The program, although structured, allows children to spread their wings and soar. The curriculum emerges from the children's expressed interests and teachers' observation of children's needs. Children's Circle is designed to bridge the gap between pre-k and kindergarten with developmentally appropriate activities and projects using both indoor and outdoor environments.

name: Kaleidoscope Preschool
details: Your child will be developing in many areas: Fitness, academic achievement, and social experiences in our 4 hour program. While the children work in the preschool room there will be an academic focus on curriculum including letters, numbers, and colors which are incorporated into a weekly theme.  A different theme each week will provide excitement during craft, story time, and more!  The program will also include your child developing gross motor skills, coordination and self-esteem.   We believe children learn through hands on experiences.  We will challenge and stimulate each child.  Your child will be encouraged to become actively involved in his or her own learning process.  View our Preschool Brochure for more information.
business hours: 9am-830pm Monday, Wednesday, Thursday; 9am-8pm Tuesday; 3pm-730pm Friday; 9am-1pm Saturday

name: Bellingham Afterschool Experience - Clara Macy
details: Play, learn, and grow in our School’s Out program which offers a before-and-after-school experience with healthy, constructive enrichment activities. A nutritious snack is offered daily. We follow the eight core contents of the YMCA’s School-Age Curriculum, which incorporates literacy, science, technology, health, wellness and fitness, arts and humanities, homework support, service learning, character development, and social competence and conflict resolution.

name: Castle Hill Academy
details:
Choosing the right preschool and children's center is a big decision. You want the best for your child. But which program will offer the appropriate combination of care and educational opportunities? How do you know you are making the right choice?

At Castle Hill Academy, we make the right choice easy. That's because we've developed a comprehensive child care and child development program that also offers maximum support and value for your child and your family. Enrolling your child at Castle Hill Academy is one of the best decisions you will make for your child’s future. Here is where excellence begins.

Our goal is to care for your child in the most nurturing, creative, supportive and educationally innovative environment within a secure and spotless facility. We take every measure to provide an environment that is safe and healthy, both inside and out.

Castle Hill Academy is open from 7:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m., five days per week. We offer programs on a five, three or two-day per week basis, year ‘round.

name: The Goddard School
details: Our approach is based on accepted research that clearly indicates the deepest, most genuine learning occurs for children through play and fun activities, lovingly guided by highly trained teachers. We deploy the talents of highly trained teachers and educational directors to prepare your child for social and academic success. Our Educational Advisory Board and Goddard Systems University ensure our faculty maintains the highest standards in early childhood education. Your child is offered ample opportunities to develop his or her natural curiosity and creativity through exploration and discovery, guided by caring teachers who cultivate these moments for lasting understanding. Every school is co-led by an on-site owner and education director who work together to make sure every family has a wonderful experience. This distinctive model also ensures children feel known and appreciated for their individual gifts and personalities.

name: Holyoke YMCA After School Program - Pine
Apple Seeds Preschool
details:
At Apple Seeds Preschool, our philosophy is to provide a safe and nurturing learning experience to all children of different developmental abilities. At Apple Seeds, we recognize the uniquenesses of the "whole child," and build upon their strengths and weaknesses socially, emotionally, physically, and cognitively. We accomplish this through our interactive program using a hands-on approach through thematic learning centers and related projects. Our well-planned program encourages children to learn about the world around them through exploration, discovery, and imagination. We employ teacher-directed learning centers, coupled with cooperative and independent learning centers, for maximum learning for your child. Our projects created in class have a specific purpose and are related to either a story we have read in class or connected to our thematic unit.

In addition to projects and learning centers, Apple Seeds also believes in the importance and power of learning through play. Play is necessary for the maturation of all areas of learning and development. Through play, children develop interpersonal relationships, the ability to work cooperatively, and the ability to solve conflicts. It also improves hand-eye coordination and both small and large muscle development. Children learn to express their feelings, to cope, to be creative, and to enjoy learning. Children also develop the various cognitive processes such as predicting, classifying, and observing, and learn new concepts. It has been well documented that play is necessary in the development of language, which promotes future successes in reading and writing, which is why we consider it an important learning tool in our program.

At Apple Seeds, we pride ourselves on providing quality Education, Knowledge, Experience and a Shared Philosophy that parents are their children's first teacher and together we form a partnership to build the foundation of their lifelong education.

We are licensed through the Department of Early Education and Care.

name: Dartmouth Early Learning Center
details:
The mission of DELC is to support the essential nurturing and guidance that is critical to healthy growth and development of young children by offering a rich home-familiar learning environment where children's curiosity and hunger for learning are promoted through play, discovery and the arts. Our programs are designed to help children build positive self-images, develop competence and positive dispositions toward learning and school, and to learn basic skills of social living. The work we do at DELC is intimately related in aim, in method, and in materials used to fundamental assumptions about how, what, and why children learn. Our constructivist approach is child centered, hands-on and humanistic and is aimed at the harmonious development of the whole child in all areas. It is meant to reflect a variety of developmental levels among children taking into account their many individual characteristics and special qualities. Our emphasis is on helping children discover and work towards their own style of learning, construct meanings, and use freedom in a carefully prepared environment.

Our philosophy of education has developed over the twenty years that we have been teaching young children. While we have integrated the ideas of many fine educators, we have been most inspired by the Reggio Emilia preschools in Italy whose aim is to "preserve the spell of the child unbroken." The basic components of Reggio Emilia include viewing the child as powerful rather than powerless; using an emergent curriculum that is based on the interests of children; engaging in projects that are not limited in time or scope; and documenting the child's progress with words and pictures.

While we design developmentally appropriate readiness activities for our children to explore, we recognize the educational value of children finding and solving self-defined problems that arise from child-initiated activity and choices. Through shared activity and social exchange children co-construct their knowledge of the world using one child's ideas to develop anothers or to explore a path yet unexplored. The teacher does not direct children's learning in lock step fashion, rather facilitates it through the selection of stimulating materials, the arrangement of the environment, and our day to day interactions with children. Our role as teachers is to set the stage for learning, to offer encouragement, and to gently guide the learning and development of the children in our care. We feel that what really matters in early childhood education is the spirit of the young child that needs to be nurtured, the reason he/she learns so well. As children become increasingly institutionalized, it helps to keep in mind that what happens to this spirit has far more consequences than any specific content in schooling. A program with this kind of focus sets the stage for positive attitudes about one's
self, about school, and learning is likely to produce children who feel that learning is enjoyable, meaningful, and rewarding.

It is our firm belief and guiding philosophy that children learn best through play, and that play is their very significant form of work. Play puts learning in a context and gives it a purpose. Through play children are given a chance to try out options, to make meaningful personal choices, to explore solutions to problems, and practice new skills without getting bored. Children need to play in an environment rich in resources, to explore, to test, and to learn from feedback on their own actions. We recognize the intrinsic worth of play and provide ample opportunity, time, and materials for this purpose.

Our schedule has a built in, yet flexible structure that alternates between periods of free play, small group activities and special projects, circle time, snack, story, music, movement, and outdoor play. We strive to create a balance between active and quiet times, and between self-selected and teacher-directed activities. Children are encouraged to express their feelings, to develop powers of concentration, to use their imaginations, to try new ideas, to develop a sense of independence and responsibility for one's decisions, and to accommodate other children's viewpoints.

In all of the children's daily activities emphasis is placed more on process rather than production. Teachers acting as partners rather than as sole imparters of knowledge, help children develop self esteem and visual awareness as well as strong social, problem-solving and communication skills. As fellow investigators, they help children explore and experiment in depth, and express their ideas not just in words, but in many visual forms that may be more understandable to them, such as drawing, painting, construction, and creative dramatics.

These goals are best achieved in an educational setting that offers security as
well as challenge. We strive to create a sense of community by supporting the
bond between parent and child by including parents in program planning, by
inviting parents to participate in as many activities as their schedules allow, by encouraging parents to participate as classroom volunteers, and by sharing our special knowledge of children in frequent and supportive conferences and group discussions. In addition to expanding our program offerings, such cooperative efforts by staff and parents enriches our center and reinforces a sense of community and an enriched family life.

name: Creative Playschool
details:
Creative Playschool is a full-day preschool/daycare center serving the Greater New Bedford area.

Our philosophy is to encourage each youngster to advance at his/her own rate. All children are unique and tend to develop at their own individual pace. We guide them in patterns which include physical, social, moral, mental and educational aspects to learn to live an effective life. Our intimate environment encourages interpersonal relationships with other children and teachers. We encourage parent involvement.

name: Anthony Perkins Community Center After School Program
The Joy of Learning Montessori Group Child Care Program
For Kids Only Afterschool @ Brown School
details: For Kids Only Afterschool (FKO) strives to support the needs of children and families through academic, recreational and social opportunities that enhance school day learning and build upon individual strengths and interests necessary for life long success. Our programs focus on the individual strengths and needs of each child in our care and aims to provide engaging and enriching activities for children in all areas of development: socio-emotional, cognitive, language and physical.

name: Children's Horizons, Inc.
address: (NEW PARISH HOUSE-FIRST PARISH CHUR 353 GREAT RD
details: Children's Horizons Preschool was founded by Audrey Davidson in 1987 in Stow, Massachusetts. A second site was added in 1989 at the First Parish Church on Main Street in Bolton. Both locations have grown into well-established community preschools and continue to serve families from Stow, Bolton, and the surrounding communities. Children's Horizons' primary goal is to provide a developmentally stimulating and caring environment for all children. We realize each child is an individual with his/her own interests, skills and values. We assist children in developing their interests and by recognizing their personal learning styles. We coordinate our programs with the area schools in preparation for future learning. We offer a program that enables children to learn as they play. We promote both child-initiated and teacher-directed activities to cultivate imagination and creativity. We believe the process of a child's work is always more important than the finished product. We help foster a love of learning and encourage students through developmentally appropriate activities and lessons. Each child learns at his/her own pace and due to our low student-teacher ratio (1:6) we are able to offer individual attention to each child. We incorporate all areas of child development in our curriculum through English language arts, math, science and technology/engineering, history, social science, the arts and health education. We offer individual, small group and large group activities.

name: Bright Horizons Children's Center
details:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: Children's Express Child Care, Inc
details:
Caring for children in Attleboro for 11 years since 2002

    No Annual Registration Fees
    15% Sibling Discount for full-time enrollments
    Nut-Free Center, 11 years experience with children and food allergies
    Licensed by Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care
    Strong focus on Building Healthy Social Skills
    Enrolled in the Massachusetts Quality Rating Improvement System

name: A Child's Wonderland
details:
At A Child's Wonderland, we teach readiness skills through fun and exciting topics. The teaching style is both formal and informal with a hands-on approach to learning that is the main focus of our program. We feel that children learn best by directly experiencing their environment. We encourage this learning through a variety of means such as cooking, planting, creating, dancing, singing, storytelling and sensory activities such as sand and water exploration. In addition, readiness skills will be incorporated into our curriculum: colors, shapes and patterns, number and letter recognition, and science concepts. Ample time is allowed for the development of fine and gross motor skills through the use of manipulative, indoor/outdoor gym equipment and group games.
     Language development is emphasized in our curriculum. Through art, music, early literacy and other age appropriate activities your child will be given many opportunities to use expressive language and devlop good listening skills.
     We feel that an exposure to a wide variety of experiences and ample time for imaginative play, your child will develop an eagerness for learning. To enhance the curriculum, we may invite a guest or parent from the community to visit our center or go on a field trip.

name: Cowlicks + Pigtails Child Care Center
details:
Our company is based on the belief that our customers' needs are of the utmost importance. Our entire team is committed to meeting those needs. As a result, a high percentage of our business is from repeat customers and referrals.
 
We would welcome the opportunity to earn your trust and deliver you the best service in the industry.

name: Guild of St. Agnes @ Worcester Arts Magnet
details:
Welcome to the Guild of St. Agnes, a long-standing, educational, private, non-profit child care agency. Founded in 1913 the Guild's mission is to: Provide families with quality, affordable, early childhood education and school age programs in a safe, nurturing, environment for children 4 weeks to 12 years. Today, the Guild is the largest early education and care agency in Central Massachusetts, serving approximately 1,450 children in 7 child care centers, 100+ licensed family homes and 11 school age programs.   All of these services are licensed by the  MA Department of Early Education and Care and our centers are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC), the premier designation in the United  States for identifying high quality child care services.  

The Guild offers developmentally appropriate learning environments for your child. Our programs use Teaching Strategies GOLD, which is an assessment, reporting, and curriculum planning system. This helps us to plan meaningful activities that match your child's strengths, needs, and interests, to track his or her progress on these over time and to build a strong foundation for your child to be ready to succeed in school. The Guild is very proud to have taken a leadership role in educating our teachers. All Lead Preschool Teachers hold a bachelor's degree in Early Education or a related field. Many of our teacher assistants have associate degrees or are currently enrolled in college.

In addition to our child care programs providing children with developmentally appropriate learning environments, the Guild also offers working parents year-round services to supplement  and support the childcare. These important services are: transportation, nutritious meals, and behavioral health services and referrals.  In doing so, we serve the whole child and aid you in your role as you raise your child.

name: Evergreen Garden
details: Evergreen Garden Playschool is a Waldorf Early Childhood Program. We are a community that fosters the growth of young children, parents, and the joint adventure they undertake – family. We see ourselves as dedicated solely to the unique period of a child’s life called early childhood, birth to age seven. In this stage of life, children learn primarily through imitation. We strive to create rich learning environments providing young children with teachers who are worthy of imitation in thought, word and deed. Evergreen Garden Playschool aims to nurture the development of children’s imaginative capacities; their desire and ability to engage in social and physical activity; their reverence for life, nature, and beauty; their curiosity and sound logical reasoning. We recognize that each child has a unique individuality that must be met with loving acceptance and guidance.

name: Cape Cod Children's Place
details:
OUR MISSION
Cape Cod Children’s Place is a non-profit resource, referral, and education center committed to providing high-quality care, support, and advocacy for families with young children in order to sustain a healthy community for Cape Cod’s future.

name: Dennison Memorial Sch Age DayCare
details:
Offering high quality extended day and summer programs for school-aged children and teens.
Our mission is to improve the educational attainment and personal development of at-risk youth and families by providing education, recreation and intervention services in a safe environment.

name: Julie's Family Learning Program
details: Julie's is a community based family support and education program that is committed to the development of strong, stable, healthy family functioning. Julie's provides services that enable poor, at-risk mothers and their children to transform their lives and become healthy, successful, and economically self-sufficient members of their communities.

name: James' Place
details: The primary goal of James Place is to serve the children and families of the Amesbury community by providing and maintaining a quality program filled with creativity, activity, and nurturing for school age children, in other words “a neighborhood without streets”.  We are open Monday through Friday, providing before and after school care for children in kindergarten through age 13.  We are open for full days of care when school is not in session, including vacations, snow days, and summer.

name: The Garden City Children's Center
details:
Garden City Children’s Center was founded by an enthusiastic educator who realized that there was a need for quality care in a child centered environment.

Garden City Children’s Center takes great pride in being a smaller child care center. We take every advantage to get to know our families on a personal level. We maintain an open line of communication with our parents concerning the individual needs and progress of the child. We strongly encourage and welcome parents to participate in our program through sharing skills and services and by offering opportunities to spend time participating with the children in their day to day activities.

Garden City Children’s Center is licensed to accept infants, toddlers and preschoolers and welcomes any opportunity to share and show new families the place where children love to play and learn. Please contact us anytime to arrange a tour of our classrooms.

name: Boyd Center For Child Care and Development-Ramco
details: Give your son or daughter a solid foundation for learning with the early childhood program at John E. Boyd Center for Child Care and Development in Fall River, Massachusetts. Tapping into your child's natural curiosity, we motivate him/her to always reach for the next level of education.

name: Crayon College, Inc.
details: Crayon College believes that children learn and develop best when in a secure, loving environment. Since we are concerned with the whole child, we aim to balance their development in all areas: social, emotional, physical and intellectual. Our teachers are dedicated to helping children grow at their natural pace by building their self-confidence, strengths and skills. Simply stated, the philosophy of Crayon College is to provide high quality, safe, secure care and learning experiences for children in a positive atmosphere.

name: Ayer Community School, Inc.
details:
The Ayer Community School was incorporated in 1974 and has served the Ayer area ever since.  Families enjoyed a half-day program until the fall of 1996 when a quality childcare program was added. 

Today children come to Ayer Community School for preschool, prekindergarten, part time and full time childcare, as well as before and after school care for school age to age 9. 

The Ayer Community School takes pride in its team of early childhood professionals.  The ACS staff is truly unique because of its 7 experienced, outstanding staff members and because of its extremely low staff turnover.  90% of the staff are mothers who bring valuable life experiences into the classrooms.  

The staff are all certified by the MA Department of Early Education and Care; they are well qualified and all are committed to early childhood education.  All are trained in CPR and First Aid.

The staff plans a balance of teacher directed and child initiated activities with individual learning styles considered.  This welcoming staff provides an inviting, homey environment for its ACS children!

Our staff has been trained on an assessment system called Teaching Strategies Gold. The teaching staff participated in a 151/2 hour training program. This  assessment program allows our center to apply for grant monies from the state under its UPK (universal Pre-Kindergarten) program.

name: Bonnie's Program
address: New Hingham Elementary School PO BOX 300

name: Children's Paradise, Inc
details:
we are a day care center with 2 different locations. One at 4 waldo street and the other one at 3132 acushnet avenue in new Bedford Massachusetts.
We have been in business since 1998 and we take children from a month old to 13 years of age.

name: Crayon Campus Learning Center
details: At Crayon Campus, Inc., our staff is committed to the belief that children can achieve a great deal. It is the role of the caregivers to build upon those skills that children have mastered. We believe that most of life’s learning – including how to learn – occurs in the first five years of life. Since each child learns at his/her own pace, our staff will allow your child to learn at their own rate while exposing them to a wide variety of opportunities. This will instill confidence and allow them to succeed socially and educationally.

name: Bright Stars Preschool
details:
Bright Stars Preschool is one of 63 schools across the country who have been awarded Project Learning Tree’s GreenWorks! Service Learning Grant.    Bright Stars installed an outdoor nature classroom this past Summer. Parents, staff, family and contractors volunteered time and funds.  Donations of supplies and technical assistance were made by the Langwater Farm, members of the Easton Garden Club and The Town of Easton DPW. This valuable participation of the community is one of requirements of this competitive grant.

With this grant, the outdoor classroom will be made more sustainable with rain barrels and compost bins, and an expanded curriculum will educate the children about the natural environment.

name: Fun Club at Hajjar School/Rogers St.
Appleton Preschool Early Learning Center and Child Care, Inc.
Echo Falls Preschool
details:
Echo Falls Preschool is located in Newton Lower Falls, Massachusetts.  This is our 27th year - the school was founded in 1987 and has been in continuous operation ever since.

At Echo Falls we believe in teaching children to love and respect themselves and others.
• Children grow socially and emotionally through play
We believe in teaching children to love learning.
• A love of learning creates a foundation for resiliency, curiosity, and healthy self-esteem through accomplishment.

name: 1-2-3 Grow Child Center
details: Our mission and philosophy: to provide outstanding, innovative and enriching programs to children of all ages, in a safe, clean fun and rewarding environment.

name: Little Corner Schoolhouse Too
details:
Little Corner SchoolHouse was founded in 1989 as a co-educational facility, servicing the needs of parents and their children from 3 months to 5+ years of age.  Our programs include Infant, Toddler, Preschool, and Pre-K. 

At Little Corner SchoolHouse we recognize the needs of each individual child and work hand in hand with parents to provide a safe, loving, and learning environment.  Our child-centered environment promotes growth in all areas of development - social, emotional, cognitive and physical.  The developmentally appropriate curriculum helps to develop the child's self-esteem.  We encourage self-help skills and support our children's natural curiosity to explore and experiment.  Our program fosters respect and teaches our children to appreciate the cultural diversity in our school.  We will celebrate customs and rituals that link our diverse cultures together with other families.

At Little Corner SchoolHouse, we understand that the most effective teachers are those who cherish children and take great pleasure in them.  Teachers are the cornerstone of our organization, upon which is built the interaction with children that reflects a sincere commitment to and respect for children above all.

Little Corner SchoolHouse shall not discriminate in providing services to children and their families on the basis of race, religion, cultural or national heritage, political beliefs, marital status or disability.

name: Almost Home Nursery and Daycare, LLC
Hands-On Montessori School
details:
At Hands-On Montessori School, we provide a foundation for personal and academic growth and success. We encourage students to become engaged and excited with their schoolwork through active learning. Students are encouraged to pursue studies in all areas of their spontaneous personal interest using hands-on “experiential” learning through concrete manipulative learning materials, experimental discovery, and group experiences. Hands-On Montessori School is committed to both high standards of individual academic achievement while at the same time respecting the child’s human dignity and well being.

Our school offers programs for families with children ages 18 months to 9 years old in a fully equipped, child centered Montessori environment. All classes from primary to Lower Elementary are guided by highly qualified Montessori trained lead teacher and assistants. We invite families to contact us to make an appointment to observe a class in session.

name: Appleseed Academy of Child Development
details: Our philosophy and goal at Appleseed Academy of Child Development is to enhance the overall development of our students: socially, emotionally, physically, cognitively, and academically.  Through a balanced combination of both free play / child-directed, and structured / teacher-directed activities, each child is given the opportunity to learn, problem solve, be challenged, achieve success, and become self-gratified.  With an atmosphere of love and warmth, all children will experience a developmentally appropriate hands-on approach to various materials and experiences to satisfy their own interest and self-discovery.  Our goal is to foster social children who will someday grow to be compassionate, self-confident members of our society.

name: Bright Beginnings Learning Center
details:
Bright Beginnings Learning Center offers programs that encourage continuous learning and growth experiences.  We give children the opportunity to learn based on the developmental level of the group and the individual strengths and needs of the child.  Through play and active learning, our activities promote optimal physical, emotional, cognitive and social development while teaching respect for oneself and others; ultimately building positive self esteem.
Bright Beginnings Learning Centers offers Infant, Toddler and Pre-School programs.   We are a group childcare center licensed by the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care (EEC).

name: Bright Horizons at Wayland
details:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: Kalia Care, Inc
details:
Welcome to Kalia Care Daycare Center where we are dedicated to providing a safe, nurturing environment for your child. We are proud to encourage, educate and help develop the social skills our children need to prepare them for academic excellence and success in life.

I designed and opened the first Kalia Care Daycare Center in Lakeville, Massachusetts in 1997 after researching childcare for my young daughter. Unfortunately, what I discovered was unsuitable for our needs. I became inspired to develop and build a center that the community would be proud of, while filling a tremendous need for quality childcare in the South Shore area. Kalia Care Daycare Center is a family-owned business that provides the highest standard in quality childcare and educational experience.

As our community’s demand for our services increased, so did the desire to continue our Early Childcare philosophy. We opened additional schools; Kalia Care in 1999, Kalia Kids in 2002 and Kalia 4.0 in 2009. Our growth and success is due in part to our continued passion and commitment to provide nurturing teachers, a rich curriculum and a close working partnership with our parents. Our mission is to continue to innovate and improve our programs and services. We pride ourselves in being an active member of our community and are mindful of the cultural diversity of the children in our program and those throughout the world.

It’s our privilege and our goal to make your child’s learning a pleasant and enlightening experience. We thank you for visiting our Kalia Care Daycare Center website and we invite you to contact us for a tour of our Centers.

name: The Arbors Kids at Bowie
details: The Arbors Kids is a family owned business with a simple philosophy - we truly care about children. Whether it’s child care services, vacation and summer camps or before and after school programs, we will provide you with the professional services and caring attention your family needs.

name: Children's Development Center
details:
At Children's Development Center, we have a deep understanding of what makes children tick. Our focus is on helping them develop their potential through a healthy mix of educational and recreational activities.

 It's up to all of us - including the parents - to encourage our kids to bolster their own personal development, independence and creativity. Because this cannot be done without the support of family and friends, we support the parents in educating their children in a manner that is consistent with their own values and beliefs.

Together, we can prepare your child for the wonderful life that lies ahead!

 What children need is what they get at Children's Development Center:

    Early exposure to languages
    Early music education
    Exercise
    Preschool-level academic work

name: Berkshire Children and Families
details:
Berkshire Children and Families offers exceptional education and care for children from birth through pre-kindergarten in Pittsfield. BCF also offers before- and after-school care programs for older children.

In BCF’s infant, toddler and preschool programs, your child plays, learns and thrives with extraordinary early childhood professionals. Our full-day, year-round programs provide education and care tailored to your child’s unique personality, individual needs and style. When it’s time for kindergarten, your child will be ready to go, and ready to shine.

Our programs are accredited through the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) and licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

name: The Goddard School of Braintree
details: Our approach is based on accepted research that clearly indicates the deepest, most genuine learning occurs for children through play and fun activities, lovingly guided by highly trained teachers. We deploy the talents of highly trained teachers and educational directors to prepare your child for social and academic success. Our Educational Advisory Board and Goddard Systems University ensure our faculty maintains the highest standards in early childhood education. Your child is offered ample opportunities to develop his or her natural curiosity and creativity through exploration and discovery, guided by caring teachers who cultivate these moments for lasting understanding. Every school is co-led by an on-site owner and education director who work together to make sure every family has a wonderful experience. This distinctive model also ensures children feel known and appreciated for their individual gifts and personalities.

name: Latchkey at the Frost School
details:
Throughout our history, we have maintained an ideal of supporting children and their families within a larger circle that includes their neighborhoods, schools, cultural groups, and employers along with local, state, and federal agencies. We strive to provide the highest quality of education and care for children by:
    offering rich programming that addresses the intellectual, social, emotional, and physical development of children.
    assessing the development of children in all programs; developing individual goals based on the results.
    implementing special services on-site as needed; speech/language therapy, occupational therapy, physical therapy, and mental health therapy are available.
