We realize each child is an individual with his/her own interests, skills and values. We assist children in developing their interests and by recognizing their personal learning styles. We coordinate our programs with the area schools in preparation for future learning. We offer a program that enables children to learn as they play. We promote both child-initiated and teacher-directed activities to cultivate imagination and creativity. We believe the process of a child's work is always more important than the finished product. We help foster a love of learning and encourage students through developmentally appropriate activities and lessons. Each child learns at his/her own pace and due to our low student-teacher ratio (1:6) we are able to offer individual attention to each child. We incorporate all areas of child development in our curriculum through English language arts, math, science and technology/engineering, history, social science, the arts and health education. We offer individual, small group and large group activities.

name: Berkshire Children and Families - Redfield House
details:
Berkshire Children and Families offers exceptional education and care for children from birth through pre-kindergarten in Pittsfield. BCF also offers before- and after-school care programs for older children.

In BCF’s infant, toddler and preschool programs, your child plays, learns and thrives with extraordinary early childhood professionals. Our full-day, year-round programs provide education and care tailored to your child’s unique personality, individual needs and style. When it’s time for kindergarten, your child will be ready to go, and ready to shine.

Our programs are accredited through the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) and licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

name: Carriage House Nursery School
details:
The Carriage House is uniquely well suited to learning and activities for toddlers, preschoolers, and pre-k students. The rooms are bright, cheerful and well equipped with a variety of age appropriate materials. Quiet areas are provided in each room for the enjoyment of books or just snuggling.

In our Toddler Program, children from 18 months to 2.9 years are gently introduced to socialization in the very relaxed, calm, fully equipped space furnished with appropriate sized equipment, play and learning materials.

The outside play area is a fully enclosed playground space with a close circuit large structure that incorporates a variety of large motor activities on a state-of-the-art soft playground surface.

name: East Boston Head Start
details: ABCD provides innovative, timely programs that promote upward mobility and a higher quality of life for people and communities. Empowering people by providing them with the tools to overcome poverty, live with dignity & achieve their full potential. ABCD responds to the needs of our community through our decentralized, city-wide network, which includes 14 unique neighborhood centers.

name: Just A Wee Day Care Center, Inc.
Acton Barn Cooperative Nursery School
details:
Mission:
The Acton Barn Cooperative Nursery School (The Barn) is a non-profit 501(c)(3) early educational organization in Acton and Littleton Massachusetts. Our school provides a warm, safe, creative learning experience for preschoolers. The cooperative model promotes collaboration between families and professional educators and celebrates the unique journey of every child.

Philosophy:
“Learning through play” best summarizes the school’s philosophy of education. Materials are accessible- located where children can reach them without adult assistance. Because we believe a child learns by doing, we feel it is important for children to become involved in their own learning and to become successful on their own terms, with educated, experienced teachers available to guide each child’s journey at the Barn.

name: 1-2-3 Grow Child Center Inc.
details: Our mission and philosophy: to provide outstanding, innovative and enriching programs to children of all ages, in a safe, clean fun and rewarding environment.

name: City Of Cambridge DHSP @ Russell Youth Center
The Children's Workshop
details:
At The Children's Workshop, our first priority is your child. And because we're run by parents, with young children like yours, we strive every day to create warm, nurturing, environments where children can explore and learn.

Our experienced team of early childhood professionals is committed to the unique and individual development of every child in our care. Each of our teachers is a professional in the field of early childhood education and has been carefully selected through an extensive interview and orientation process. In addition, all of our teachers receive ongoing classroom support, supervision, continuing education, and extensive opportunities for professional development.

We're not a large company with a cookie-cutter approach. Each of our programs is unique and designed to reflect the community it serves. We utilize The Children's Workshop Curriculum Framework, a research and evidence based curriculum created by our bright and talented education team, which provides enough flexibility to be tailored to your child's interests (which we know can change daily) and the needs of our families.

We pride ourselves on providing children and their families throughout Massachusetts and Rhode Islandwith high quality care and learning. We are committed to providing excellence in education for young children. We opened our first center in 1990, and we have since grown to 19 early learning centers. Our main objective is to ensure excellent programs, dedicated caregivers and classrooms that are warm and inviting. We invite you to learn more about our programs and to become part of our family "where learning is child's play"!

name: Leaps & Bounds Preschool
details:
At Leaps & Bounds Preschool, our philosophy is to help children learn through positive and age appropriate educational and play experiences.

We offer children a creative curriculum which includes extraordinary projects, dramatic play & music, time to play with their peers and learning how to be a friend - all in a comfortable, safe and happy environment.

name: Haverhill YMCA ASP at Pentucket Lake School
details:
MISSION
Our Y welcomes all. We strengthen communities, educate and nurture children, and promote healthy living in spirit, mind and body. 
Vision Statement
Where all children, adults and families are healthy, confident and connected.
Our Values
Caring, Honesty, Respect, and Responsibility.

name: Carriage House Nursery School
details: The Carriage House Schools offer childcare, preschool, pre-kindergarten and kindergarten programs and services at three child-friendly centers conveniently located in Milton, MA.  We provide life skills learning programs that foster each child's growth and development, because we believe that, "play is a child's work, children play to learn, to grow and to experience the world around them." We have created an atmosphere that entices each child to play and learn, providing the age appropriate tools to reach his/her maximum potential in a safe, loving environment.

name: AGAPE Childcare and Family Life Center, Inc.
Bright Beginnings Nursery School
details: Bright Beginnings Nursery School in Lenox, MA. serves children 2.9- 5 years old and their families. We are NAEYC certified and licensed by the state of Massachusetts.

name: JCC ELC - Wayland
details: Temple Shir Tikva is proud to host the Jewish Community Center (JCC) Early Learning Center (ELC) of Wayland within our building. Teachers at the JCC Early Learning Center believe nurturing children in a warm, caring environment enhances their confidence and willingness to inquire, explore, and experiment. The focus is on developing all aspects of development: cognitive, physical, emotional, social and language with a respect for individual differences. The school offers a rich early learning experience inspired by Jewish values and traditions. The JCC ELC is a place of joy, learning, and social connection for children and their families. The Learning Center offers a flexible program for children ages 15 months - 5 years. Hours of operation are Monday-Thursday, 8 a.m.-5 p.m. and Friday, 8 a.m.-4 p.m. Families can choose a half-day program from 9 a.m.-noon or an extended day.
business hours: Monday-Thursday, 8 a.m.-5 p.m. and Friday, 8 a.m.-4 p.m.

name: Kids Count Playschool, Inc.
details:
For 20 years Kids Count, a private preschool, has been educating children 2.9 to 6 years of age in the Boxford, Georgetown and surrounding communities.
We offer three different programs: Preschool, Pre-kindergarten and Kindergarten. Kids Count is conveniently located on the Boxford /Georgetown, Massachusetts line. We are minutes away from routes 95 North and South. Established 20 years ago, Kids Count continues to be one of the finest academic-based Preschools on the North Shore.

name: The Learning Garden, Inc
details: The Learning Garden is a private nonprofit preschool, offering developmentally appropriate programs for children agaes 3-6 years as well as extended day programs. We're open Monday - Friday from 8 am - 5pm servicing the Lower Cape towns of Orleans, Eastham, Brewster, Chatham, Harwich. We are licensed by Early Education and Care and we are proud of our student-teacher ratios in all our programs. We support children and their families by developing confidence, respect, and trust in a nurturing environment. Our school is located on a 2 acre parcel of land in Orleans and was establishd in 1983 with sunny cheerful classrooms and a large well equipped playground

name: Bambi Nursery School
details: Our goal is to provide for a very young child a meaningful environment, relating to their needs and interests. Under the guidance of trained teachers, our programs are planned to help the individual child grow and develop physically, socially and intellectually. Careful selection of educational materials and equipment designed for free use and experimentation are involved in a warm and friendly environment.
business hours:
Hours of Operation:
Monday–Friday, 7:30 a.m.–5:30 p.m.

name: For Kids Only at The Lafayette School
details: For Kids Only Afterschool (FKO) strives to support the needs of children and families through academic, recreational and social opportunities that enhance school day learning and build upon individual strengths and interests necessary for life long success. Our programs focus on the individual strengths and needs of each child in our care and aims to provide engaging and enriching activities for children in all areas of development: socio-emotional, cognitive, language and physical.

name: Little Patriots Early Learning Center
details: The mission of Little Patriots Early Learning Center is to provide a safe, nurturing and developmentally appropriate learning environment that supports infants, toddlers and preschooler’s social, cognitive, emotional and physical development necessary to construct their own knowledge and prepare them for their future school success

name: Plymouth KinderCare
details: KinderCare Learning Centers is committed to your child's future. With our experienced staff and innovative programs unlike any other, we provide your child with an unsurpassed learning experience. Your child will discover that learning is fun, while making new friends and building strong relationships with teachers who partner with you in your child's education.

name: Bright Horizons @ Sudbury
details:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: Boyd Center for Child Care and Development-South Main
details: Give your son or daughter a solid foundation for learning with the early childhood program at John E. Boyd Center for Child Care and Development in Fall River, Massachusetts. Tapping into your child's natural curiosity, we motivate him/her to always reach for the next level of education.

name: Ballardvale Preschool
details:
Ballardvale was established in 1972 as a non-profit organization serving neighborhood children from Andover and surrounding communities.  We offer our families large, bright and cheerful classrooms, flexible schedules and continuous communication from loving, well educated teachers.  We have a large, fenced-in playground and we are conveniently located near Interstate 93.
* Two, three, four, and five day schedules available.
* Two morning sessions 8:45am-11:30am and 8:45am-1pm
* Lunch Bunch- Daily 11:30am-1pm
* Stay n' Play- Daily 1pm-2:30pm
* 5 to 1 student to teacher ratios
* Experienced Teachers with 20 plus years working at our preschool
* Located near Route 93
* Spacious classroom for ages 2.9 to 5 years old
* We follow the USDA guidelines and serve healthy nutritional snacks
* Peanut Free Facility

name: CAAS Head Start/ Windsor Center
details: The program is designed to serve children 3-5 years of age from families who qualify for Head Start services in Somerville and Cambridge. CAAS Head Start helps all children succeed by providing comprehensive services to children through activities that help them grow: socially, emotionally, cognitively, and physically. These services lay the foundation for life long learning and continued school success. Children transition from our program into elementary schools prepared and ready to continue to learn and grow. Parents are encouraged to become partners with the program since CAAS Head Start recognizes you as your child’s first teacher. Working together will allow us to make your Head Start experience more valuable for both you and your child. We offer opportunities for you to become involved in classroom activities direct involvement in the decision making of program planning and operation. The CAAS Head Start program is operated by the Community Action Agency of Somerville, which also provides additional services in the Somerville community.

name: Learning Step by Step Day School, Inc.
Belchertown Day School Before School Program
address: SWIFT RIVER ELEMENTARY SCHOOL 57 STATE ST
details:
The goal of Belchertown Day School is to provide a happy homelike environment in an educational setting which develops the whole child through social awareness, in preparation for continued learning. We take pride in serving children whose families need a high quality child care program while they are at work. We welcome families of all backgrounds and ethnicities. We believe that true diversity is an asset to all who participate in our programs.

We further believe that adherence to principles of child development is crucial to the growth of each young child. Working collaboratively with parents, our teachers and staff create nurturing educational programs that allow children to learn through exploration and discovery, through interaction with a great variety of experiences.

We adhere to the principles of early childhood education as described by the Developmentally Appropriate Practices of the Nationally Association of the Education of Young Children (NAEYC).

Belchertown Day School's mission is to provide a safe, motivating and nurturing learning environment for all children. We are committed to support children's development, respect individual differences, help children to learn to live and learn to work cooperatively, and to promote health, self-awareness, competence, self-worth, and resiliency.
business hours: Monday through Friday from 7:15 AM until 5:30 PM

name: 1-2-3 Grow Child Center, Inc.
details: Our mission and philosophy: to provide outstanding, innovative and enriching programs to children of all ages, in a safe, clean fun and rewarding environment.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: Kiddie Kampus
details:
Kiddie Kampus is a family owned and operated Child Care Development Center that supports children and their families from infancy to teens.  Founded in 1989 by Marjorie & Ray Nunes, Kiddie Kampus is conveniently located in Dartmouth.   Our three unique facilities are new, warm and inviting, and were designed and constructed specifically for children Teacher reading to infant.

Our goal is to care for your child at each stage of their development. Our dedicated and caring staff nurture and prepare your infant and toddler for pre-school. The certified teachers in our accredited preschool program will prepare your child for kindergarten. Teacher reading to children in Kindergarten class.

Kiddie Kampus even has its own certified kindergarten so your child can continue developing in our caring, exciting and educational environment. For an in depth look at Kiddie Kampus and to hear what other parents are saying about us, order our FREE DVD “Come Join our Family!” on the FREE DVD page.

We also invite you to come visit Kiddie Kampus, tour our facilities, meet with our staff and see what we have to offer.  Because choosing a child care center will be one of your major life decisions.  And we are here to help you with that decision.  Come, Join Our Family!

name: Charles River YMCA Afterschool
details: Parents love YMCA After School, our family-centered program that nurtures the whole child by inspiring academic success, healthy movement and social and emotional development. Our staff of caring, trained educators are role models who lead activities that promote cooperation and character development. Parents can be productive at work knowing their children are in a safe and stimulating after school environment.

name: First Congregational Church of Holden Nursery School
details:
Our purpose is to provide a warm, nurturing, safe and loving environment where self concepts are enhanced, independence encouraged and individuality respected.

We believe the most effective learning takes place when a child is self- motivated. The teacher's role is to provide the children with choices in which they can explore the materials provided at their own rate and in their own style. The teacher is ready to guide, to be a resource and to provide fun, engaging activities that appeal to the children's interests.

name: Full Circle Farm Preschool Program
details:
Our idea of education is to provide children with those experiences and opportunities to journey on the path of wanting to know about themselves and the world around them, with a sense of respect and a positive self-esteem.

At Full Circle Farm Preschool, each child is seen for who he or she truly is; a unique and special individual. Children have the opportunity to explore and experiment at their own level of knowledge and interest. Within this framework, the curriculum allows each child to master new skills in the areas of social, emotional, cognitive and physical development. We believe that learning is best accomplished through play, observation and discovery.

Our classroom offers a variety of learning centers. These centers include a block corner, an art area, sensory tables, writing center, book corner, play dough table, manipulative area, painting easel, math and science areas and a dramatic play area. Outdoor play is an essential part of our daily curriculum.We have a wonderful playground the children enjoy throughout the school year.

name: Children Aboard Rainbow Express
details: Our goal as teachers is to be role models and to love these children with the love Christ has given us. We strive to recognize each of them as individuals, and provide opportunities that will enable them to learn about themselves, about others, and about their environment.  Through a variety of interactions and environments the children will develop at their own rate, physically, socially, emotionally, creatively and intellectually. We aim to encourage each child in his or her own personality and capability.

name: Bethel Nursery School
details:
Bethel Preschool is a non-profit Christian preschool established  in 1977 under the direction of Anna E. Westlund.  The school is a self-supporting ministry of Bethel Lutheran Church within its mission to serve families and children in our neighborhood and beyond.  We are a Christ centered, joy filled place where children grow and learn within a framework of love, care, and respect.  We provide a developmentally appropriate curriculum for both Nursery (age 3 approx.) and Pre-Kindergarten (age 4 approx.) classes, as well as small class sizes to ensure a favorable child/teacher ratio.

Bethel Preschool meets all the requirements and is licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care.  We are members of the National Association for the Education of Young Children and the Evangelical Lutheran Education Association.  We work closely with parents to provide the best preschool experience for each child.

 All school policies are set by the Board of Directors of the school following the DEEC guidelines.  The Board sets tuition rates, hires staff, and approves the school budget.

We start enrolling children at the age of 2 years and 9 months from Auburn and the surrounding towns.  We do not exclude any family because of race, creed, political beliefs, religion and cultural heritage, national origin, sexual orientation, marital status, or toilet training status.

Religion is not taught at Bethel Preschool, but Christian attitudes are upheld by the staff and Christian concepts are modeled through  our songs, our prayers at snack time, and our holiday celebrations.

The preschool rooms are located in Voosen Hall, on the west side of the church building.  The parking lot, school entrance, and coatroom are accessed from Homestead Avenue.  Our outside play area is adjacent to the parking lot.

name: Lee Youth Association- K thru 6 After School Program
Kid-Start Child Care Center
details: The KID-START Child Care program has been providing quality care for your children since 1986. Our services include a large network of home-based Providers serving the Greater Lawrence area as well as a brand new Child Care Center. In addition, we offer transportation to and from each site. Our office will help you find a solution that will satisfy your child care needs.

name: Kids on Track
details:
Thank you for considering KOT for your child's early childhood education.  We believe every child should be "on track" and see how much fun learning can be!   We look forward to getting to know you and your child.

Our program appreciates and addresses each child individually. Our mission is to build confidence and love of learning, giving our children a solid foundation for a healthy and happy life. 

Our longtime teachers and staff are dedicated to helping each child discover their unique potential – academically, socially, and interpersonally.

name: For Kids Only Afterschool Inc. @ Fort Banks
details: For Kids Only Afterschool (FKO) strives to support the needs of children and families through academic, recreational and social opportunities that enhance school day learning and build upon individual strengths and interests necessary for life long success. Our programs focus on the individual strengths and needs of each child in our care and aims to provide engaging and enriching activities for children in all areas of development: socio-emotional, cognitive, language and physical.

name: The Joyful Noise Preschool
details:
*Joyful Noise is a non-profit, non-denominational preschool
*Developmental age-appropriate program
*Multi-sensory environment
*29 years of experience

During the year a variety of educational units are planned to help expose the children to many new ideas and concepts.  The activities and materials are selected to maximize each child’s potential physical, cognitive, language and creative abilities.

The Guidelines for Preschool Learning Experiences (Massachusetts Curriculum Frameworks) demonstrate that we are providing experiences that build broad and balanced foundations for learning in all content areas.

It is our goal to create a loving atmosphere that will help each child to develop sensitivity to others, curiosity, responsibility, creativity, self-discipline and a genuine interest in and love of learning.
business hours:
Morning Session
9:00 am – 12:00 pm
Lunch Bunch Option:  12:00 pm – 1:00 pm

name: Gertrude E. Townsend Headstart
details: ABCD provides innovative, timely programs that promote upward mobility and a higher quality of life for people and communities. Empowering people by providing them with the tools to overcome poverty, live with dignity & achieve their full potential. ABCD responds to the needs of our community through our decentralized, city-wide network, which includes 14 unique neighborhood centers.

name: Crayon Campus - Howland
details: At Crayon Campus, Inc., our staff is committed to the belief that children can achieve a great deal. It is the role of the caregivers to build upon those skills that children have mastered. We believe that most of life’s learning – including how to learn – occurs in the first five years of life. Since each child learns at his/her own pace, our staff will allow your child to learn at their own rate while exposing them to a wide variety of opportunities. This will instill confidence and allow them to succeed socially and educationally.

name: CAAS Head Start Mystic
details: The program is designed to serve children 3-5 years of age from families who qualify for Head Start services in Somerville and Cambridge. CAAS Head Start helps all children succeed by providing comprehensive services to children through activities that help them grow: socially, emotionally, cognitively, and physically. These services lay the foundation for life long learning and continued school success. Children transition from our program into elementary schools prepared and ready to continue to learn and grow. Parents are encouraged to become partners with the program since CAAS Head Start recognizes you as your child’s first teacher. Working together will allow us to make your Head Start experience more valuable for both you and your child. We offer opportunities for you to become involved in classroom activities direct involvement in the decision making of program planning and operation. The CAAS Head Start program is operated by the Community Action Agency of Somerville, which also provides additional services in the Somerville community.

name: Childrens Own School
details: Children’s Own School is a private, non-profit, Montessori School located in Winchester, Massachusetts. It is the oldest Montessori Primary School in New England serving children ages two years five months to six. Our teachers embody the Montessori principles providing a beautiful environment where children learn essential skills for life-long creative thinking and learning.

name: ABC Fun Preschool
details:
Children are our most precious commodity. They are our future. As parents and teachers, it is our obligation to help them to learn and grow. At ABC fun we will provide the type of nurturing and relaxing atmosphere that will allow them to be confident in who they are and what they know.

Our curriculum is designed with age and skill level appropriate "learning through play" activities that will enrich them socially, physically, developmentally and intellectually. At the same time, they will be guided with readiness skills for school.

Our qualified staff understands these "learning through play" opportunities and will engage and encourage the learning experience in our activity centers.

You will be confident in knowing that your child will be learning throughout the day and have fun doing it.

name: Country Kids Preschool
details:
Country Kids first opened it's doors to young children and their families in 1991 when the birth of my niece inspired me to leave my job as a preschool teacher in Lincoln, MA. I wanted to create a program that would provide my niece with the kind of loving, engaging and creative learning environment that I longed for her to have. Our first school was small and humble, but our dedication to the families and the children that we served, was enormous. Our little school grew as did my family-all of my three children were born during this wonderful, busy, amazing time!

     In 2001 we moved to a new location in West Groton at the site of a historic mill, now called RiverCourt. Although we greatly enjoyed our time at RiverCourt and the wonderful neighbors and friends we made there, we were so excited to have the opportunity to move back to Main Street into our beautiful new school in January of 2014. My staff and I spent many months carefully planning the classrooms, playgrounds and a curriculum for our new location.            

     When you visit our school, you will see the love and attention that has been put into every detail. The most remarkable part of our program however, are the people who make up the school community. They are easily the most caring, intelligent, creative and fun group of women you ever want to meet. .

name: Church of the Nativity Community Nursery School
details: Our Preschool seeks to provide children with an environment that is fun and exciting, and at the same time challenging.  We offer a Christian atmosphere of caring and acceptance, and operate by values that are shared with the Church of the Nativity Way of Life, such as forgiveness, acceptance, confidence, empowerment, relationships, reflectiveness, curiosity, compassion, and contentment.  Our Preschool program is based on the develpmental approach to education.  The children participate in self-motivated learning ghrough active exploration and interaction with children, adults, and learning materials.  They will touch, fell, smeel, hear and see during the learning process.  The children in our school will be provided with a safe, nurturing, yet challenging environment that allows for their physical, social, emotional, and ocgnitive development.  Our staff are screened, trained, and well-supervised in order to ensure the well-being of every child.  Our program is designed around a wide variety of materials and activites which allow for individual needs and interests.

name: Kids Corner After School Program
details:
Kids' Corner After School Program is a parent sponsored non-profit organization licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care. We have been serving the Winchester, MA community since 1982. The program provides quality enrichment programs to school age children after school, on all school days from September through June. Kids' Corner After School Program is a place where children can learn, have fun and make new friends. We promote education enrichment and personal growth through a variety of activities.

Kids' Corner is located on the lower level of the old Mystic School at 263 Main Street. Transportation is provided for students; however, parents are responsible for purchasing their own bus passes through Winchester School Department.

name: GenCenter After School Day Care
details: Every child deserves access to a healthy, safe, productive and nurturing environment. We believe that day care services must be administered by qualified personnel who promote positive social behavior through developmentally appropriate and stimulating activities that meet the educational, social, emotional and recreational needs of our families.

details:
Kiddie Kampus is a family owned and operated Child Care Development Center that supports children and their families from infancy to teens.  Founded in 1989 by Marjorie & Ray Nunes, Kiddie Kampus is conveniently located in Dartmouth. Kiddie Kampus even has its own certified kindergarten so your child can continue developing in our caring, exciting and educational environment. We also invite you to come visit Kiddie Kampus, tour our facilities, meet with our staff and see what we have to offer.  Because choosing a child care center will be one of your major life decisions.  And we are here to help you with that decision.  Come, Join Our Family!

details: For Kids Only Afterschool (FKO) strives to support the needs of children and families through academic, recreational and social opportunities that enhance school day learning and build upon individual strengths and interests necessary for life long success. Our programs focus on the individual strengths and needs of each child in our care and aims to provide engaging and enriching activities for children in all areas of development: socio-emotional, cognitive, language and physical.

name: Brackett After School Program
details:
Brackett After School Program (BASP) serves children who are in the kindergarten through 5th grades at the Brackett Elementary School. The program runs September through June, Monday through Friday on school days from school dismissal until 6:00pm.

The program strives to offer a flexible, relaxed, and enjoyable environment.

Our program is child centered and designed with careful understanding of each child’s developmental needs.

name: Crayon College at Plymouth
details:
Crayon College has solutions for safe affordable childcare and early childhood education in a warm and nurturing environment.

We offer developmentally appropriate educational curriculum throughout the year for children from infancy though kindergarten. The warm, loving, and nurturing atmosphere creates a safe, optimum learning environment. And our low student-teacher ratio provides the individual attention that is essential in helping children thrive and grow.

name: Children's Corner, Inc.
details: Here at Children’s Corner we have preschool five mornings a week and offer lunch extended hours on Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday. You will find us to be a warm caring environment where we learn and play and discover new things every day. Children will learn the alphabet letters, colors, shapes, & numbers. They write their names every day progressing to last names when appropriate. We use many different art mediums and they create a project every day. Staff are First Aid & CPR certified as well as college educated. We are also both parents and have years of experience working with children.

name: Little Hands Big Hearts Lutheran Preschool
details:
Little Hands, Big Hearts Christian Preschool (LHBH) has been established by Lutheran Church of the Redeemer to provide a quality preschool experience for children in and around the community. Our Christian-based philosophy and curriculum are guided by an understanding of children’s individual difference and developmental needs. Our aim is to provide a safe and nurturing environment, guided by love to encourage physical, social, and emotional growth, as well as knowledge development of young children, all while responding to the needs of their families. Children are engaged within small classes through art, music, science, language, and social studies to realize their creative and imaginative abilities.

LHBH is a challenging and enjoyable program. We offer structure and creativity through play and teacher-guided activities. LHBH Preschool’s ultimate goal is to have each child feel a sense of accomplishment in self-help tasks and to be be comfortable in group situations, while looking forward to the kindergarten experience ahead.

Little Hands, Big Hearts Preschool is located minutes from Rt. 128 and I-93 in Woburn. We are housed in the Education Wing of the Lutheran Church of the Redeemer, 60 Forest Park Road, Woburn, MA 01801. Our telephone number is 781-937-5645.

We are proud to say that Little Hands Big Hearts Christian Preschool was recently voted in Spring 2014 #1 Preschool in Woburn with Readers Choice Awards, and also voted Silver in Readers Choice Awards out of 8 surrounding communities!

name: The Andover Country Day School
details:
The Mission of Andover Country Day School
To awaken and expand each and every child's sense of discovery-to fulfill the joys of understanding their environment, to take them as high as they can comfortably soar, and to have a happy, fun and safe experience at school.

name: Action Adventure After School at Muddy Brook
Kids Corner at the Pines
details:
In 1987, Kids’ Corner at the Pines opened, which is licensed for 44 children between the ages of 1 month to 7 years both for the community and our staff: this promotes the attraction, retention, and longevity of some of the top professionals in the industry. Our program allows our staff to return to work earlier because they are able to look in on their infants during the work day. We have fewer callouts because Kids Corner does not close for snow days and is only closed for 6 holidays, the day after Thanksgiving, and Christmas Eve. Knowing that you can have consistent staff (Early Education Teachers and aides) caring for your child through a Licensed Program Certified through the Office of Children is a tremendous benefit. Having it subsidized by SPEC has given us the ability to be selective in who we hire to care for your child. We have a great many nursing candidates interested in working in our child daycare program as well as our other departments.

The children in Kids Corner join in with activities with the residents such as crafts, music, fashion shows, Trick or Treating, etc.

On occasion some of our residents and their families visit the children.  The exposure to the infants and toddlers as well as the pre-schoolers creates a non-threatening relationship and many of our lower functioning residents become very responsive and start engaging the little ones in conversation, stirring old memories of their prior lives. The families are able to see the parent they remembered as a child who is now responding to the toddler.  We see role reversals where the children become the caregivers who watch out for the memory impaired residents and help them wherever they can.

name: Crayon Campus - Cove
details: At Crayon Campus, Inc., our staff is committed to the belief that children can achieve a great deal. It is the role of the caregivers to build upon those skills that children have mastered. We believe that most of life’s learning – including how to learn – occurs in the first five years of life. Since each child learns at his/her own pace, our staff will allow your child to learn at their own rate while exposing them to a wide variety of opportunities. This will instill confidence and allow them to succeed socially and educationally.

name: Chicopee Child Development Center, Inc.
details:
We are permanently located in our own building near Westover Air Reserve Base. We are easily accessible from Memorial Drive (Rt. 33), the MA turnpike, and from main roads leading from Holyoke, South Hadley, and surrounding communities. 

Our center is open year-round, Monday through Friday, with the exception of the major holidays. Our hours are 7:00 am to 5:30 pm.

Children may be enrolled who have reached the age of 2 years and 9 months to 7 years old. Families must visit CCDC for a tour and to complete all necessary paperwork for admission. Tours may be schedules by contacting the Business Administrator or Director at 413-593-3942. 

Our staff follows the Creative Curriculum for Preschool and is motivated by the philosophy that each child is an individual with their own unique needs, concerns, and interests. We believe our center is a place of learning on both formal and informal levels where each child is able to reach their full potential. We nurture the social, emotional, physical, language, and cognitive growth and development of all children. The children participate in a safe and stimulating environment, designed to foster opportunities to foster independence, exploration, and creativity. 

We are proud to be a NAEYC accredited center serving the needs of children and families for over 45 years! We would love the opportunity to serve you!

name: Holyoke YMCA After School Program - Plains
The Learning Experience
details: The Learning Experience enhances the lives of children ages 6 weeks to 5 years. In each contemporary, colorful building children learn in a fun fashion starting with sign language for infants through preschool, technology, early literacy, math, sciences, music, theater, creative arts, dance, physical fitness, nutrition, etiquette and much more. Graduates of TLE are more than prepared to enter Kindergarten and first grade. All the curriculum is proprietary and has been designed, written and published especially for TLE children. At The Learning Experience early learning is an art. We believe that knowledge is like the sky, never ending. Parents dream of the best for their children and at TLE their dreams become reality making those important first years creative, productive, happy and most importantly filled with lots of love.

name: Busy Bee Preschool #2
details: At Busy Bee Pre-School, our true desire is to educate all children in all ways. We believe our classrooms provide a combination of both old and new views and are full of creative and motivating ideas. Our classrooms are environments that your child will remember for a lifetime.  We provide a daily curriculum that encourages children to express themselves through creative dramatic play, while at the same time providing academic skills through hands-on experiences that are developmentally appropriate.

name: CAAS Head Start- Frisoli Center
details: The program is designed to serve children 3-5 years of age from families who qualify for Head Start services in Somerville and Cambridge. CAAS Head Start helps all children succeed by providing comprehensive services to children through activities that help them grow: socially, emotionally, cognitively, and physically. These services lay the foundation for life long learning and continued school success. Children transition from our program into elementary schools prepared and ready to continue to learn and grow. Parents are encouraged to become partners with the program since CAAS Head Start recognizes you as your child’s first teacher. Working together will allow us to make your Head Start experience more valuable for both you and your child. We offer opportunities for you to become involved in classroom activities direct involvement in the decision making of program planning and operation. The CAAS Head Start program is operated by the Community Action Agency of Somerville, which also provides additional services in the Somerville community.

name: Children's Playhouse Daycare, Inc.
details:
Welcome to Children's Playhouse Daycare. I hope that your child's years with us are fun, nurturing and happy. The staff and I are anxiously awaiting your child's arrival. We are committed to providing a rich and caring environment where children can feel confident about themselves and their ability to succeed. We want you to know that your child's daycare is your daycare and we expect you to stop by, talk with the staff, ask questions, and share your ideas and talents with us.

Your child's day will be filled with many varied and exciting activities. Our teachers carefully prepare the classroom environment with many interests to stimulate self-motivated learning. Children are encouraged to grow and progress at their own pace by choosing from a variety of interesting and fun activities. At our daycare you will see happy faces, full of wonder, ideas, and things to talk about, relate to, compare, match, fit into, try out, reinvent, discover, and enjoy.

The program we pursue is geared toward helping children develop habits of observation, questioning, and listening. It gives them awareness of their own feelings, and their right to express those feelings by sometimes channeling in to other means of expression. They learn they are free to make choices. A program like ours gives your child the necessary guidance and nurturing he/she needs to become self confident, independent, and most of all happy!

Fully licensed by The Department Of Early Education And Care Of Massachusetts. Proudly providing exceptional and quality services to our families of Everett and the surrounding communities since 1993.

name: The Barn Coop Nursery School
details:
In the summer of 1969 Barbara Buchan (then a graduate student at the Eliot-Pearson Department of Child Study, Tufts University) and Sally Mlavsky decided to start a nursery school for their daughters. The school would be based on the idea that a child should be actively involved in making decisions about his or her day’s activities rather than passively responding to the teacher’s notions about what he or she would be interested in. This idea appealed to many other parents, and with a great deal of work The Barn Nursery School opened on Winter Street in Lincoln.

The first year program consisted of one class of fifteen children and one teacher, Noreen Nolan. At the end of the first year the school settled into more permanent quarters at the Concord Scout House, which, incidentally, contains the beams of an old barn in the large first-floor room.

We continue to adapt the space in the school to our educational philosophy.  In the fall of 1970, Dr. Anita Olds, a faculty member of the Eliot-Pearson Child Study Department, was invited to visit our school. She helped us design an environment that encourages maximum involvement of the children and offers opportunities for self-initiated creative play. Then, a major renovation to the entire inside space (play area, office, and bathroom) took place during the summer of 1988. The construction added a functional kitchen area, increased bathroom facilities, staff office, and a significant upgrade in appearance and space utilization. More recently, we have modified our playground environment (introducing new structures, changing existing ones, and creating new areas) to better meet the needs of our school and our physical and educational goals for that space.

The existing school is a reminder of the enormous commitment of the parents and staff to creating an exciting environment in which the child is free to follow his or her curiosity. The Barn continues to explore new possibilities and incorporate new talents and ideas into the flexible structure that is a cooperative.

name: Giggle Garden's, Inc.
details: Giggle Gardens, Inc., offers day care educational programs for children at two locations in Springfield, Mass. We take pride in our commitment to quality care and the education of young children. We are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children and work closely with the Department of Early Education and Care as well as other cooperative organizations to constantly improve the quality of our programs.

name: Garden Gate Child Development Ctr
details:
At Garden Gate, children are seen as creative, competent and capable. Our teachers look at each individual child in a holistic way, respecting and nurturing each child's potential for physical, emotional, social, cognitive, creative and spiritual growth.

We believe children strive to form deep, meaningful relationships with family, school and community. At Garden Gate children learn about the reciprocity of relationships, the give-and-take of helping and being helped, of giving as well as getting, and mutual care and respect for one another. Children participate, with teachers' help, in caring for our classroom and classroom pets, negotiating play, solving conflicts with one another and helping to create social rules and boundaries as needed in the group.

We believe that taking personal responsibility for one's actions, in the classroom, on the playground and in the world, leads to empowerment, self-satisfaction, empathy and a generous spirit. Our children are responsible for their own feelings and actions and we support them with words and strategies for dealing with frustration, disappointment, anger and sadness. We help them to share their wonder, joy, and delight with others.

We believe that children are inquisitive, resourceful and motivated to learn about the world around them. At Garden Gate the learning process is dynamic, involving the teachers, parents, and the children in hands-on learning. Our teachers encourage children to explore, take risks, succeed, fail and persevere. Our children are responsible, with teachers' help, for generating inquiries, brainstorming ideas, experimenting with a wide variety of materials, and communicating their knowledge and understanding.

name: ABCD Walnut Grove Head Start
details: ABCD provides innovative, timely programs that promote upward mobility and a higher quality of life for people and communities. Empowering people by providing them with the tools to overcome poverty, live with dignity & achieve their full potential. ABCD responds to the needs of our community through our decentralized, city-wide network, which includes 14 unique neighborhood centers.

name: Active Learners, Inc
details: Active Learners recognizes the importance of early childhood education, and employs various programs to assist cognitive and social development for children within Norton, Massachusetts, and the surrounding communities. Unlike other private preschools, our facility focuses on the independent learning experience of each child.

name: Boyd Center For Child Care And Development-Rodman
details: Give your son or daughter a solid foundation for learning with the early childhood program at John E. Boyd Center for Child Care and Development in Fall River, Massachusetts. Tapping into your child's natural curiosity, we motivate him/her to always reach for the next level of education.

name: The Barn School
details: We envision a diverse, committed and unified community of parents, children and teachers who work together to encourage, enrich and inspire each other. Our mission  to create a safe, nurturing and respectful environment for children, families and teachers, where childhood is celebrated.

name: Camp Fire USA @ Connery
details: Camp Fire's After School Program provides opportunities for youth to realize their potential by participating in various activities while making new friends under the supervision of qualified, caring adults. Our after school program runs Monday thru Friday from 1:45 - 6:00pm and operates on the Lynn Public School calendar. It includes age appropriate activities such as Homework Club, Arts & Crafts, Sports, Games & Outdoor Play. Camp Fire North Shore also offers a nutritious snack daily!

name: C.E.O.C. Child Care Program
details:
CEOC was established in April 1965 as Cambridge’s designated community action anti-poverty agency, and it has never strayed from its mission to challenge poverty’s causes and impacts. CEOC is working harder than ever to provide individual and family support, advocacy and organizing to empower  CEOC participants and community members to have their voices heard by policy makers in setting public policy that directly impacts them.

At CEOC, we realize that our programs and public policy advocacy are critical because of the economic challenges that confront low and limited income individuals and families.  Those with limited and low incomes continue to experience the burden of not being able to make ends meet.  Many individuals and families are working hard and playing by the rules but are still not able to make ends meet.  CEOC works with participants to build their economic stability to maximize their ability to move out of poverty.  CEOC also advocates for public policies that support individuals and families attempts to move out of poverty.

name: Happy Day School
details: At Happy Day School we believe in encouraging children to grow into confident, positive individuals. The program will aid children in their socialization skills and provide opportunities for decision making. Positive experiences in a warm and accepting environment will help children with both self confidence and self expression. Teachers will give strong consideration to each child’s individual needs. Group activities will be provided to further develop social relationships.

name: Animal Crackers Nursery School
details: Animal Crackers Nursery School was established in 1978. We are committed to providing high quality programming to our families. Our school house is designed with your child in mind ensuring safety, cleanliness, and a warm, cozy environment. We offer a developmental program allowing your child to learn and grow at his or her own pace. Our curriculum goals are aligned with the Massachusetts Guidelines for Preschool, the Kindergarten Frameworks and The Creative Curriculum. Children are assessed on an ongoing basis with Parent Teacher Conferences held at least twice each year. Individual portfolios of children's work as well as personal checklists are kept as part of our assessment system. Our team of professionals strive to provide the best preschool care and education to each child entrusted to us combined with an unsurpassed environment of caring.
business hours:
Morning Sessions: 8:30 -11:15 am

Afternoon Sessions: 12:15 -3:00 pm

name: Clarke School East
details:
Clarke provides children who are deaf or hard of hearing with the listening, learning and spoken language skills they need to succeed. Annually, more than 1,000 children and their families benefit from programs and services at our five locations: Boston, Jacksonville, New York City, Northampton and Philadelphia.

Clarke impacts the lives of children and adults through educational and early childhood programs, hearing services, mainstream services, research, curriculum development and the teachers and professionals trained by Clarke who take their special skills to all parts of the world.

Formerly Clarke School for the Deaf / Center for Oral Education, in 2010, we changed our name to Clarke Schools for Hearing and Speech. This change reflects our distinct mission of teaching children who are deaf and hard of hearing how to listen and talk using the latest technology; and it also highlights our multiple locations—which continue to grow! Our new logo is a vibrant mark celebrating the growth and success of Clarke children. Each day, we watch and listen as they blossom—gaining confidence and acquiring the ability to reach their full potential.

As Clarke reaches more children than ever before, our mission remains unchanged: Providing children who are deaf and hard of hearing with the listening, learning and spoken language skills they need to succeed. Today, the possibilities for children who are deaf and hard of hearing are greater than ever before. We work with families and professionals to ensure that every child has the chance to reach their full potential.

name: Kinderbook Inc.
details:
Kinderbook is a program designed to provide children with a warm caring environment to make everyday happy and productive for your child.  We encourage parent participation for the continuous education and growth of your child.  Our program fosters physical, social and academic development in an emotionally supportive environment.  Our goal is for children to develop a positive self-image and to be provided with a pleasant and happy learning experience.  We have a wide variety of appropriate work and play centers, which will provide a stimulating environment while your child is at Kinderbook.

Each month a new calendar is provided with the weekly themes and projects.  Our curriculum is designed to challenge your child’s growth socially, physically, academically and emotionally.  We intend to encourage positive attitudes towards your child’s learning experience.  Children are introduced to a variety of appropriate decisions and choices throughout the school day.  Finger plays, action songs, and musicals games provide many exploratory and rhythmic expressions.

name: Little Blessings Preschool
details:
A State-licensed facility for three and four year old pre-school classes as well as an accredited kindergarten class, Little Blessings is a ministry of the Evangelical Covenant Church of Attleboro, MA.

We provide our students with opportunities for growth in a wide range of areas: social, emotional, cognitive, creative, physical and spiritual.  We strive to develop a positive self-image in each child.  Spiritual emphasis is placed on sharing and caring for one another and on recognizing the God- given qualities in each of us.

In the early childhood years, we believe much learning takes place through play, exploration and discovery.  Through developmentally appropriate experiences in all areas, we seek to instill in our students a positive attitude toward themselves, each other, school and learning, thus contributing to their future success.

name: Little Learners Preschool LTD
details:
Little Learners Preschool has provided a positive learning experience for children since 2003. We have a caring and nurturing staff that are all certified through the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care and are also CPR and First Aid certified. Our school nurse is very active in our school and teaches quality programs to the children throughout the school year. 

Children learn at their own pace and should be treated as individuals. We believe a safe and nurturing environment will provide endless opportunities for children to learn and grow. They should be encouraged to explore, make choices, learn and apply new skills and make new friends.  Children are eager to learn and teachers will guide them in any way they can.

The goal at Little Learners Preschool is to provide a positive learning experience for every child, which will help them to develop a positive self-concept and self- esteem. We want to teach the children to respect diversity and individual differences while they learn about the world they live in. We want to support the child's family, in hopes that together we will contribute to the child's health, growth and development in a way that is positive and most beneficial.

name: The Children's House
details:
At our school, children are given the precious gift of time: time to know themselves, time to nurture friendships, time to learn, explore and reach out to the world around them. Montessori education is a dynamic philosophy with over a hundred years of experience in “helping children help themselves.”

We invite you to come and experience our school for yourself. Take a tour of our campus. Observe in our toddler, preschool and elementary classes and picture your child in our classrooms. We would love the opportunity to show you our community with the hope that you will consider making it yours.

name: French For Kids
details: At French for Kids! we honor and respect children as individuals with unique personalities, temperaments, talents, interests and learning styles. We encourage children to explore their world in a joyful, playful, loving, and unhurried learning environment. We are passionate about also giving children the gift of learning a second or third language at the time when their brains are primed for this. We derive tremendous satisfaction from supporting a diverse community of children and their families who value interactive learning and recognize the cultural, social, and cognitive benefits of bilingualism.

name: Acton Cooperative School, Inc.
details:
Welcome to the Acton Cooperative School -- a preschool for children 2 years, 9 months through pre-kindergarten conveniently located in West Acton, Massachusetts. We are licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, and our activities are overseen by the Department of Early Education and Care (EEC).

Acton Cooperative School staff and parents have been “working together to make learning fun” since 1957. We focus on learning through play, with teachers directing play in ways that allow children to develop important skills.

We take great pride in our highly trained teachers and very low staff turnover. All of our teachers are certified in Early Childhood Education, have completed first aid and CPR courses, and are parents themselves. In addition, all of our teachers have been with us for many years, most for more than 10 years.

Our school is governed by the Director and an elected Parent Board, and run by parents. As a parent-run school, each parent spends time in the classroom and plays a role, large or small, in managing the school.

This parent involvement means that costs stay low, the school becomes a tight-knit and supportive community, and parents play a unique, hands-on role in their child’s first school experience. It also means happy parents and kids! Children excitedly anticipate their parent's day at school, and parents enjoy watching their child learn and interact with friends.

name: Academy of Early Learning, Inc.
details: The Academy of Early Learning is dedicated to recognizing and appreciating the individuality of each child while providing instruction by teachers outstanding in their ability to teach. We believe in assisting each child to gently 'stretch' to fulfill his or her potential - academically, emotionally, socially and physically - by presenting as many different opportunities as possible in an intellectually stimulating, supportive and value-based environment. At The Academy of Early Learning all children can succeed and feel a sense of accomplishment.

name: Days of Discovery Child Care Center
Cloverdale Cooperative Nursery School
details: Cloverdale, a half-day parent cooperative preschool, with an option for extended days, has been in existence since 1954. Its philosophy has remained unchanged throughout the years. In the true sense of the word cooperative, teachers and parents work closely together to provide children a meaningful blend of experiences to peak their innate curiosity, therefore imparting a lifetime love of learning. Cloverdale Prechool is dedicated to providing a nurturing environment, rich in enjoyable, sensory-based experiences that promote confidence through exploration, questioning, reasoning, predicting, and creating. Children are actively supported as they negotiate and celebrate their similarities and differences within a curriculum designed to emphasize social responsibility within their world.

name: Children's House
details:
The cornerstone of our program is providing opportunities for healthy ego development in the young child. At Children's House, the daily routine caters to a young child’s need to feel important and be successful.

Children are invited to participate in activities, as they are ready and confident to do so. Social interaction and verbal communication are stressed. Children’s efforts are consistently acknowledged and complimented. Children are encouraged to make choices regarding activities, which most interest them. This option provides practice at decision-making, promotes independence and allows children to feel some control over their day. This framework reinforces children’s ability to be successful, thus rewarding them with a positive sense of self-worth.

Children's House seeks to support parents and offer guidance in their child-rearing efforts. We are always happy to offer resource and referral to the families we care for. We are available for conversation, comfort, and professional expertise as needed.

Children's House does not discriminate in providing service(s) to children and their families on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, gender, age, veteran status, gender identity, cultural heritage, political beliefs, national origin, disability, sexual orientation, marital status, or any other legally

name: Knotty Pine Nursery School, Inc
details:
Knotty Pine Nursery School is a family owned business that first opened its doors in 1949.  It has been providing preschool education continually for over 60 years.  It is conveniently located just off  Route 152 in a residential neighborhood of North Seekonk. Its location makes it readily accessible to many of the neighboring communities, including, Seekonk, Attleboro, Rehoboth, East Providence and Pawtucket. The staff of Knotty Pine dedicate themselves to helping children effectively transition from home to a more structured learning environment while maintaining the feeling and look of a more homelike atmosphere.

We are a Massachusetts licensed facility accepting children 2 years 9 months through Kindergarten.

name: Easton Learning Adventures Preschool
details:
Our preschool is founded on the philosophy that children, their families and society as a whole benefit from high quality early childhood programs. We believe that what your children learn through their early experiences will carry on to later successes in life. We also know your children need time to be kids and experience their childhoods. When your child is in our care, he/she will have the opportunity to explore and create as they interact with their environment, their teachers and their peers.

Our ultimate goal is to provide a program which fosters a warm, nurturing, enriching, and developmentally appropriate environment that meets the individual needs of your child. Our dedicated teachers are committed to building strong relationships with both children and their families while giving back to the community.

name: The Kids' League
details: For over 16 years, The Kids’ League of Westford has served the children and families of Westford and beyond by providing a high quality After-School Program and Summer Program at affordable rates. Our greatest asset is our dedicated, qualified, and caring staff that enjoys investing in the lives of each child. We recognize the individual needs and interests of each child and have designed our program to challenge, nurture, and care for each child who passes through our doors. Our program includes homework time, enrichment clubs, indoor and outdoor play time, arts & crafts, and more.

name: The Campbell School
details:
The Campbell School was established in the year 2002.  Its mission is to provide a developmentally appropriate preschool and kindergarten program in an atmosphere of security, warmth, acceptance and encouragement.  The Campbell School is dedicated to maintaining a learning environment designed to enrich all students by meeting their unique educational and developmental needs.

The school is fully licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts through the Department of Early Education and Care.  Located on the corner of Blue Hill Avenue and Decker Street, the school has a daily capacity of seventy-eight children.  The children range in age from 2.9 years through 6 years old.

The Campbell School provides a prepared learning environment where each child is free to act and develop along the lines of his or her own inner direction.  Teachers guide and encourage the preschool child to develop skills, which lead toward communication and self-confidence.

A child’s imagination grows individually, and at its own pace, while also functioning as part of a group.  Therefore, various modes of creative expression through art, drama and music are an integral part of each school day.  Science experiences, which help the child to understand the world around him or her, are regularly presented.  Opportunities for children to grow socially, emotionally and intellectually are a regular, integrated part of each and every day.

The role of the teacher is to understand each child as fully as possible.  An effective and beneficial function of the teacher is primarily that of observer.  While observing, the teacher is always ready to guide and direct the child’s efforts to teach himself.  In this way, the young child learns according to his or her own individual needs and capabilities.

Overall, our curriculum is designed to develop the child’s readiness skills.  We wish to provide continuity and stability, which is essential for children at this age.  Our role is to recognize each child’s individual gifts, and to nurture, love, and support in a congenial environment.

In addition, we strive to maintain a sound parent and teacher relationship of mutual respect and trust.  Scheduled conferences may be requested at any time to discuss a child’s school experience and progress.  Also, since parents drop off and pick up their children from the classrooms, they are encouraged to interact with teachers daily.

The Campbell School came to be through a unique and wonderful collaboration of dedicated, caring, committed individuals who believe in the value of a developmentally sound educational program that embraces tolerance, acceptance, love, humor, kindness and diversity.  The children, parents, teachers and administration of the Campbell School are family.  As family, we strive daily to fulfill the promise each child brings to us and to the world.

name: The Learning Center for The Deaf
details: Our mission is to ensure that deaf and hard-of-hearing students achieve their full potential in an educational environment where language and communication are keys to building competence, character and community.

name: Kiddie Kollege
details:
Kiddie Kollege was founded in 1973 and offers a professionally designed, thematic curriculum; complete with lesson plans, assessments, progress reports, portfolios and newsletters for parents to use as a guide.

Children learn through hands on play and structured activities in our well organized learning centers. These are the places within our classroom where the children can find the toys and materials related by theme, interest, and skills. These activities and toys can be used independently by the children, or with teacher direction, to reinforce and enrich skills and concepts they need. Learning environments are an excellent way to individualize the curriculum to meet the varying needs of young children.
business hours:
7:30 AM to 5:30 PM
Monday through Friday

name: The Gorse Children's Center
details:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: Creative Minds II
details:
We currently have four learning centers; three in Dracut and one in Tyngsboro. 
Our original program is located at 1385 Lakeview Ave. Dracut and provides care for infants, toddlers, and preschoolers.  Our largest program is located at 1827 Bridge St. Dracut (Greenmont Ave School District) and provides care for infants, toddlers, preschoolers and school age children. Our Tyngsboro location is located at 164 Westford Rd. and offers full and half day preschool and after-school programs. Our newest location is located at 469 Nashua Rd. in Dracut (Brookside School District) and offers full and half day care for children aged preschool through school age.
 
At all of our programs, we use a child driven, play based curriculum. 
We offer many choices and opportunities for exploration.  Our goal is to provide each child a safe and stimulating environment in which to grow and learn. 

So whether you are looking for childcare, preschool programs, or before and after school care, we are here to help.  Please contact us for more information.

name: Burlington Day Care Center
details:
We have six bright and spacious classrooms that include equipment and toys that allow children to develop at their own pace. Our center also includes a well-equipped outside playground.

Our very caring and professional staff is dedicated to the growth and development of young children. The staff members attend classes and seminars regularly as part of their training. This, combined with a common belief that working for a non-profit means we put children first, has formed us into a close family of dedicated teachers.
business hours: Monday through Friday, 7 am to 6 pm

name: Hockomock Area YMCA School's Out - Wrentham
details: Play, learn, and grow in our School’s Out program which offers a before-and-after-school experience with healthy, constructive enrichment activities. A nutritious snack is offered daily. We follow the eight core contents of the YMCA’s School-Age Curriculum, which incorporates literacy, science, technology, health, wellness and fitness, arts and humanities, homework support, service learning, character development, and social competence and conflict resolution.

name: Little Trails Learning Center
details:
Little Trails Learning Center provides exceptional care to children in Mansfield and the surrounding communities. We are open from 7:00 am to 6:00pm Monday through Friday. We offer care Monday through Friday in our infant, toddler, preschool, pre-k and kindergarten programs. In addition we offer before school care and wrap-around care for public kindergarten students. Students may be picked up and dropped off by the public school buses. Whether you need full time care or just a few days we can design a program to meet your needs.

We offer a distinctive program that meets all of your child’s developmental needs from age six weeks through kindergarten age. We have a state of the art facility, which includes a fenced in outdoor playground adjacent to the facility, security cameras and front door access cards. Our entire staff is fully licensed and certified by the Department of Early Education and Care. They are dedicated and committed to preparing your child for a lifetime of learning in a safe and nurturing environment.

name: Magic Years Nursery School
details:
At Magic Years Cooperative Nursery School, our goal is to provide a rich introduction to your child’s learning experience.

Our school offers a collaborative approach that fosters a fun, personalized and community oriented learning environment. The cooperative arrangement also gives you the unique opportunity to participate in your child’s school experience.

Our two-year program offers a “learning through play” approach that prepares children for kindergarten by making school a fun and friendly place to learn. Focusing on planned themes throughout the year, children explore their world in age-appropriate ways through art, music, movement, science experiments, field trips, guest speakers and community service. Our small enrollment of 24 ensures a dynamic, fun, close-knit community for the children.

As a cooperative nursery school parent involvement is pivotal to the success of the school. Parents assume a special role, participating as classroom aids ("Parent Helpers"). They also adopt a "Parent Job" and attend monthly business meetings of the school.

Magic Years is located on Chapel Lane in downtown Manchester-by-the-Sea, Massachusetts.

The after school period represents a major portion of a child’s free time.  MAP is designed to provide a less structured environment than the regular school day, while introducing various enriching themes and activities to enhance children’s interest, talents, and values.  The program fosters each child’s need for socialization, play, learning, and relaxation, in a supportive atmosphere.

 MAP is an equal opportunity employer.  The teachers at MAP are qualified professionals with a variety of backgrounds and experiences.  While teacher certification is not required, teacher‘s degrees may include Elementary or Early Childhood Education, School Age Care, Physical Education, English, Psychology, Drama, Music, etc
