details: Bright Beginnings welcomes families of all faiths, creeds and ethnic origins to its program. Bright Beginnings intends to give each child an educational experience, which is appropriate to his/her development. Our curriculum is bias-free and focuses on the individual child's social,emotional and intellectual needs. It will also provide challenging and rewarding experiences for the development of each child's creative abilities. Our professional staff encourages exploration and growth in a well-equipped environment that is stimulating, safe, consistent and nurturing. We are committed to working closely with parents toward the welfare of the whole family. Parents are welcome to visit Bright Beginnings at any time. Both prior to enrolling their child and during the child's time at school.

name: Montessori Academy of Cape Cod
details: The Montessori Academy of Cape Cod was founded in 1993 as a nonprofit school recognized at the state and federal levels. The Academy does not discriminate and welcomes children, families, and staff from all racial, national, ethnic, religions, political belief, sexual orientation, disability, marital and economic backgrounds to participate in all Academy programs. At the Academy, children work at their own pace in a non-competitive atmosphere and are free to engage in independent "spontaneous activity" and to experience success. The child perfects himself through his own powers, and moves forward guided by that inner force which distinguishes him or her as an individual. The Academy is one of only sixteen schools in Massachusetts to have been honored with affiliation status from the American Montessori Society. The administration and staff are dedicated to their work with children and uphold the high ethical standards set by our national organization. The National Association for the Education of Young Children has also recognized the quality of our program. As a NAEYC accredited early childhood program, the Academy is rated amongst the top programs in the country.

name: Northeast Montessori School
details:
A Montessori education places an emphasis on the development of a child by encouraging their independent learning.

Maria Montessori believed that a child actively participates in the learning experience, as such; the classroom is designed to enhance a child’s cognitive and social development. Instruction is organized but also adapts to each students needs and style. Children are allowed to learn at their pace and encouraged to collaborate and help other children in the classroom.

Montessori Education is named after Maria Montessori. Born in the town of Chiaravalle, in the province of Ancona, Italy, in 1870, she became the first female physician in Italy upon her graduation from medical school in 1896. In her medical practice, her clinical observations led her to analyze how children learn, and she concluded that they build themselves from what they find in their environment.  She founded the first Casa dei Bambini, or "Children's House” which became the basis for the Montessori method of education and integrated Montessori's scientific observations of children's almost effortless ability to absorb knowledge from their surroundings, as well as their tireless interest in manipulating materials. Every piece of equipment, every exercise, every method Montessori developed was based on what she observed children to do "naturally," by themselves, unassisted by adults. Children teach themselves. This simple but profound truth inspired Montessori's lifelong pursuit of educational reform, methodology, psychology, teaching, and teacher training--all based on her dedication to furthering the self-creating process of the child. Today, Maria Montessori’s work lives on through the Association Montessori Internationale (AMI).
If you are interested in learning more about the Northeast Montessori School, we would be delighted to hear from you.

Conveniently located at Boston's Copley Square crossroads, it is easily accessible to families who live as near as the surrounding neighborhoods and as far as the suburbs of Greater Boston. name: Pond Lot PreSchool, Inc.
details:
Pond Lot PreSchool, Inc. was established in 2006. Our vision is to offer a positive preschool experience for children that will foster a love for learning in the years ahead. We do this by making the preschool learning years fun, exciting, exploratory and full of laughter. We will provide the children with many opportunities to promote their self-esteem, social skills, cognitive thinking, and gross & fine motor skills. The children will do the rest with their amazing natural curiosity and enthusiasm.

Our vision also includes our parents, grandparents, and all the friends and relatives that are so important in the children’s lives. The fundamental areas of natural concern, such as safety, warmth, kindness, understanding teachers and beautiful surroundings are all part of the decision making process when choosing a preschool. We provide these essentials for every child within a balanced and developmentally appropriate program. Our primary focus is to provide a safe and nurturing environment for all the children. When you leave your child at Pond Lot PreSchool, you know that your child is getting the very best in care, safety, teaching and love. details: At Pre-School Playmates, our goal for all of our children is that when they leave our program to enter into public school, they will be strong emotionally, socially, and academically. We will work very hard to make sure your child has developed great self-esteem while being in our program. The emphasis in our program is learning through Art and Music. We will put on several shows during the year where the children will sing and dance and learn many new songs and poems. We will also do an amazing Art show where the children will be exposed to several well known artists such as Monet and Van Gogh. We will never discriminate against any child or family based on their religion, race, cultural heritage, political beliefs, national origin, marital status, sexual orientation, or disability. We believe every child deserves an amazing early childhood experience and we will work every day to be sure they get one at Pre-School Playmates.

Holyoke • Chicopee • Springfield Head Start, Inc. is committed to providing low-income children and their families with a Beacon of Hope and source of support for a brighter future. We strive to do so by providing high quality comprehensive child development services to enrolled children and empowering families to achieve stability in their home environment.

Our CORE VALUES
Excellence • Respect • Diversity • Communication Team Work • Flexibility • Dedication • Shared Vision

Our HISTORY
Since 1965 HCS Head Start Inc. has been providing high-quality early childhood education services for children and families in cities and towns located in Western Massachusetts, including Holyoke, Chicopee, Springfield, Ludlow, Palmer, and Granby. Head Start provides a solid foundation for children to gain necessary skills to enter kindergarten and to be successful in life. Our centers are fully licensed by the MA Department of Early Education and Care. For a complete list of the cities and towns we serve, contact us at (413)788-6522.

name: Sunshine Academy Early Education Center
details: We believe that children do their most important learning before the age of five. They learn best through child-centered and child-directed activities, and through the exploration of materials and themes. Teachers act as facilitators, providing materials, guidance and support for each child to learn at his or her own pace. We recognize that every aspect of the program affects all of the children enrolled. The physical environment, staff, activities and services all contribute to your child’s experience. The program maintains a maximum quality level that promotes your child’s health, growth and development; encourages services that strengthen family life; and supports families in the essential task of nurturing your child’s development.

name: Temple Beth Elohim Nursery School
details:
Temple Beth Elohim is a community deeply committed to spiritual searching, the study of ethics and morality, the pursuit of justice, and deeds of loving kindness.  TBE is a community with a diverse population of over 1,100 families from more than 37 communities throughout Greater Boston.  

We provide a multitude of opportunities for involvement including: social justice activities, formal and informal education programs, participatory and joyful worship, nursery school and toddler programs, religious school for grades K through 12 and extensive opportunities for adult learning. For more information about any of our programs or services please ask our Clergy, Educators or Administrative staff. 

Temple Beth Elohim is affiliated with the Union of Reform Judaism.

name: Temple Beth Shalom Children's Center
details:
Temple Beth Shalom Children’s Center (TBSCC) offers a nurturing, vibrant, developmentally appropriate, discovery-based environment, which allows children to develop to their maximum potential.  The program focuses on encouraging children’s social, emotional, cognitive and physical growth and development, along with developing in children a love and understanding of what it means to be Jewish. 

Children’s natural creativity and curiosity are facilitated and encouraged, as they become engaged in a variety of activities to promote their individual strengths and meet new challenges. This is accomplished through a variety of large and small group activities, as well as individual activities.  At TBSCC, our goal is to develop a community of curious, active learners with high self-competence, confidence and respect for others. 

We believe in the uniqueness of each child and because a child is part of a family, we feel that the family deserves our attention as well.  We partner with families to support each child’s growth and development.

name: Terri's Little Pumpkins
details:
We’d like to welcome you and your family into our circle of families. At Terri’s Little Pumpkins, we strive to offer the very best high quality child care possible for children six weeks – 10.9 years of age.

    Our care giving philosophy is based on the belief that children are unique and respond best in an environment which fosters individuality, creativity, and growth.
    Our stimulating curriculum allows children to learn through the process of discovery and play while being guided by nurturing and professional staff. You will find our philosophy reflected in the quality and focus of our programs.
    The center’s modern facility was designed specifically with the children in mind and provides a safe, friendly, and warm environment where children can explore freely.
    Our convenient locations and extended hours meet the needs of today’s busy parents.

name: The Magical Years Early Learning Center
details:
Our purpose is to provide the highest quality early childhood programs in a secure, nurturing and stimulating environment. The Magical Years serves the physical, emotional and intellectual needs of the child and their families. We meet these goals with our age-appropriate curriculum, our highly qualified staff, state-of-the-art facilities, the highest standards of cleanliness, and our ongoing communication with parents.

All of the dedicated, caring staff at The Magical Years want to be certain that your child has the very best early childhood experience possible. We want to thank you for entrusting us with that privilege and responsibility.
business hours: Pembroke Center is open 6:30am - 6:00pm                                                                                     Halifax Center is open 7:00am - 6:00pm

name: The Playhouse Preschool Inc.
address: ST PAUL'S EPISCOPAL CHURCH 61 WOOD ST
details:
In todays busy world, children need unhurried time to "just be kids and have fun".  The preschool years are a precious time in their lives, where their needs for love and acceptance, play and exploration, and making new connections are our priorities.

The Playhouse uses The Creative Curriculum which is based on several accepted theories of child development and current research.  This curriculum follows developmentally appropriate practice (DAP) which is defined as giving children opportunities to learn and practice newly acquired skills, challenging them just beyond the level of their present mastery.  The Playhouse becomes their learning community.  An important component of our curriculum is the family.  We want to get to know all the family members, including pets, and encourage parents to linger during arrival time checking in with the teachers and playing with their child.  As the parent-teacher relationship grows, the child's trust and security blossoms and more energy can be focused on learning and discovery.  We use our knowledge of the stages of development and child observation to set up our learning centers.  The children's interests guide our choice of materials and activities.  The teachers and parents become partners in their child's development.

Our classroom is divided into approximately eight learning centers:
   - Art which includes crafts, play dough, writing, easel work
   - House for pretend play and dress up
   - Blocks and Building
   - Math, Alphabet, Board games
   - Reading corner
   - Dramatic play (theme changed monthly)
   - Science which includes a water and sensory table (changed monthly)
   - Music and movement
   - Playground, spacious and fenced in

The children are encouraged to follow their interests and make choices during free play time.  We maintain a balance of child directed and teacher directed activities throughout the day.  As they visit the different areas, they are practicing many of the basic skills that prepare them for kindergarten.  They're exposed to letter recognition and printing, counting and number comparisons, listening and reading comprehension, observing and questioning during science time, making friends and taking turns, and developing their gross motor skills on the playground.

name: The Tobin School
details: At The Tobin School, we are committed to developing happy, engaged and intellectually curious children. - See more at: http://www.thetobinschool.org/philosophy.html#sthash.dZa8LJiB.dpuf

name: The Village School
details:
The Village School is a safe and nurturing preschool for children ages 2.9-6 years where each child is encouraged to explore and learn through play.

We provide a variety of developmentally appropriate learning experiences to promote each child’s social, intellectual, emotional, and physical growth. Through rich classroom environments, engaging curricula, and guidance from experienced teachers, children are given the opportunity to develop at their own pace and in their own style. At the Village School, we strive to stimulate curiosity and provide hands-on experiences in all areas of learning to ensure that our preschoolers go off to Kindergarten to succeed.

name: Torit Language Center Montessori
details:
Torit Montessori School offers a unique early education, from infancy through Elementary School. We teach children in the Montessori tradition, a tradition well-researched, honed and perfected over more than 100 years. The method teaches strong subject matter foundations, which in turn underlie the inter-disciplinary 21st century skills ranging from social interconnectedness to technological entrepreneurship.

In keeping with Dr. Maria Montessori’s own globalism and commitment to peace education, we teach our children (future citizenry) the foreign languages of Arabic, Mandarin and Spanish. Our exceptional curriculum for children is complimented by schedules and offerings designed to support busy families.

The more you learn about Montessori, early foreign language exposure, interdisciplinary education and our school culture, the more convinced you may be that Torit Montessori School could be your perfect partner in the weighty, uplifting, journey that is child-rearing from birth through Elementary.
Quick Facts

details:
The mission of the Weymouth Montessori School is to prepare learning environments for children between the ages of 2.9 and 6 years that will aid in their natural development. This includes:

Creating environments where trust, respect, responsibility, community and cooperation can flourish.
Nurturing the social, emotional, and cognitive developmental needs for each child individually.
Respecting the rights of children as independent beings.
Providing a place where children are heard and given the opportunity for self-expression.
Creating challenging and safe environments.
Giving each child the tools necessary for him or her to realize his or her full potential.

name: YMCA of Martha's Vineyard After School Program
Morningside School Age Child Care
details:
Berkshire Children and Families offers exceptional education and care for children from birth through pre-kindergarten in Pittsfield. BCF also offers before- and after-school care programs for older children.

In BCF’s infant, toddler and preschool programs, your child plays, learns and thrives with extraordinary early childhood professionals. Our full-day, year-round programs provide education and care tailored to your child’s unique personality, individual needs and style. When it’s time for kindergarten, your child will be ready to go, and ready to shine.

Our programs are accredited through the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) and licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

name: Pam's Place Child Care Center
details:
Our Philosophy
PAM'S PLACE provides a safe, loving, and nurturing place for children to be so that parents may feel comfortable and relaxed knowing that their children are being well cared for.

At PAM'S PLACE every child comes first. They are their own selves with different values, customs, behaviors, strengths, and weaknesses. They are treated as individuals not as a group, each one unique and different from the rest. Our goal at PAM'S PLACE is for children to be happy learning to grow. By providing them with a warm and inviting atmosphere, children thrive on the socialization and educational activities that PAM'S PLACE has to offer.

name: Small World Preschool and Child Care Center
details:
Children are offered a supportive environment in which to express themselves creatively and to expand an awareness of themselves and the world around them. They are welcomed into a stimulating, child-centered environment which is exciting yet safe. Through praise, encouragement, support and positive reinforcement, children develop decision-making abilities, self-sufficiency, independence and problem-solving skills. Most importantly, they gain a positive self-image.

In a caring and positive atmosphere, we create a warm and happy place for preschoolers to learn. As we bridge the gap from home to school, we guide children to a continued good self-image while building social skills in a school setting.
 

Recognizing that children grow in predictable stages, we treat each child as an individual, working from the level each child has attained and moving forward a step at a time. We teach a love of learning and allow children to experience their own stage of development and help them to feel success without pressure.

We value the active involvement of parents in our program. Parents may gain valuable insights and techniques from the expertise of the staff and at the same time, share their own talents and interests to maintain the excellent quality here at SMALL WORLD. School then becomes a shared experience which hopefully will continue throughout each child’s educational process.

SMALL WORLD does not discriminate in providing services to children and their families on the basis of race, religion, cultural heritage, political beliefs, marital status, disability, sexual orientation, or national origin.
business hours: 7:30 a.m. and 5:30 p.m. Monday through Friday

name: Merrimack Child Care Center
details:
Merrimack Child Care Center provides all day care and before/after school care for children ages 6 weeks to 10 years. Public school bus transportation to/from Merrimac schools, Crowell and Golden Hill schools is available for kindergarten and elementary age children. Known as “the little red school house” in the historic Rocks Village section of Haverhill, Merrimack Child Care has been serving the needs of the Haverhill-Newburyport area for over 40 years. Our mission is to provide quality, affordable day care to the community on a non-profit basis.

Benefits for your Child
A child centered environment
Social & educational experiences
Physical well-being
Emotional development
Security & love
Cognitive development
Reading readiness skills
Speech & language development
Opportunity for creative development
Training in self discipline
Positive relationships
Incentive for self motivation

Safe, nurturing environment
Alternative home care structure
Confidence about their child’s care
Positive growth for your child
Opportunity for involvement in the center
Support & guidance when needed

Our Staff
All staff are certified by the Department of Early Education and Care and experienced in the field of early childhood.

name: YMCA School Age Child Care Program
Pawtucketville Memorial Program
details: Pawtucketville Memorial Elementary School is a collaborative community fostering high expectations, which encompassed by a caring, safe and respectful environment. Our learning culture is anchored in a comprehensive curriculum and effective instruction. We frame our school on the philosophy that we are all teachers and we are all learners. At Pawtucketville School we are committed to the academic and social growth of our entire community of learners.  We believe that with determination, perseverance and resiliency we can all be successful.

name: The Northbridge After School Program
details: Cherub's Haven provides quality childcare, preschool, and after school care to families residing in Linwood and the surrounding areas. Children learn daily life skills, manners, and early childhood education that will help them as they grow and further their education. Our staff members, many of which have been with our facility for 5+ years, are all certified and provide a nurturing and safe learning environment. We understand how difficult it can be for parents to entrust the care of their child with other people. That is why at Cherub's Haven, we treat the children we care for as if they were our own. We are a professionally staffed child care center which cares and educates children from infancy to school age. Our goal as educators is to provide an external environment that will create a positive self-image and sense of self worth in each child. Thus aiding his or her growth in the areas of socialization, concept development, problem solving, language development, and sensory development. We are able to accomplish this through programs that we have designed to elicit the natural desire to learn that is inherit in each child.
business hours:
Monday-Friday: 3:00 pm - 6:00 pm

Release Days: 12:00 pm - 6:00 pm

Full Days: 6:30 am- 6:00 pm

name: Mother's Morning Out, Inc.
details:
We at MMO provide your children with a first-class early development education.  We focus on children ages 2 to 5 and offer a variety of program options.
Mothers Morning Out's mission is to develop the academic and social growth of the individual child in a safe nurturing setting. Students are encouraged to express their ideas, make decisions, explore and experience their suroundings. We encourage them to be independent while also learning to respect others. Our play based approach utilizes the classroom situation as a learning tool. 
      Our child centered classrooms are full of materials that will interest and develop the mind of the individual child. Daily activities promote learning through self-expression, good decision making skills and exploration of their environment.
business hours:
Monday, Tuesday,Thursday
9:00am to 3:15pm

 Wednesday and Friday 
9:00AM to 1:00PM

name: St. John's Nursery School
details: St. John’s Nursery School is a NAEYC (www.naeyc.org) accredited pre-school established to meet the needs of the three-year old nursery school child. St. John’s has served young children for over thirty-five years in Westwood. A curriculum has been set up to provide a diverse, creative learning experience catering to the child’s developmental level. The program follows a structured plan while leaving room for flexibility that allows the children to be creative and explore many materials within an enriching, literacy-based environment. Children grow into relationships with peers while subtly directed by an attentive and dedicated staff. The curriculum is designed to help each child develop emotionally, physically, intellectually and socially in a caring environment. Each child is accepted as an individual and is encouraged to grow with independence, self-assurance, and self-esteem.

name: West Falmouth Preschool
details:
Welcome to West Falmouth Preschool – a parent cooperative that nurtures and develops a child’s love of learning, independence and creativity.

West Falmouth Preschool is a non-profit, Early Education and Care-licensed school for children between the ages of 2.9 and 5 years old. Certified teachers and dedicated parents work together to provide a positive learning environment where children are encouraged to create, explore, investigate, problem solve, experiment, and share. The West Falmouth Preschool is a warm, caring and cozy place where kids can be kids!

name: The Red School, Inc., Site 1
details: We are an exceptional childcare center, dedicated to the educational needs of all children aged 15 months to 7 years old. We are fully licensed, insured, and offer a nurturing yet structured pre-school, pre-k and full-day kindergarten programs celebrating the differences that make us wonderful individuals and openly welcome the children and families of all races, cultural heritages, religions and special needs. Since 2004, we have offered a loving learning environment where children respond because of that environment, all our children are happy and feel cared for and loved.

name: Peas in a Pod Nursery School
details: We are an exceptional childcare center, dedicated to the educational needs of all children aged 15 months to 7 years old. We are fully licensed, insured, and offer a nurturing yet structured pre-school, pre-k and full-day kindergarten programs celebrating the differences that make us wonderful individuals and openly welcome the children and families of all races, cultural heritages, religions and special needs. Since 2004, we have offered a loving learning environment where children respond because of that environment, all our children are happy and feel cared for and loved.

name: Witchcraft Kids Cllub
details:
The Boys & Girls Club of Greater Salem engages a Formula for Impact that ensures that success is within reach of every young person who walks through our doors with all members promoted from one grade to the next and on track to graduate from high school with a plan for the future, demonstrating good character and citizenship, and living a healthy lifestyle.

This Formula is accomplished by employing caring adult professionals, utilizing nationally tested programs including those that are evidence-based, and understanding that we are “Powered by the Community.”

Every day we expand the minds and broaden the horizons of our youth while also developing their sense of belonging to the community.

name: YMCA School Age Child Care At Cole School
Walnut Grove School House, Inc.
details:
Walnut Grove School House is a year- round, privately owned facility offering traditional childcare for ages 4 weeks to 8 years old. We pride ourselves on our warm loving environment, as we try to make it a place a way from home.

A place where children can grow, learn and explore as they have fun. Our mission is to provide the highest quality educational care available as well as providing a safe nurturing setting.

Teaching children a love for learning, and building the foundation for future educational success is the main focus of our curriculum. Preparing all children for their school years by providing experiences that enhance and stimulate growth socially, cognitively, and physically. Walnut Grove School House is licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care, and accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children.

name: North Suburban Family YMCA/Memorial School
details: Parents love YMCA After School, our family-centered program that nurtures the whole child by inspiring academic success, healthy movement and social and emotional development. Our staff of caring, trained educators are role models who lead activities that promote cooperation and character development. Parents can be productive at work knowing their children are in a safe and stimulating after school environment.

name: Northfield Mount Hermon School
details: The Northfield Mount Hermon Campus Nursery School provides quality early childhood care for the children of parents working at Northfield Mount Hermon and in the surrounding community. We provide a nurturing environment that is rich in experiences designed to encourage independence and support the development of a positive sense of self. Our goal is to help children develop at their own pace while learning age-appropriate skills. We recognize and respect the unique qualities, abilities, and potential of each child. We provide a stimulating educational and social environment where children feel confident and secure. We are committed to supporting all aspects of children’s growth in an atmosphere of respect.

name: Springfield Jewish Community Center Pre School
Milestones Childrens Center
details:
Milestones Children's Center, an independently owned child care center founded in 2000, has a focus on children as individuals.  We provide a developmentally appropriate environment for the care of children one month to five years of age.  The Center's schedules, policies, and program are designed to meet the social-emotional, physical and intellectual needs of the children served. Classes include infant, toddler, tots, preschool and pre-kindergarten programs.
 
We acknowledge children's play as an essential component of a developmentally appropriate curriculum.  Therefore, we encourage children to play and create as we guide them in gaining knowledge, independence and self-confidence in their abilities.  Children have the opportunity to play in small groups and/or alone with various hands-on materials inside learning centers: dramatic play; blocks; art; sensory; language/writing; manipulatives; and books within the classrooms.

name: The Wonderful World of Children
details: Our mission is to provide preschool education to young children and to establish a nurturing school atmosphere so that children and their families can have a sense of belonging. We want children to have a love of learning while they are having fun as well.

name: Pre-School Playmates
details: At Pre-School Playmates, our goal for all of our children is that when they leave our program to enter into public school, they will be strong emotionally, socially, and academically. We will work very hard to make sure your child has developed great self-esteem while being in our program. The emphasis in our program is learning through Art and Music. We will put on several shows during the year where the children will sing and dance and learn many new songs and poems. We will also do an amazing Art show where the children will be exposed to several well known artists such as Monet and Van Gogh. We will never discriminate against any child or family based on their religion, race, cultural heritage, political beliefs, national origin, marital status, sexual orientation, or disability. We believe every child deserves an amazing early childhood experience and we will work every day to be sure they get one at Pre-School Playmates.

name: Self Help, Inc Head Start - Norwood
details:
The Head Start Program is based on the premise that all children share certain needs and that children of low income families, in particular, can benefit from a comprehensive developmental program to meet those needs. The Head Start approach make the following assumptions:

A child can benefit from a comprehensive, interdisciplinary program to foster development.

Because the family is the principal influence on the child's development, the child's family, as well as the community, must be involved in the program.

The overall goal of the Head Start Program is to bring about a greater degree of social competence in children of low-income families. Social competence means the child's everyday effectiveness in dealing with both the present environment and later responsibilities in school and in life. Social competence takes into account the interrelatedness of cognitive and intellectual development, physical and mental health,nutritional needs as well as other factors. To achieve social competence, Head Start objectives and performance standards provide for:

    Improvement of the child's health and physical abilities, including appropriate steps to correct physical and mental health problems and to enhance every child's access to an adequate diet.
    Improvement of the family's attitude toward future health care and physical abilities.
    Encouragement of self-confidence, spontaneity, curiosity and self-discipline that will assist the child's social and emotional health.
    Enhancement of the child's mental processes and skill, with particular attention to conceptual and communication skills.
    Establishment of patterns and expectations for success for the child that will create a climate of confidence for present and future learning efforts and overall development.
    Enhancement of the ability of the child and the family to relate to one another and to others.
    Development of a sense of dignity and self-worth within the child and his family.
business hours: 8:30 am to 4:30 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Tiny Tots Nursery School
details:
Tiny Tots Preschool was established in 1968 and is the longest running preschool in the town of Easton. Tiny Tots is a State accredited school licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care. First and foremost, we believe in joyful learning!  We are dedicated to providing exciting opportunities for the children to develop both cognitively, socially and emotionally through arts, thematic units and creative play. Speech and language, and fine motor skills are developed daily through literature, crafts, finger play and music and movement. Through interaction with their peers, the children engage in problem solving, and conflict resolution, as well as making lasting friendships. Under the guidance of our devoted and nurturing teachers, the children are provided opportunities to develop self-confidence, independence, and a love of learning, which is the true beginning of a great student and academic success. Our  large gym and outdoor playground promotes gross motor development and provide physical activity, encouraging health and fitness on a daily basis.

We offer a spacious, cheery classroom environment, with curriculum geared towards learning through open-ended, hands-on activities that encourage curiosity and enthusiasm throughout the school year. Fun and exciting themes, our large gym, and/or outdoor play yard, provide the opportunity for the children to learn, be creative, and freely express themselves in a safe and nurturing environment.  Most importantly, we strive to make all our children feel secure, special, and loved focusing on each child's individuality and uniqueness.

name: Southern Berkshire Child Care Program and After School Program
Robin's Nest Day Care Center Afterschool Program
details:
Our philosophy at the Robin's Nest Daycare Center is to ensure an environment that fosters genuine love, concern in which children are guided toward their fullest development physically, emotionally, socially, and mentally. Through our programs we seek to prepare children for more formal learning in later years by presenting a wide range of materials for introduction to language, social studies, science, math, art, and music.

Our schedule of daily activities will encourage children in developing greater self-relianc and confidence. We always have a wide variety of pets, dogs and cats on the premises for the children to receive a little extra love. Our staff includes licensed professionals and aides specifically trained in early childhood education. We also provide opportunities for parent involvement. Parents are encouraged to visit and make suggestions. There will be written progress reports updating your child's social, intellectual, physical and emotional development sent home in January and June. Parents may request conferences at any time of the week. Information contained in these reports are the child's records which are confidential and shall not be released to anyone without written parental consent. Parents have access to their child's records.

We provide a safe, caring environment where children are able to develop a positive sense of self, participate in a range of developmentally appropriate activities, learn life skills such as making friends, learning to share and waiting your turn. We celebrate all of the qualities that make each child a unique gift and encourage him/her to explore through play and learning all that he/she can become.

name: Allson Brighton St. Gabriel's Head Start
details: ABCD provides innovative, timely programs that promote upward mobility and a higher quality of life for people and communities. Empowering people by providing them with the tools to overcome poverty, live with dignity & achieve their full potential. ABCD responds to the needs of our community through our decentralized, city-wide network, which includes 14 unique neighborhood centers.

name: Little Wagon Early Care & Education Center
details: Welcome to the Little Wagon Early Education Center in Waltham. You are about to learn a Chinese-English preschool program begun by the Cambridge Center for Chinese Culture. The Center (CCCC) has a rich history described in detail in its website. Our program opened in March 2005 and is first and foremost a quality nurturing and educational experience for young children. Little Wagon is a bilingual Chinese-English multicultural preschool program that will serve the public. It will be a place where children whose first language is Chinese can learn English in a setting that affirms their culture of origin. And for children whose first language is English, it offers an opportunity to learn Chinese language, dance and art.  Our goal is to bring together the best of western-style developmentally appropriate practice with the best of Chinese early childhood practice. Teachers will pay close attention to the children's physical, intellectual, creative, social and emotional development. We believe children are eager to learn new things and will provide many opportunities for hands-on exploration and problem solving. Honoring children's growing awareness of the world around them, respecting their thoughts and feelings, the program will support curiosity, build confidence and self-esteem, and nurture excellence. .

name: Mason Rice After School The Hut
Winchester School of Chinese Culture After School Program
details:
Winchester School of Chinese Culture (WSCC) is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization whose mission is to teach the language and traditional culture of China through classroom instructions, the arts, and cultural events and to promote and engage in cultural exchanges and civic activities to develop and sustain community-school partnerships.

To accomplish its mission, the school relies on experienced teachers, the cooperation and involvement of parents, the active participation of students, and the support of the community. The school seeks to provide students with a foundation for future learning and to cultivate a life-long interest in the language and cultural traditions of China by creating an enjoyable learning environment. The school is committed to high professional standards and is a member of the Association of Chinese Schools (1st District) and the New England Chinese School Association.

name: Puddle Jumpers Learning Center LLC
details:
Welcome to Puddle Jumpers Learning Center
At our center your child is our first priority.  We provide an environment that will assist your child in his/her growth and development.  

We are proud of our center and program and we want to do all we can to serve your needs and those of your family and community.

name: Wellfleet Childcare Association After School Program
Longmeadow Montessori
details: At Longmeadow Montessori Internationale, we believe that Montessori is more than just a method of education; it is a philosophy of life that we honor in our classroom. We believe the Montessori principles support a child’s fullest development, independence, initiative, creativity, self-discipline, and confidence.

name: Norwood Cooperative Nursery School
details:
The Norwood Cooperative Nursery School, Inc. offers a child-centered, teacher-guided preschool experience. At NCNS, children are provided with ample opportunity to learn through play. Play is a medium through which children learn about themselves and the world around them. We define classrooms as communities where children are provided with concrete learning materials and activities relevant to their own lives.

The Norwood Cooperative Nursery School, Inc. is a nonprofit, nonsectarian preschool serving Norwood and surrounding communities. The school was established in 1962, incorporated in 1978 under Massachusetts State Law and gained tax-exempt status in 1980. NCNS is licensed in Massachusetts by the Department of Early Education and Care.

Our school is located at 24 Berwick Street in Norwood, adjacent to Berwick Park, occupying the lower level of the Emmanuel Lutheran Church since 1983.

With the growing consciousness of peanut-allergy in the general population, NCNS is peanut-free.

name: Temple Nursery School
details:
Temple Nursery School is a non-profit preschool founded in 1974.  The school was established to provide young children in Burlington and surrounding communities with an age appropriate education in a safe, nurturing, bias-free environment.

Our program  offers 2 to 5 days for children 2 years and 9 months to 5 years old as well as extended play options.

We are licensed by the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care.

name: Early Childhood School of Georgetown
details:
As we are dedicated to consistently providing the best in early childhood education and care, we make it a point to stay current on best practices, child-developmental pedagogies and developmental benchmarks. We believe in small group, process-orientated instruction and constant, clear communication between our families and our educators. It is this prior experience, combined with our knowledge and implementation of Massachusetts State Frameworks for early childhood education that will ensure your child a seamless transition into his or her school age experience.

It is our goal that family, school and community work together as a unified team to enrich your child’s development. In this spirit of collaboration, our office door is always open for feedback or discussion. We always enjoy the opportunity to provide prospective parents with a tour of our early childhood school, so that you see the joy and wonder of hands-on learning!

name: Mittineague's Children Center
details: We are committed to providing excellence in early childhood care and education to the families and children in our community.  We are delighted to partner with  you in providing great beginnings for your child.  Mittineague Children's Center's main goal is to provide developmentally appropriate early education experiences and consistent loving care in a warm and nurturing environment for children ages 8 weeks to 7 years.

name: Make Way for Ducklings
details:
PHILOSOPHY: M.W.F.D. philosophy is to foster each child’s development to his or her full potential: cognitively, emotionally, physically and socially.  This goal is accomplished by providing a warm and stimulating environment in which children can learn and grow.  At M.W.F.D. children are helped to build self-esteem, to exercise self-control, and to learn to interact with their peers and teachers, as individuals and in-group situations.  Hands-on experiences are provided in and out of the classroom.  The enriched curriculum includes field trips and special programming in the areas of physical education and music.  Areas covered in the curriculum are outlined in the progress reports.

Make Way for Ducklings has set Goals, Objectives and Standards as guides in working with young children and their families.  At your visit you will be introduced to our guidelines and upon enrollment you will receive a copy of  M.W.F.D. Parent Handbook which includes our policies, procedure, standards, goals and objectives.

name: Second Church Nursery School
details: Our Mission:  The Second Church Nursery School is a nonsectarian nursery school serving families in Newton and the surrounding communities. Toddler classes, morning preschool classes and extended afternoon sessions are offered. Children are grouped developmentally to promote their growth and to enhance their social, cognitive and motor skills. Second Church Nursery School is designed to help your child become a confident, happy and independent person!

name: The Little Souls Center for Children
SMOC Head Start Northbridge
details: Head Start provides comprehensive early education and support services for children ages three to five and their families. In addition to providing center-based and home-based preschool education, the program provides supportive services in the areas of health and dental care, nutrition, special education, parent skill workshops and social services. Children are provided with a daily lunch and breakfast or snack, which meet all federal, and state nutrition guidelines. Door-to-door transportation is provided at many of the centers. Classrooms typically operate from September through May, Mondays through Fridays and from 8:30am to 2pm.

name: Triumph, Inc Head Start
details: Triumph, Inc. is an independent non-profit 501c3 agency incorporated in 1965. TRIUMPH is an acronym that stands for "Taunton Responds in Unison Many People Help". This spirit of community support remains an integral part of Triumph's work today. Initial funding came in the form of a federal Head Start grant during the summer of 1965 as part of President Lyndon Johnson's War on Poverty. Forty-eight years, later the Head Start program remains a central focus of the agency. Triumph's exceptionally high quality programming focuses on children under the age of five. We are deeply committed to the belief that parents are a child's first and most important teacher. We work in close partnership with families and offer a range of programs and opportunities that support families in growing strong and successful children. The agency is committed to ensuring that children and families of all socio-economic levels in the city of Taunton and town of Raynham, Massachusetts have access to the very best early childhood experiences.

name: TLC Preschool and Child Care Center
Old Colony YMCA Preschool
details:
Before and After School Care is a great option for children of parents who need care which fits with both work and school schedules.  Children can choose from a wide variety of activities including arts & crafts, reading, sports, games, plus field trips, themed special events, team building activites, and more!
 
The Old Colony YMCA believes that each child is special, with his or her own personality, talents, and skills.  Our approach to child care reflects the YMCA's core values of caring, honesty, respect, and responsibility, as well as our commitment to building strong kids, strong families and strong communities.
 
We offer so many wonderful activities and programs - all in a safe, nuturing, developmentally appropriate environment!

name: Park Street Kids, Inc.
details:
What makes an education remarkable? Passionate teachers, an engaging curriculum, committed parents and a strong vision are essential. Appealing spaces and places to learn are valuable, and location is important. Harder to define – but equally vital – is a sense of spirit, community and purpose.

Welcome to Park Street School and Park Street Kids, a continuous, integrated Christian-based education for children, toddler through sixth grade.

Park Street School and Park Street Kids are grounded in a content-rich curriculum that lays a foundation of knowledge, built upon and expanded in each grade. Our children engage in hands-on activities, learn to think creatively and solve problems methodically. Their growth as unique individuals – academically, spiritually, emotionally and physically – is fostered with intention in a nurturing environment. They develop a strong sense of self and place, learning to invest in their communities and the world around them.

name: MOC Child Care and Head Start Services
details: Head Start provides comprehensive early education and support services for children ages three to five and their families. In addition to providing center-based and home-based preschool education, the program provides supportive services in the areas of health and dental care, nutrition, special education, parent skill workshops and social services. Children are provided with a daily lunch and breakfast or snack, which meet all federal, and state nutrition guidelines. Door-to-door transportation is provided at many of the centers. Classrooms typically operate from September through May, Mondays through Fridays and from 8:30am to 2pm.

name: Maple Street Learn & Play Preschool & Daycare
Oak Square YMCA SACC Program
details: Parents love YMCA After School, our family-centered program that nurtures the whole child by inspiring academic success, healthy movement and social and emotional development. Our staff of caring, trained educators are role models who lead activities that promote cooperation and character development. Parents can be productive at work knowing their children are in a safe and stimulating after school environment.

name: Shannah Montessori School, Rms 15-1, 15-2 and 21B
details: Our School provides Montessori based education for children aged 18 months through 6 years of age. We are located in the heart of Magnolia, Massachusetts, a quaint, family oriented town situated along the ocean. The name "Shannah" is derived from the Irish word "Shannon", which means "small, but wise". We strive to keep a small and intimate feeling to the school with an emphasis on quality Montessori education. We strongly believe that every child, although small in stature, has the potential of unwrapping their inner strengths and wisdom.

name: Waquoit Nursery School
details:
Waquoit Nursery School has served the community as a non-sectarian, non-profit, cooperative school since 1975. We believe that a child's years from three to five are of vital importance.

WNS provides a warm, safe and loving environment that will nurture your child's social, emotional and academic growth. Through working, sharing, and playing with others, your child will develop traits of independence and self-reliance.

Our school was founded on the cooperative ideal and requires parent participation. Parent helpers are scheduled to assist in the classroom one day each month. Responsibilities include assisting the teachers, providing a snack and drink for the day and clean up.

A Board of Directors, consisting of past and present parents, govern our school. It is the responsibility of each parent to make contributions to their child's preschool experience as well as to the school as a whole.

name: YMCA Nursery School
details:
The YMCA of Greater Westfield offers a variety of child care programs; Preschool and Before and After School Care. All of our child care is state certified.

Visit our welcome desk to register for the Y’s Kids State Licensed Before & After School Care registration for the ongoing school year!

Our Before School program runs from 7:00AM-9:00AM and includes games, sports, arts and crafts, as well as homework help. Our After School program runs from 2:30PM-6:00PM and includes homework tutoring, STEAM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts and Math activities), sports,  cooking, games, arts & crafts and more!

Full day, half day, snow day and vacation day care is also available. Children currently enrolled in our Before and After School programs receive a discounted rate. Extended care, in the event of two hour school delays and early releases due to inclement weather, is also included in your weekly fee.

name: Magic Years
details: At Magic Years, we have programs for children age 4 weeks to 5 years that involves a loving atmosphere in a learning environment. Owner and director Elisabeth Kelly has over 20 years of experience in the childcare industry. Please call us to schedule a visit.

name: Viveiros After School Day Care
details: Every child deserves access to a healthy, safe, productive and nurturing environment. We believe that day care services must be administered by qualified personnel who promote positive social behavior through developmentally appropriate and stimulating activities that meet the educational, social, emotional and recreational needs of our families.

name: Scantic Valley YMCA Child Development Center
South Shore YMCA Quincy ASCP Marshall School
Pine Village Preschool
details:
Our Mission is to educate and nurture each child’s individuality within a culturally diverse, bilingual community so that every child develops a true passion for learning and an ability to engage in any environment and community.

Our CORE values define our choices and hold the truths of what is most important to us as an organization. These four elements cannot stand alone within Pine Village.  We need each of them to be present in our schools and our classrooms, as well as within the organization as a whole. When these four elements exist our choices are strong and our approach is clear.

name: Smith College Center for Early Childhood Education
Salvation Army Day Children's Learning Center
details: The Children's Learning Center is the oldest childcare facility in The Salvation Army's Massachusetts Division. This facility has provided outstanding education to more than 2,400 children in its 38-year history at its present location on Wales St. and over 5,000 families throughout its 86 year history. Currently, the Children's Learning Center (CLC) serves 60 preschool children between the ages of 2.9 to 5years of age from the Dorchester area and surrounding neighborhoods. The operating hours are 7:30 am to 5:30 pm and a nutritious breakfast, lunch and snack is provided at no extra cost. Transportation is provided for the children. All of the teachers are EEC certified. The CLC accepts vouchers, EEC contracted slots, MBTA slots, and Salvation Army reduced rate slots are available. Paige Farley-Hackel Memorial PlaygroundThe Salvation Army Children's Learning Center strives to provide a place where children and families can find vital services. At the Salvation Army CLC, a preschoolers' world begins as a caterpillar and opens up into a beautiful butterfly as they learn hands on skills through play and one on one supervised activities. The Salvation Army CLC has an organized theme based curriculum that addresses everyday situations that encourage children to develop and foster social, emotional, physical and cognitive skills. The CLC has an on site playground and structured field trips.

name: Mansfield YMCA - Balcom St. School's Out
details: Play, learn, and grow in our School’s Out program which offers a before-and-after-school experience with healthy, constructive enrichment activities. A nutritious snack is offered daily. We follow the eight core contents of the YMCA’s School-Age Curriculum, which incorporates literacy, science, technology, health, wellness and fitness, arts and humanities, homework support, service learning, character development, and social competence and conflict resolution.

name: The Preschool Center II
details:
Our Mission
    The primary mission of The Preschool Center Inc. is to help parents raise healthy, happy children who will become confident successful learners. It is our belief that your child’s sense of belonging to a family should not be weakened by a group educational and care experience, but rather your family ties will be strengthened as we share in the planning and the excitement of your child’s days and weeks at school.

name: The Rocking Unicorn Nursery School
details:
The Rocking Unicorn Nursery School was established in 1981. It is owned/operated by Gretchen Kolb Cauble, M.S. Ed. Gretchen is a 1984 graduate of Chatham High School, a 1988 graduate of Colby-Sawyer College, and received her Master's Degree in Education from Wheelock College in 1993.

The facility is licensed by the MA Dept of Early Education and Care. All teachers and administrators meet and exceed the state requirements for certification. Additional state certifications include the areas of early childhood education, elementary education and special education.

Enrollment is open to 24 children per day, ranging in age of 2 years 9 months through pre-kindergarten. The three year old program has a 1:6 teacher to child ratio; the pre-kindergarten program has a 1:8 ratio.

name: Play-Learn-Preschool, LLC
details:
Our primary concern is to help each child develop a healthy self-image by encouraging self-confidence, appreciation for others, and positive social interaction.

Play-Learn Preschool is a supervised environment that promotes healthy growth and development. Our teachers fill each day with a wide variety of fun, age-appropriate experiences and challenges designed to prepare children for a lifetime of learning. Our activities focus on socialization skills, fine and gross motor coordination, language skills, and auditory and visual activities.

We involve parents in their childrens' education by encouraging regular school visits, volunteering, and maintaining open communication between home and school.

name: United Methodist Nursery School
details: ﻿The United Methodist Nursery School is a non-profit, non-sectarian program, founded in 1969, owned and operated by Crawford Memorial United Methodist Church. Our curriculum mixes structure with plenty of flexibility for young active minds, taught by a highly qualified team of teachers in a happy nurturing environment.  The Nursery School program is licensed by the Dept. of Early Education and Care of Massachusetts and is in compliance with all Health and Safety Regulations of the Town of Winchester. It is also accredited by the National Academy of Early Childhood Programs.

name: W O R D, Inc Child Care Center
Plymouth House Nursery School
details: Plymouth House Nursery School first opened its doors to children in 1959 as one of the first preschools in Framingham. We started off as a small program offered to Plymouth Church parishioners, then in 1961 we opened our doors to welcome children from surrounding towns. We pride ourselves in our reputation and excellent service to young children over the years. Plymouth House Nursery School is licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care (E.E.C.) and is accredited by the National Education of Young Children (N.A.E.Y.C.). All of our Lead Teachers have been with our program for many years and truly enjoy the children they teach. We offer many programs to serve your family's needs; full and part time, early drop off, extended hours and a summer program. Our building houses four large, bright classrooms, a large space for our music and physical education programs. We have a beautiful fenced in playground and plenty of room to explore nature and science on property surrounding the school. Our experienced and certified staff has been with our program for many years and truly enjoys the children they teach. Our music and physical education classes are lead by experienced professionals. We offer a program that will build your child's self esteem and prepare them for their future years in education. We provide a safe environment for children to explore and nurture the world of learning. We provide a diverse program of language, social, emotional, and academic skills at a pace for children to learn and succeed.

name: Old South Union Nursery School
details:
Welcome to Old South Union Preschool celebrating fifty years of educational excellence.

At Old South Union Preschool students acquire a strong foundation for future academic success. Teachers strive to instill in each child a lifelong love of learning.

We hope this site will help familiarize you with our program and answer any questions you may have about us.

name: Small Wonders Learning Center
details:
Our Philosophy:  At Small Wonders, we believe that each child is a special individual with unique experiences and perceptions of the world.

Our Goals:  To build high self esteem; To promote social and cultural awareness; To foster emotional and intellectual growth; To provide activities that are fun, but also challenge and stimulate young children; To give parents “peace of mind”; To provide high quality early care and education services at reasonable prices.  Children are learning skills and academics needed to succeed in kindergarten and beyond. A love of learning is important, so all educational activities and teacher directed learning time are fun and flexible to help each child learn at his or her own pace.

Services provided: We care for children 6 months-kindergarten both full and part time; Open year round; Written daily reports for all classrooms; Bi-annual progress reports for each child; Sibling discounts; Snacks and drinks provided daily; Hot lunches available; Flexible schedules

name: Thomas Chew Memorial Boys & Girls
details:
Our Mission is to enable youth to reach their full potential as responsible, caring and productive citizens.

We believe that that every child in our community should have a safe place to learn and play, where caring adults supervise, guide and lead them to adulthood. The Boys & Girls Club of Fall River is that place. To the full extent of our powers, we will assure that our members will complete high school and have access to a post-secondary education. In partnership with our community, we will be outstanding stewards of the public trust and our donors’ gifts.

name: Montessori Children's House of West Springfield, Inc.
details: Montessori Children's House of West Springfield Inc. Preschool through 3rd grade. We are open all year round. Located in West Springfield, we are one of the finest private schools in the country.

name: North Suburban Family YMCA/Burlington Extended Day Program
details: Parents love YMCA After School, our family-centered program that nurtures the whole child by inspiring academic success, healthy movement and social and emotional development. Our staff of caring, trained educators are role models who lead activities that promote cooperation and character development. Parents can be productive at work knowing their children are in a safe and stimulating after school environment.

name: Square One @ King Street
details:
King Street is a well-established early education and care center located near Springfield College. Our staff is diverse with many bi-lingual and bi-cultural teachers. A brand new, beautiful playground was installed in 2012 -- it is a large, fabulous play space with an outdoor water spray, bicycle track and a large gardening area.  At this time, we are active participants in the Department of Early Education and Care's Quality Rating Improvement System and have just recently submitted for our NAEYC (National Association of Young Children) accreditation with an anticipated site visit in the Fall. This accreditation is like the Good Housekeeping seal of approval in our world!

We have a cooperative Program with Putnam Vocational Academy.  Juniors and seniors enrolled in Putnam’s early childhood tract alternate weeks between  Square One and their academic program @ Putnam providing all Square One children with additional attention and care.

Our curriculum is based on national outcome expectations and all our children are regularly assessed to ensure they are reaching their full educational, emotional and social potential. Literacy is a big component of our work with story books and literature incorporated into our daily learning schedules. Field trips are taken regularly to local museums, farms and other exciting attractions.

We would look forward to hosting you for a tour and look forward to supporting your child's educational success.

name: North Star LC - Schooner Program
details: Born from local community action during the civil rights movement, NorthStar Learning Centers remains grounded in our original vision to provide individualized, strength-based, family-focused programs that "help children, youth, and families realize their strengths and dreams." Founded in 1974, we have grown from one neighborhood-based preschool center to a constellation of programs that serve New Bedford area children from birth to adulthood. In all our programs, we are committed to serving the underserved and reaching the " hard-to-reach."

name: Little Red Schoolhouse
details:
The Little Red Schoolhouse operates as part of the Sheldonville Community Center, Inc., a not-for-profit organization dedicated to supporting and enhancing the community.  That spirit of community spills over into the classroom.

We believe that every hand needs another, every tear deserves drying, every voice deserves respect and every child helps another.  While the children are part of the Little Red Community for a few short years, our hope is to touch their lives forever.

If you are not familiar with our school and your first contact with us is online: We would be pleased to hear from you! Please let us know what your needs and questions are, we will be more than happy to help.

name: Underwood After School
details:
The Underwood After School Program or UASP was founded in 1982 by several parents in the Underwood Elementary School. The program was established to provide a safe, nurturing, and enriching environment for children in grades K to 5 after the school day ends.

The primary goal of the program is to meet the individual needs of children by offering flexibility within a structured, stimulating environment. The program offers a wide range of activities including arts and crafts, music, drama, sports, games, and field trips. In addition, the children's experiences are enriched by allowing the opportunity for interaction with both younger and older children.

The Underwood After School Program is staffed by a group of professionals with wide ranging backgrounds, working together for the safety, care, and enrichment of the children in the program.

name: Churchill Homes Early Education & Child Care Center
details: VOC operates five childcare centers in Holyoke and Chicopee. Our goal is to assist parents who are working, in training leading to employment, or have other special needs. We provide a complete education program, meals, and opportunities for parent involvement.

name: Nashoba Montessori School, Inc.
details:
Nashoba Montessori School is a place where your child can reach their fullest potential in a learning environment which promotes respect, independence, and personal achievement.

Nashoba Montessori School, inc. was established in 2000. The director is certified in Montessori Education, holds a B.S. in Elementary Education, and is a member of the American Montessori Society, International Montessori Society, Montessori Foundation and the Massachusetts Teachers’ Association.

“The goal of early childhood education should not be to fill a child with facts from a set course, but rather to cultivate his own natural desire to learn.” - Dr. Maria Montessori

We offer an enriched curriculum based on Dr. Maria Montessori’s philosophy for early childhood development. Believing that a child’s early development is a critical factor in later success, we offer an environment that promotes a lifelong love for learning. Children are given the basics of all-future studies; Science/Nature, Math, Language, Art, Music, Cultural Studies and Cooking.

Children are free to work at their own pace with materials they have chose.  The teacher relies on his/her own observations of the children to determine which new activities and material may be introduced to challenge and ensure success for the child.  The aim is to encourage active learning.

A child’s fine motor skills, care of the environment, care of self, as well as grace and courtesy develop through activities in daily living. The sensorial materials develop the skills of observation in every sense, develop rich vocabulary, as well as an appreciation of the materials used. Language develops through many materials in the classroom. Stories, songs, poems, the vocabulary used in geography and science, and the tactile sandpaper letters all contribute to a multi-faceted approach to learning.

Math concepts initiate with concrete materials including sorting, counting and problem solving. Eventually, children move on to use the many math materials available in our classrooms.

name: School Age Mother's Infant & Toddler Center
Sandy's School of Southborough
details:
Sandy Boucher is the owner and director of Sandy’s School. She has 30 years of child care experience and still loves teaching and being with the children.

Our teachers are all qualified, certified and very experienced. Some of them have even attended Sandy’s School as a child.  Many of the   children enrolled now have also had parents who attended here when they were small. 

Our small based center provides a home away from home atmosphere with a lot of emphasis placed on a more personal interaction with the family as opposed to a larger center.

Our program is known for providing a very friendly, warm, comfortable, and nurturing environment which allows children to learn at their own pace without feeling pressured.

Our group ratios are small enough that we can offer a variety of learning experiences to enhance each child’s individual growth.

We offer a structured and organized curriculum which promotes many learning experiences and emphasizes having fun and playing.

name: Ulysses G. Shelton Headstart Center
details:
The Head Start Program is based on the premise that all children share certain needs and that children of low income families, in particular, can benefit from a comprehensive developmental program to meet those needs. The Head Start approach make the following assumptions:

A child can benefit from a comprehensive, interdisciplinary program to foster development.

Because the family is the principal influence on the child's development, the child's family, as well as the community, must be involved in the program.

The overall goal of the Head Start Program is to bring about a greater degree of social competence in children of low-income families. Social competence means the child's everyday effectiveness in dealing with both the present environment and later responsibilities in school and in life. Social competence takes into account the interrelatedness of cognitive and intellectual development, physical and mental health,nutritional needs as well as other factors. To achieve social competence, Head Start objectives and performance standards provide for:

    Improvement of the child's health and physical abilities, including appropriate steps to correct physical and mental health problems and to enhance every child's access to an adequate diet.
    Improvement of the family's attitude toward future health care and physical abilities.
    Encouragement of self-confidence, spontaneity, curiosity and self-discipline that will assist the child's social and emotional health.
    Enhancement of the child's mental processes and skill, with particular attention to conceptual and communication skills.
    Establishment of patterns and expectations for success for the child that will create a climate of confidence for present and future learning efforts and overall development.
    Enhancement of the ability of the child and the family to relate to one another and to others.
    Development of a sense of dignity and self-worth within the child and his family.
business hours: 8:30 am to 4:30 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Preschool for Creative Beginnings
details: Preschool for Creative Beginnings is devoted to facilitating the development of social awareness, the identification of individual learning styles, and the encouragement of emerging curiosity in the lives of 3, 4 and 5 year old children. Our students are introduced to Spanish, yoga, the world of music, art and great artists, science, global skills, and, of course, reading, math and writing readiness. Creative Beginnings preschoolers learn our curriculum while playing and exploring at their own level and ability. We celebrate the diversity, growth and talents of each of our children.

name: Pakachoag Acres Day Care Center, Inc.
Mill Brook Country Day School, Inc.
Pilgrim Child Care & Preschool
details: The Pilgrim Child Care and Preschool (PCCP), is a non-profit organization created to serve the community with care and education for infants, toddlers, preschool, and Kindergarten children. The PCCP upholds a State license for ages two months - seven years and a school age license for up to age nine. The Center accepts applications from all families regardless of one’s race, religion, cultural heritage, political belief, marital status, sexual orientation, national origin, or disability. The Center does not use ‘toilet training’ status as a criterion of admission. Faculty are trained in the National Association for the Education of Young Children’s (NAEYC’s) Code of Ethical Conduct and Statement of Commitment including but not limited to appreciating childhood as a uniquely valuable stage of human development.

name: TSC Tot Child Care Center
details: The Center is committed to creating and sustaining a nurturing home like environment for children and parents. Teachers encourage cooperation, respect, and individuality. A desire for learning through age appropriate curriculum provides children with a variety of rich opportunities for growth in social, emotional, physical and cognitive development. The Center encourages parent involvement through a variety of classroom opportunities, newsletters, e-mail notices, family events and suggestions; supporting working parents by offering consistent high quality childcare.
business hours: Monday through Friday, 7:30 AM to 5:45 PM

name: Make Way for Ducklings Nursery School
details:
PHILOSOPHY: M.W.F.D. philosophy is to foster each child’s development to his or her full potential: cognitively, emotionally, physically and socially.  This goal is accomplished by providing a warm and stimulating environment in which children can learn and grow.  At M.W.F.D. children are helped to build self-esteem, to exercise self-control, and to learn to interact with their peers and teachers, as individuals and in-group situations.  Hands-on experiences are provided in and out of the classroom.  The enriched curriculum includes field trips and special programming in the areas of physical education and music.  Areas covered in the curriculum are outlined in the progress reports.

Make Way for Ducklings has set Goals, Objectives and Standards as guides in working with young children and their families.  At your visit you will be introduced to our guidelines and upon enrollment you will receive a copy of  M.W.F.D. Parent Handbook which includes our policies, procedure, standards, goals and objectives.

name: Wellesley Community Children's Center - Bates School
details: The Wellesley Community Children’s Center is a private, non-profit corporation, operated by a Board of Directors, administrative staff, and professional teaching staff. In 1971, WCCC began by enrolling preschoolers and kindergartners. We now serve more than 400 children from infancy through middle school in our Early Childhood and After School Programs.
