name: Weston Wing
details:
Weston Wing is a non-profit preschool and childcare program conveniently located on North Ave (Route 117), yet nestled on a vast treed lot. The building has six large, bright classrooms, and the half acre playground was specifically designed for children with a sandlot, climbing structure, swings, sledding hill, and paved bike yard.

Weston Wing is licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care (DEEC).  We are staffed by educated and nurturing teachers who are certified by the DEEC. They participate in ongoing professional development to strengthen their knowledge base and stay abreast of the latest research and education practices. In collaboration with parents, our teachers dedicate themselves to providing an environment where children can become the best that they can be.

Weston Wing offers flexible schedules for morning or full time care. We have younger and older toddler, preschool and pre-k classrooms. At Weston Wing, your child can develop in an environment that is safe, nurturing and responsive to your family’s needs.

name: MOC Child Care & Head Start Services / Coleman Street
details: MOC’s Child Care & Head Start (CCHS) provides early education and care and prepares children and families for appropriate growth, development, and school readiness through comprehensive, family-centered services. CCHS supports the success of both parents and children by offering quality center-based and family child care home-based services to area low-income families with children from birth to twelve years of age. Centers are located in Fitchburg, Leominster, Clinton, Gardner, Winchendon, and Athol and at Mount Wachusett Community College.  Family Child Care homes are located throughout MOC’s service area.

name: Pattikakes' A Place to Grow
details:
Pattikakes' is a privately owned child care center located on the Campus of the Tewksbury Hospital.  Pattikakes' offers quality child care services to the employees of the hospital, to those who are employed elsewhere on Campus, and to those in the community.  Pattikakes' serves families with children 6 weeks to 8 years old. 

Children have the opportunity to enjoy the beautiful and expansive grounds of the Tewksbury Hospital Campus throughout the year; with walks, outdoor time in our enclosed playground and hours of fun in any one of the many large open areas.

name: N.I.C.E. Inc.
details:
N.I.C.E., Inc. was founded by parents of the Roxbury/Jamaica Plain community to address their child care needs.  They decided to start their own childcare program.  These moms created Neighborhood Involvement for Children’s Education.  After moving from temporary space, they opened a center for 50 preschoolers in 1973, at 3297 Washington Street behind Brookside clinic.

N.I.C.E. first became accredited from the National Academy of Early Childhood Programs (N.A.E.Y.C.) in 1995.  Going beyond minimum licensing standards, accredited programs make a commitment to excellence.  N.I.C.E. renovated an abandoned building near Egleston Square.  The space, designed specifically for children, welcomed the relocation of N.I.C.E. in 1999.

N.I.C.E. is a multicultural/bilingual early education center, which fosters children’s self-esteem and provides a stimulating environment where each child can develop cognitively, physically, emotionally and socially at his or her own pace.

name: W. Roxbury/Roslindale YMCA @ Oakdale
details: Parents love YMCA After School, our family-centered program that nurtures the whole child by inspiring academic success, healthy movement and social and emotional development. Our staff of caring, trained educators are role models who lead activities that promote cooperation and character development. Parents can be productive at work knowing their children are in a safe and stimulating after school environment.

name: Ryan Road Before School Care and After School Care
details:
The Ryan Road Elementary School is a neighborhood school in Florence, Massachusetts with approximately 250 students in grades K-5. We are part of the Northampton Public Schools. We are committed to meeting the needs of all learners. We are a friendly and collaborative school community, and we hope all feel welcome and valued here.

The entire staff is trained in Responsive Classroom techniques, and we all work hard to address the academic, emotional, and behavioral needs of our students.  We value cross grade cooperation and have reading/recess buddies in grades K/4 and 1/5. We are always pleased with the caring relationships that develop through this practice.

We have monthly all-school celebrations so that we can celebrate the start of new seasons and what we value as a school community. We like to remind everyone that our school C.A.R.E.S. This acronym represents our values of:

C—Cooperation

A—Assertion

R—Responsibility

E—Empathy

S—Self-Control

name: Medway Extended Day, Inc.
details:
Medway Extended Day, Inc. (MEDI), a private, non-profit before- and after-school program, is an innovative child care alternative. MEDI is fully licensed by the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care. School-aged children have the benefit of programs that emphasize cooperation, fun and respect in a safe and relaxing environment. Our well-trained, caring staff provide personal attention to give your children a home away from home during the out-of-school hours.
​
We offer fun and exciting activities to choose from including creative projects and sports. Daily choices include: clubs, arts and crafts, science, sports, dramatic play, outdoor time, snack, and quiet reading and play areas. In addition, we offer plenty of time for study and homework.

name: Twelfth Baptist Church After School Program
Olympic Taekwondo After School Program I
details:
Master Han's Olympic Taekwondo, is a martial arts school located in East Longmeadow, MA and at our newest location in Pittsfield, MA. 

    We strive to provide Traditional and Olympic style Taekwondo training -- training that teaches not only the body but more importantly the mind and the spirit to overcome all obstascles. Our unique martial arts program is specialized in teaching children, teens and adults alike. All ages and martial levels are welcome to join!

    If you want to relieve stress, build strength and flexibility, gain an attitude that gives you that air of confidence then this is for you, your child and/or teen! 

    Martial arts training is one of the best things you can do for yourself and your child both physically and mentally. 

    We offer martial arts training from an experienced staff of black belt masters' who will teach you the style and power of this ancient martial arts form - while increasing your self-confidence, concentration, focus and self-control. 

    We understand that martial arts can be intimidating, but all it takes is the willingness to try. Each class is meant to push your boundaries, but in a positive and progressive manner.
business hours:
Mon - Fri: 
4:30 pm - 8:30 pm
Sat: 
9:00 am - 1:00 pm

name: WCCCS Teen Care Program - Burncoat
details: The Wellesley Community Children’s Center is a private, non-profit corporation, operated by a Board of Directors, administrative staff, and professional teaching staff. In 1971, WCCC began by enrolling preschoolers and kindergartners. We now serve more than 400 children from infancy through middle school in our Early Childhood and After School Programs.

name: Old Colony Y - Plymouth South
details:
Before and After School Care is a great option for children of parents who need care which fits with both work and school schedules.  Children can choose from a wide variety of activities including arts & crafts, reading, sports, games, plus field trips, themed special events, team building activites, and more!
 
The Old Colony YMCA believes that each child is special, with his or her own personality, talents, and skills.  Our approach to child care reflects the YMCA's core values of caring, honesty, respect, and responsibility, as well as our commitment to building strong kids, strong families and strong communities.
 
We offer so many wonderful activities and programs - all in a safe, nuturing, developmentally appropriate environment!

name: Montessori Children's House of Southbridge, Inc.
details: In 1976, a group of parents, wanting a different education for their preschool children, decided to open a Montessori school.  Since that day, Montessori Children's House of Southbridge (MCHS) has successfully educated well over one thousand children, between the ages of 2.9 and 6, in the tri-community area.  Montessori Children's House of Southbridge (MCHS) strives to create an environment where academic excellence can be achieved within a community that promotes creativity and responsibility.   In the Montessori tradition, MCHS seeks to help each child discover their joy in learning as well as their place in the greater society by strengthening the bonds between the parents, children and staff of  MCHS.  The sense of family will become a stable base from which each child can explore themselves, their community and the world.

name: Waltham Family YMCA @ Stanley Elem.
details: Parents love YMCA After School, our family-centered program that nurtures the whole child by inspiring academic success, healthy movement and social and emotional development. Our staff of caring, trained educators are role models who lead activities that promote cooperation and character development. name: Palmer Head Start
details:
Our MISSION
Holyoke • Chicopee • Springfield Head Start, Inc. is committed to providing low-income children and their families with a Beacon of Hope and source of support for a brighter future. We strive to do so by providing high quality comprehensive child development services to enrolled children and empowering families to achieve stability in their home environment.

Our CORE VALUES
Excellence • Respect • Diversity • Communication Team Work • Flexibility • Dedication • Shared Vision

Our HISTORY
Since 1965 HCS Head Start Inc. has been providing high-quality early childhood education services for children and families in cities and towns located in Western Massachusetts, including Holyoke, Chicopee, Springfield, Ludlow, Palmer, and Granby. Head Start provides a solid foundation for children to gain necessary skills to enter kindergarten and to be successful in life. Our centers are fully licensed by the MA Department of Early Education and Care. For a complete list of the cities and towns we serve, contact us at (413)788-6522.

name: Totland College Nursery School
details:
The purpose of Totland College is to provide the best possible non-profit nursery school for the children of the Union Congregational Church parish and the surrounding neighborhoods.  Totland College does not discriminate in providing services to children and their families on the basis of race, religion, cultural heritage, national origin, political belief, toileting issues, marital status, sexual orientation or disability.  Totland will accept applications for children with disabilities and will work with parents in trying to accommodate their children according to state regulations. Toileting status is not an enrollment criteria.

Totland College accepts children from ages 3 to kindergarten.  We have a 2 and 3-day preschool program.  We begin registration in January.  There is a $30.00 non-refundable registration fee to hold the student’s place.  We have an Open House in the spring for the parents and children and a Parent/Teacher/Child Orientation before school starts in September. At this meeting, you get to meet the teachers, see your child’s classroom and ask any questions you might have.

business hours: 8:30 am to 4:30 pm, Monday through Friday

name: Self Help Inc, Head Start - Whitman
details:
The Head Start Program is based on the premise that all children share certain needs and that children of low income families, in particular, can benefit from a comprehensive developmental program to meet those needs. The Head Start approach make the following assumptions:

A child can benefit from a comprehensive, interdisciplinary program to foster development.

Because the family is the principal influence on the child's development, the child's family, as well as the community, must be involved in the program.

The overall goal of the Head Start Program is to bring about a greater degree of social competence in children of low-income families. Social competence means the child's everyday effectiveness in dealing with both the present environment and later responsibilities in school and in life. Social competence takes into account the interrelatedness of cognitive and intellectual development, physical and mental health,nutritional needs as well as other factors. To achieve social competence, Head Start objectives and performance standards provide for:

    Improvement of the child's health and physical abilities, including appropriate steps to correct physical and mental health problems and to enhance every child's access to an adequate diet.
    Improvement of the family's attitude toward future health care and physical abilities.
    Encouragement of self-confidence, spontaneity, curiosity and self-discipline that will assist the child's social and emotional health.
    Enhancement of the child's mental processes and skill, with particular attention to conceptual and communication skills.
    Establishment of patterns and expectations for success for the child that will create a climate of confidence for present and future learning efforts and overall development.
    Enhancement of the ability of the child and the family to relate to one another and to others.
    Development of a sense of dignity and self-worth within the child and his family.
business hours: 8:30 am to 4:30 pm, Monday through Friday

name: South Boston Head Start
details: ABCD provides innovative, timely programs that promote upward mobility and a higher quality of life for people and communities. Empowering people by providing them with the tools to overcome poverty, live with dignity & achieve their full potential. ABCD responds to the needs of our community through our decentralized, city-wide network, which includes 14 unique neighborhood centers.

name: Sturbridge Nursery School
details:
At The Sturbridge Cooperative Nursery School we help our preschool children learn to work and play with other children, give them the opportunity to work and play with different equipment and toys, and foster growth and independence in each child, while promoting healthy habits that prepare them for kindergarten.

We are a non profit cooperative school where parent involvement is crucial to our success.  Our nursery school is based on a parent-participatory model.  All parents are expected to volunteer, or "co-op," in the classroom for at least two weeks during the school year, participate on a board or commitee which includes various fundraisers, and maintain the building and school grounds throughout the year.  This greater involvement allows parents to share in and add
to their child’s preschool experience and allows the children to see that their education is an important part of family life.

 The School's Board of Directors, comprised of current member parents, conducts monthly parent meetings, maintains and distributes documents to the families of the School, including the School's Handbook, financial status, current enrollment roster, and a current set of Bylaws.

name: World Tae Kwon Do Training Center After School Program
details:
The World Tae Kwon Do Training Center will provide a safe and nurturing environment in which students respect and appreciate each other while training together regardless of race, nationality, or religion.  Our students learn and grow intellectually, physically, and emotionally through developmentally appropriate lessons.

An important quality of our programs is the ability to maintain active, open and informative communication between students, parents, and staff.  We will provide parents with notices and/or calendars of upcoming special events, and other pertinent information.

We encourage all students to speak with the instructors if any problems/schedule changes (i.e., illness, appointments, etc.) should arise.  It is especially helpful if there are any significant events taking place in the student¡Ë¢ç?s life (positive or not) that our staff/director is informed so we may respond appropriately to the student¡Ë¢ç?s needs.

name: Mansfield Children's Center Inc
details:
35 years ago our Directors, each of whom was successful in related fields, chose to design and develop a learning environment for children that was unique.

 We worked to create an alternative to generic corporate child care chains by building a non-profit center in Mansfield, Massachusetts that was engaging indoors, spaciously natural outdoors, and child-nourishing throughout.  We were committed to developing a rich curriculum that brought out the social, emotional, creative, intellectual, and physical capacities of each child.

 We have been fortunate to bring together a core of caring and highly motivated people who have helped us make our commitment become a reality.

 Explore our program here and now and come to visit our 2 1/2 acre campus at your leisure.

name: YMCA Schools Out @ Quarry Hill
details:
The YMCA of Greater Springfield provides a safe, fun environment for children to continue learning and developing during out-of-school periods. During Before-School programs, the YMCA provides a safe environment for children from 6:30am until the start of the school day.Breakfast is provided and children can choose from a variety of activities. 

During After-School programs, we provide snack and homework assistance.  We also provide age appropriate activities each day, including sports, outdoor play, arts and crafts, science, cooking, story time, and much more. This program begins at the end of the full school day and runs until 6:00pm.
- See more at: http://www.springfieldy.org/our-focus/for-youth-development/early-education-school-age-care/school-age/scantic-schools-out-program/#sthash.wZPS5Ajt.dpuf

name: SMOC Head Start Medway
details: Head Start provides comprehensive early education and support services for children ages three to five and their families. In addition to providing center-based and home-based preschool education, the program provides supportive services in the areas of health and dental care, nutrition, special education, parent skill workshops and social services. Children are provided with a daily lunch and breakfast or snack, which meet all federal, and state nutrition guidelines. Door-to-door transportation is provided at many of the centers. Classrooms typically operate from September through May, Mondays through Fridays and from 8:30am to 2pm.

name: Wellesley Community Children's Center-Sprague
details: The Wellesley Community Children’s Center is a private, non-profit corporation, operated by a Board of Directors, administrative staff, and professional teaching staff. In 1971, WCCC began by enrolling preschoolers and kindergartners. We now serve more than 400 children from infancy through middle school in our Early Childhood and After School Programs.

name: Rainbow Child Development School Age Ctr
details:
Rainbow Child Development Center’ school-age program services children between the ages of 5 and 13 years old.  

Our School Age Program collaborates with nine Worcester Schools to offer well over 100 children affordable after-school programs. The program focuses on providing an enriched, stimulating curriculum with a heavy emphasis on homework, academic assistance, enrichment activities, and physical exercise from the close of school until 5:30 pm Monday through Friday and school vacation weeks.
business hours: close of school until 5:30 pm Monday through Friday

name: South Shore Charter After School Program
details:
Our Norwell Afterschool Programs include before and after school care for students grades K through 6 at Vinal Elementary School and Cole Elementary School as well as an after school program for students at South Shore Charter Public School.
Our Scituate programs include before and after school care for students at Cushing Elementary School, Hatherly Elementary School, Jenkins Elementary School and Wampatuck Elementary School.

name: Mini's & Wynnie's Day Care
details:
Mini's And Wynnie's Day & Night Care LLC provides a year-round, full day educational child development program for children ages 2 months to 14 years. Our goal is to work with parents, the community, and our staff to offer a comprehensive program that will ensure enrichment in the lives of children and their families.
 
The program operates on the premise that each child is unique, and each child has individual needs that must be met, always considering their diverse ethnic, social and economic backgrounds.
 
Mini's And Wynnie's offers learning opportunities for children and parents in all areas that foster social, emotional, physical, and intellectual development. These educational areas are education, health, nutrition, special needs, social service, and parent education.
 
It is our philosophy that all children and families (regardless of race, religion, cultural heritage, political beliefs, marital status, income, national origin, sexual orientation, or disability), have the right to engage in learning opportunities designed to empower them to grow to their full potential.

name: Winn Brook PTA Child Care Programs
details:
Winn Brook Child Care (WBCC) provides high quality before- and after-school programming for children in the Winn Brook School population, kindergarten through fourth grade. If additional spaces in the program remain, they will be open to children of the same age group within the Winn Brook district, as well as other Belmont elementary schools. WBCC offers supervised and staff-directed activities that aim to enhance children’s educational, social physical and emotional development.

The philosophy of the program dictates that the needs of the children come first, but that the special circumstances of parents/families using the program are also considered.  It is a goal of the program to treat each child individually, so long as the accommodation of individual needs can be accomplished without harm to the overall health of the program. WBCC recognizes the various needs of children of different ages and stages of development and uses those variations as the basis for the program’s curriculum.

name: Stepping Stones Nursery School
details: Stepping Stones has a 2-day program for children ages 2.9 to 4 years old. Your child must be two years nine months old on or before September 1st of the year they attend. Stepping Stones also offers a 3-day program for 3.9 to 5 year olds. Your child must be three years nine months old on or before September 1st of the year they attend. You may choose to attend the morning or afternoon session. STEPPING STONES PRE-SCHOOL is a nonprofit, non-denominational preschool for children ages 2.9 to 5 years old, sponsored by All Saints Episcopal Church of the North Shore. We meet every Monday through Friday in the Preschool Classroom of the Parish House, behind the Big RED door. In addition to our regular programs, we offer an EXTENDED DAY ENRICHMENT PROGRAM until 2 pm., Monday through Friday, in our 2, 3 and 5 Day programs. Our Extended Day Enrichment Program activities includes lunch, indoor and outdoor play, cooking project, science experiments and literacy fun!

name: Old Colony Y/Dighton
details:
Before and After School Care is a great option for children of parents who need care which fits with both work and school schedules.  Children can choose from a wide variety of activities including arts & crafts, reading, sports, games, plus field trips, themed special events, team building activites, and more!
 
The Old Colony YMCA believes that each child is special, with his or her own personality, talents, and skills.  Our approach to child care reflects the YMCA's core values of caring, honesty, respect, and responsibility, as well as our commitment to building strong kids, strong families and strong communities.
 
We offer so many wonderful activities and programs - all in a safe, nuturing, developmentally appropriate environment!

name: Parkway Preschool Center
details:
Our early childhood professionals are ready to meet the needs of young children.  
The school strives to create an atmosphere that is joyful, friendly, caring, creative, enthusiastic and most of all fun.  
It is most important to all of us at Parkway Preschool that we continue to inspire, stimulate interest and provide learning opportunities for each and every child in an accepting and loving environment.  
The concept of excellence is deeply embedded in our philosophy of caring and educating the young.

name: Olson Nursery School
details:
Olson Nursery School is a preschool serving children, ages 2.9 yrs old to 5 yrs old.

We offer two class options: Tuesday and Thursday classes 9:00am -11:50 am for the 2.9- 4yrolds.
Monday, Wednesday and Friday classes for 3 1/2 – 5  year olds

We are open during the Public School schedule. WIth the exception of opening and closing dates. We open the first full week after Labor Day and close the week before Memorial day.

Our goal is to prepare children with the necessary skills they will need to attend Kindergarten. In a safe and nurturing environment. Our belief is that there is nothing so important to stress a preschooler over. We pay attention to individual needs, and learning styles, incorporating into our curriculum the various learning styles, adapting to the needs of each child.

name: Riverview Preschool
details:
Our goal at Riverview Preschool is to provide a warm, safe, and nurturing environment where children can grow and learn while having fun. We provide opportunities to enhance the social, emotional, cognitive, and physical skills of your child, for future experiences. At the Riverview Preschool, we know that children grow and learn at their own pace. Therefore, we provide enriching activities that will challenge children in areas that strengthen and enhance their abilities and skills and to develop a positive self-image.

We promote the child’s creativity, trust, curiosity, independence, self-confidence, self-control, adaptability, cooperation, verbal ability, physical, intellectual awareness, and the acceptance of others. We also provide opportunities for the children to explore and learn about the world around them through topics that are of interest to them.

We welcome children 2.9 to 7 years old and have a low teacher to child ratio of 1/6. For your convenience, we offer several payment plans. Annual, semi-annual, monthly, and weekly tuition. Tours of our facility are available by appointment at 978-282-1910.

name: Purpose School
details:
During the early 1940's, Reverend Mark Strickland had a dream of providing a community service for mothers who were busy working in the defense industry or volunteering in the war effort. In September of 1943 that dream became a reality. In 1962 the addition that now contains Purpose School was built. Because of the dedication of teachers and directors that dream continues to be fulfilled some 65 years later.

​The goals of Purpose School have remained the same over the years. In 1955, director Mrs. Morrill pointed out the necessity of focusing on the development of the whole child - physical, emotional, social and cognitive. She described the preschool age child as follows: "He is acquiring a great mass of information, broadening his range of interest, improving his skills and learning the techniques of solving problems. The Purpose School program offers a broad preparatory program to develop readiness for learning. This program affords children a natural opportunity for language development, manipulating materials, sensing meanings and relationships, developing work habits and attending social maturity. The teachers help the children learn to work and play together."

Ultimately the success of a preschool program depends on the relationship between teachers, children and parents - teachers who love what they do, children who thrive in a nurturing and caring atmosphere and parents who appreciate and encourage their children's growth. We are proud to offer that special relationship still today.

name: Madison Avenue Headstart/HCS Headstart
details:
Our MISSION
Holyoke • Chicopee • Springfield Head Start, Inc. is committed to providing low-income children and their families with a Beacon of Hope and source of support for a brighter future. We strive to do so by providing high quality comprehensive child development services to enrolled children and empowering families to achieve stability in their home environment.

Our CORE VALUES
Excellence • Respect • Diversity • Communication Team Work • Flexibility • Dedication • Shared Vision

Our HISTORY
Since 1965 HCS Head Start Inc. has been providing high-quality early childhood education services for children and families in cities and towns located in Western Massachusetts, including Holyoke, Chicopee, Springfield, Ludlow, Palmer, and Granby. Head Start provides a solid foundation for children to gain necessary skills to enter kindergarten and to be successful in life. Our centers are fully licensed by the MA Department of Early Education and Care. For a complete list of the cities and towns we serve, contact us at (413)788-6522.

name: Winthrop Country Day Learning Center
details:

Established in 1947 — Become part of the "Tradition."

name: NorthStar Learning Centers, Inc.
details: Born from local community action during the civil rights movement, NorthStar Learning Centers remains grounded in our original vision to provide individualized, strength-based, family-focused programs that "help children, youth, and families realize their strengths and dreams." Founded in 1974, we have grown from one neighborhood-based preschool center to a constellation of programs that serve New Bedford area children from birth to adulthood. In all our programs, we are committed to serving the underserved and reaching the " hard-to-reach."

name: Young Parents Learning Center-Durfee High School
Wellfleet Montessori Preschool

The Wellfleet Montessori Preschool was established in 1976 by a group of local mothers to provide a supervised environment for preschool children on the lower cape. Over the years the school has evolved from a playgroup to a certified Montessori preschool, run jointly by the parent members and salaried teachers.

The Wellfleet Montessori Preschool’s mission is to celebrate and foster the natural curiosity and potential of the individual child within a learning environment that invites children to discover and recognize the unique gifts and interests of self and others. Through deliberate modeling of respect, kindness and responsibility, we guide children toward confidence in their local and global community.

details:

Children in this age group are unique and interesting, and it is our goal to help foster each child's growth. Our staff members take into consideration the mood of the group and act accordingly. Flexibility is a must.

name: Methodist Weekday School
details:
As a private, non-profit, non-sectarian preschool we strive to offer excellent teaching, facilities, and programs to children of all cultures, faiths, and walks of life.

MWS is a happy manageable place away from home. Our caring teachers provide hands-on experiences and positive feedback to stimulate social, emotional, physical, and intellectual growth. As children enjoy what’s familiar and master what’s difficult, they gain confidence in their ability to succeed in school.

We  believe all children are on a predictable path of development and that they reveal their individual strengths, personalities and preferences as they explore the world around them. By offering a broad variety of experiences, we help them establish the skills and self-control they need to work and play effectively with others. Above all else, we make sure school is an exciting and fun place to be, so each child develops a life-long love of learning.

We enroll 115 children from Lexington, Bedford, other nearby communities, and even other countries. Our students range in age from 2 years nine months to 5+ years old.  They enter school in various stages of motor, social and language development–including some who speak little or no English. Whether they enter speaking American English, Russian, Mandarin, Korean, Dutch, or Farsi, our students are all fluent in the universal language of play, movement, and laughter. We welcome the wonderful variety of students and parents; they enrich our school life on a daily basis.

name: Old Deerfield Nursery School
details: Welcome to the Old Deerfield Nursery School, a nonprofit half-day program for preschool children (2.9 – 5  years old). We build a warm and nurturing environment in which your child can learn and work with others. We offer a professionally designed, thematic curriculum; complete with lesson plans, assessments, progress reports, portfolios and newsletters for parents to use as a guide. Our classroom is organized into “learning environments” where children learn through hands on play and structured activities.  Within the classroom, children can find the toys and materials related by theme, interest, and skills.  Activities and toys can be used independently by the children, or with teacher direction, to reinforce and enrich skills and concepts. Learning environments are an excellent way to individualize the curriculum to meet the varying needs of young children. ODNS is open to all families who may benefit from our type of program regardless of race, religion, cultural heritage, national origin, political beliefs, marital status, sexual orientation, or disability. Our school is located in the beautiful village of Historic Deerfield, at the corner of Main Street and Memorial Street.

name: MOC Child Care & Head Start Service / Clinton
details: MOC’s Child Care & Head Start (CCHS) provides early education and care and prepares children and families for appropriate growth, development, and school readiness through comprehensive, family-centered services. CCHS supports the success of both parents and children by offering quality center-based and family child care home-based services to area low-income families with children from birth to twelve years of age. Centers are located in Fitchburg, Leominster, Clinton, Gardner, Winchendon, and Athol and at Mount Wachusett Community College.  Family Child Care homes are located throughout MOC’s service area.

name: Watertown Cooperative Nursery School
details: WCNS was created in 1952 by a group of parents who envisioned a nursery school where their children would feel comfortable and cared for, where friendships could grow, and where positive reinforcement would be a constant.  We serve children and families in Watertown, Belmont, Cambridge, Waltham and Newton.  At WCNS our goal is to help children feel good about themselves and their accomplishments.  We encourage individual creativity, group participation, and problem solving in everything we do.  Our curriculum encourages healthy social, physical, and cognitive skills, but is first and foremost designed for fun.  A cooperative spirit underlies all aspects of WCNS, and the resulting sense of community is priceless.

name: Mittineague Methodist Community Preschool
details:
The primary purpose of Mittineague Methodist Community Preschool is to serve the children and families of the community by providing a safe and supportive environment for young children between the ages of 2.9 and 5. The activities and materials offered are specifically selected to promote all aspects of preschooler's growth;emotional, social, physical and intellectual.

 Our approach is positive and our hope is to give each child the clear message "I am lovable and capable".

name: Medfield Afterschool Program, Inc.
details:
MAP is a parent based non-profit program that was established 25 years ago to provide quality care to children enrolled in the Medfield Public Schools.  MAP is fully licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care and provides care for children in Kindergarten through 6th grade. 

Since the afterschool period represents a major portion of a child's free time, MAP is designed to provide a less structured environment than a regular school day.  MAP offers various enrichment activities to enhance children’s interest, talents, and values.  The program fosters each child’s need for relaxation, quiet time, an environment for homework, and a supportive atmosphere.

 MAP currently services over 300 children at three different sites. 

At Memorial, our modular classroom  provides programming for children that are 4 and 5 years of age but not enrolled in kindergarten from 9:30-2:30 with a half day option and kindergarten children from 8:00 a.m. until 6:00 p.m. Kindergarten children may sign up for different sessions and programs depending on their schedules (morning K, afternoon K, or full day K)  and the 1st graders join them at 2:40. 

To find out more about our Jump Start or Kindergarten programs, please go to our Jump Start page
for children that are 4 and 5 but not yet in school or our Kindergarten page for children enrolled in kindergarten in the Medfield Public schools.

Have a first grader, check out all the fun activities by going to our K-1st grade program page!

At the Wheelock School modular, we offer programming for the 2nd and 3rd graders.  Go to our 2nd and 3rd grade page to see more!

name: P.A.C.E. Head Start
details:
Our mission at P.A.C.E. Head Start is to provide a family centered child development program for eligible children in the Greater New Bedford area. Families are empowered through a range of services which include:

~ an early education experience which builds upon a child’s strengths and engages parents as partners ~
~ child care options that address the diverse needs of families ~
~ meaningful parent involvement opportunities ~
~ advocacy to overcome obstacles and improve quality of life ~
~ collaborations with community agencies ~

Services are provided in an environment that promotes respect, fosters inclusion and celebrates diversity among children, families and staff.

name: Teddy Bear Learning and Daycare Ctr
details: Teddybear Learning & Daycare Center has been in operation since 1988. Our school has organized classrooms with centers for creative art, literature, science, pre-math, and dramatic play in order to promote cognitive and small motor development. Our professional staff is kind, caring, and committed to working closely with families. In fact, we keep the welfare of every child at the top of our priority list and work endlessly to help children grow. At Teddybear Learning & Daycare Center, we understand that the right environment is important for the growth and development of children. Our teachers are mothers and grandmothers who know how to maintain a home-like environment to help all students feel comfortable and ready to learn.

name: The Natick Montessori School
details: The Riverbend School is a collaborative Montessori environment that develops self-motivated, independent learners by integrating academic excellence and a respectful social community that results in confidence and lifelong achievement.  At Riverbend, our innovative approach encourages students to explore their talents with confidence, strive for achievement and discover new ways of thinking, all in an environment founded on respect and collaboration.

name: Old Colony Y-West Elementary
details:

name: Melrose Montessori School
details: We strive to offer children of the community an educational experience that puts into practice the profound observations and principles of Dr. Maria Montessori. The Montessori program is characterized by order, structure and comprehensiveness, based on the physiological needs of the child; incorporating reality based activities designed to assist the child in the development of all areas of learning at the child’s personal ability level and at the child’s own pace. The goal of our program is to develop each child’s independent physical, emotional and intellectual functioning to his maximum potential through the exciting process of exploration and discovery.

name: Woodside Montessori Academy
details:
Woodside Montessori Academy offers the full Montessori educational experience, educating students from three years old through eighth grade. Our school offers a challenging and stimulating academic environment where students are guided by faculty members who are knowledgeable, dedicated, and caring. Our in-school academic atmosphere is complemented by the wide variety of real life experiences.

Based largely on Dr. Maria Montessori’s ideals and teachings, our program reflects a love and respect for each student. It is completely student-centered, with a commitment to the success and happiness of each of our students.

name: The Wonder Years Learning Center
details: The Wonder Years Learning Center offers children of all ages an environment in which they can explore, play, create, and learn at their own pace. Far beyond providing basic daycare services, our philosophy is based upon the developmentally appropriate practice guidelines.

name: WCCCS South High Teen Parent Program
details: The Wellesley Community Children’s Center is a private, non-profit corporation, operated by a Board of Directors, administrative staff, and professional teaching staff. In 1971, WCCC began by enrolling preschoolers and kindergartners. We now serve more than 400 children from infancy through middle school in our Early Childhood and After School Programs.

name: Russell Cooperative Preschool
details: Russell Cooperative Preschool is a parent cooperative preschool located in Watertown Square. Russell offers a play-based curriculum, a high adult-to-child ratio, sunny and spacious classrooms, an experienced and committed staff, and a community of involved parents.

name: Radcliffe Child Care Center
details:
Celebrating 40 years in the community, Radcliffe Child Care Center is located in the Heart of Harvard Square, steps from the Charles River. Through our well-trained staff, we offer high-quality group care and education on a fee basis for children 3 months old through 5 years of age.

RCCC, Inc. is a non-profit organization dedicated to providing care to families of Harvard University Faculty and Staff, as well as families within the community. Since 2002 we have been accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children, a true benchmark of quality facilities.

name: Spring Street Preschool
details: Founded in 1959, Spring Street 2011-2012_class_photos_012Preschool sits in the heart of Amherst.  We enroll children ages 2 years, 9 months to 5 years old. As a not-for-profit organization, the preschool is overseen by an active Parent Board. We support families and welcome all family members.  Families are encouraged to participate in all school functions, fund-raising events, and classroom activities.  We also celebrate the diversity of all our families and welcome families of all ethnic, racial, and socioeconomic backgrounds. Spring Street Preschool is licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care.

name: South Shore Head Start & Child Care-Plymouth
The Steeple School of Trinity Church
details:
The Steeple School of Trinity Church began in 1963 by the people of Trinity Church in Marshfield Hills to try to fulfill a real community need for a kindergarten/nursery school. At that time there was no public kindergarten and only a few private preschools in Marshfield and the surrounding towns.

In the beginning there was one kindergarten and one nursery class, staffed by a teacher and a rotating roster of volunteer assistant teachers, one for each day of the week. The total enrollment was 30 children.

A Board of Directors was established to administer the school, which was located in Johnson Hall. Equipment was either made or donated. By 1969 the present school building with six classrooms was built.

At that time, Steeple School enrolled about 250 children, from three to five years of age. The staff was professional and salaried with a teacher and assistant teacher for each class. Enrollment reached 275 children in 1972, the year before public kindergarten was instituted in Marshfield.

In the years following, one classroom was changed into a specialized room for large motor skill development. A drop-in babysitting program was also established for those who needed occasional child care in the afternoons.

Today Steeple School of Trinity Church continues to provide a quality preschool program for children of Marshfield and surrounding towns. Steeple School enrolls children in three programs: Playgroup, Nursery, and Pre-Kindergarten. It also offers an ExtendedCare Program each afternoon.

name: Salem Community Child Care
details:
Advantages of Our Centers
Our child to teacher ratio is as low as 1:7, so your child will always receive personal and individual attention.
All of our teachers are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children, and we thoroughly follow Massachusetts state guidelines for child education and care.
We also make sure to keep our prices low while never sacrificing high-quality, professional care, so both your finances and your mind can rest easy.

Our History
Owner Christin Hatch has 36 years of experience in child care and education. She started her business as a private non-profit with a parent board of directors, who demanded a child care center with high standards.

name: Marblehead Children's Center
details: The purpose of Marblehead Children's Center is to provide activities which help children to learn at their own growth rate in an informal and flexible program aimed at the needs of the individual child.

name: Skribbles Learning Center
details: Skribbles was founded in 1992 and began as a Family Daycare Home, Skribbles Family Daycare. The program was run by Tara Rogers, DEEC qualified Director II. Tara and her sister Juliane Blackmore, BA in accounting, have always thought of opening a business together by combining Tara's child care knowledge and Julie's business background. After 10 successful years and the caring of over 100 children in the home, Tara and Julie finally teamed up to expand the program for more children in the community. Skribbles Learning Center opened in February, 2003. In 2007, we had another growth and opened a second location in Northboro. Skribbles is family owned and operated. We are proud of our facility and are always striving to make Skribbles the best that it can be. We are licensed by the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care (DEEC) and have received the prestigious award of becoming NAEYC accredited in April 2006. The Center is open 52 weeks per year to accommodate working families. Our goal is to maintain a highly qualified staff and to offer your children the best environment during the early years of their lives.   At Skribbles Learning Center, we believe that children learn through playing. Playing is a tough job, but somebody has to do it. Through play, your child will have the opportunity to learn and explore with the many offered materials and equipment. Each child will develop at their own pace and will have the freedom to express their independence. We believe that it is the process of learning that is important and not the final product. Each child will be treated as an individual for the special person that they are. While your children are in our care, we promise to love, nurture and support their development. We will encourage each child to be the best that he/she can be and we will enhance their social, emotional, physical and cognitive development. Our mission is to provide families with the high quality care that is needed, along with offering the children a happy, safe and fun learning environment.

name: Y's Kids-Southampton Road
details:
The YMCA of Greater Westfield offers a variety of child care programs; Preschool and Before and After School Care. All of our child care is state certified.

Visit our welcome desk to register for the Y’s Kids State Licensed Before & After School Care registration for the ongoing school year!

Our Before School program runs from 7:00AM-9:00AM and includes games, sports, arts and crafts, as well as homework help. Our After School program runs from 2:30PM-6:00PM and includes homework tutoring, STEAM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts and Math activities), sports,  cooking, games, arts & crafts and more!

Full day, half day, snow day and vacation day care is also available. Children currently enrolled in our Before and After School programs receive a discounted rate. Extended care, in the event of two hour school delays and early releases due to inclement weather, is also included in your weekly fee.

name: V. O. C. Child Care on Montgomery Street
details: VOC operates five childcare centers in Holyoke and Chicopee. Our goal is to assist parents who are working, in training leading to employment, or have other special needs. We provide a complete education program, meals, and opportunities for parent involvement.

name: Wellington Student Care Programs
details:
Our mission is to create a community in which our highest value is mutual respect. By accepting each child as a unique individual, we can help each child in turn to accept and get along with others. Our goal is for children in our programs to become comfortable socially as they develop competence and independence through discovery of their own capabilities.

Our staff of caring adult professionals provides positive role models for our children in responding to life’s daily realities, while emphasizing the norms of appropriate interpersonal behavior. In their interactions with the children, they seek to instill a sense of belonging, helpfulness, discovery, proficiency and leadership.

name: The Princeton Community Preschool
details:
The Princeton Community Preschool is a program sponsored by the First Congregational Church in Princeton. It was founded in 1990 and has operated continuously since then. It is located in the First Congregational Church on the second floor.

A Board of Directors governs the Preschool. The Board is comprised of nine members: the Preschool Director, a Church Council representative, a member from the church congregation, and parents and guardians of enrolled and alumni students.

The Preschool Board meets monthly. These are public forums and, as such, are open to the public. See the Director for a calendar of meetings.

name: Young World Academy, Inc.
details:
Young World Preschool & Daycare in Salem, MA offers enjoyable developmental programs for infants, toddlers, pre-K, and kindergarteners. With over 30 years of experience and our highly qualified staff, we are sure to provide the best care and programs that suit your child's developmental needs.

We daycare services available for infants along with stellar preschool and kindergarten programs – all at favorable rates and with flexible schedules.

name: Sunny Hill Preschool
details:
Sunny Hill Preschool was founded as a non-profit organization in 1958 by the Sudbury United Methodist Church, and we celebrated our fiftieth anniversary in 2008.  While the school is sponsored by the church, religion is not a part of the curriculum. The school offers a play-based program that combines preparation for kindergarten with an emphasis on a child’s social and emotional development. The focus of the programs at Sunny Hill Preschool is on the whole child’s social, emotional, cognitive and physical development. Teachers develop classroom themes and activities that integrate sensory experiences, pre-reading and pre-math concepts, science, social studies, art, social and self-help skills.

The mission of the school is to provide a high quality, affordable, nurturing and supportive early childhood learning environment to families in Sudbury and the surrounding communities.

As one of the very first programs in the Sudbury area, Sunny Hill Preschool serves as a model of excellence in early childhood education. The daily operations of the school are overseen by a full-time Director. An appointed committee of church members is responsible for policy making and various functions related to the operation of the school.

Our programs are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children, which sets professional standards for early education programs.

name: Little Prince and Princess Day School
Peoples Institute Child Care
details:
The People’s Institute has been a center for educational, recreational and social services for Northampton and surrounding communities for more than a hundred years. Over the last thirty, our focus has been on providing quality, affordable, childcare. Today we offer child care and educational options for children from fifteen months old through the eighth grade.

Our programs and staff are licensed/qualified by EEC (The Commonwealth of Massachusetts Department of Early Education and care). We are staffed by warm, caring, competent personnel who recognize the unique qualities of each child and support each child’s positive development of self-worth, self-esteem and learning.

name: Payson Park Nursery School
details:
Payson Park Nursery School (PPNS) is a nonsectarian, non-profit pre-school located on the first floor of Payson Park Church. PPNS has served Belmont and the surrounding communities for over 25 years.

Under the supervision of an experienced and qualified staff, the children at PPNS are encouraged to grow socially, emotionally, intellectually and physically in a balanced pre-school program that offers a comfortable transition from home to school.

A loving and stimulating learning environment is provided for the children at PPNS. They experience many areas of development. Free-play gives children an opportunity to socialize. Story time enriches listening skills. Music time gives children a sense of rhythm and an appreciation of songs. Activity time teaches children to follow and apply directions in a class setting. Large motor skills are developed through playtime either outside or in our indoor gymnasium.

name: Zervas After-School Program
details:
Welcome to the  Zervas After School Program,Inc. (ZASP) is commited to providing quality childcare for the children of the Newton. 

Our objective is to offer enriching, creative activities tha allow children to develop their social, emotional, physical cultural and academic skills.  The theme-based curriculum provides educaional and social experinces tha encourage children to develop thei own individual interests, self-confidence, independance and responsibilty.

Our longtime teachers and staff are dedicated to helping each child discover their unique potential – academically, socially, and interpersonally.

name: MOC Child Care & Head Start Services - Garrison Ctr. for ECE
details: MOC’s Child Care & Head Start (CCHS) provides early education and care and prepares children and families for appropriate growth, development, and school readiness through comprehensive, family-centered services. CCHS supports the success of both parents and children by offering quality center-based and family child care home-based services to area low-income families with children from birth to twelve years of age. Centers are located in Fitchburg, Leominster, Clinton, Gardner, Winchendon, and Athol and at Mount Wachusett Community College.  Family Child Care homes are located throughout MOC’s service area.

name: MOC Child Care & Head Start Services
details: MOC’s Child Care & Head Start (CCHS) provides early education and care and prepares children and families for appropriate growth, development, and school readiness through comprehensive, family-centered services. CCHS supports the success of both parents and children by offering quality center-based and family child care home-based services to area low-income families with children from birth to twelve years of age. Centers are located in Fitchburg, Leominster, Clinton, Gardner, Winchendon, and Athol and at Mount Wachusett Community College.  Family Child Care homes are located throughout MOC’s service area.

name: Springfield Boys & Girls Club School Age Prog.
Toddler Loving Care II, Inc.
details: TLC Nursery School consists of two small private schools. Our first location in Newton, MA has been in business for over 20 years. We have a second location in Wayland, MA. We offer Toddler, Preschool, Transitional Kindergarten and Kindergarten programs. Foreign language multiculturalism and personal celebrations are important components of our program.

name: Toepfert Head Start
details:
Our MISSION
Holyoke • Chicopee • Springfield Head Start, Inc. is committed to providing low-income children and their families with a Beacon of Hope and source of support for a brighter future. We strive to do so by providing high quality comprehensive child development services to enrolled children and empowering families to achieve stability in their home environment.

Our CORE VALUES
Excellence • Respect • Diversity • Communication Team Work • Flexibility • Dedication • Shared Vision

Our HISTORY
Since 1965 HCS Head Start Inc. has been providing high-quality early childhood education services for children and families in cities and towns located in Western Massachusetts, including Holyoke, Chicopee, Springfield, Ludlow, Palmer, and Granby. Head Start provides a solid foundation for children to gain necessary skills to enter kindergarten and to be successful in life. Our centers are fully licensed by the MA Department of Early Education and Care. For a complete list of the cities and towns we serve, contact us at (413)788-6522.

name: MOC Child Care & Head Start Services/School Age Program
details: MOC’s Child Care & Head Start (CCHS) provides early education and care and prepares children and families for appropriate growth, development, and school readiness through comprehensive, family-centered services. CCHS supports the success of both parents and children by offering quality center-based and family child care home-based services to area low-income families with children from birth to twelve years of age. Centers are located in Fitchburg, Leominster, Clinton, Gardner, Winchendon, and Athol and at Mount Wachusett Community College.  Family Child Care homes are located throughout MOC’s service area.

name: Tot-Spot at Landmark
details:
Tot Spot was developed by a group of parents who were teachers and administrators at Landmark School. Due to their research, dedication and hard work, Tot Spot opened during the summer of 1983 to provide Landmark employees with on-site childcare. Tot Spot later expanded to include community children in the program. Landmark’s commitment to Tot Spot has continued for over 29 years!

Tot Spot is also utilized by Landmark School as a practicum experience for students involved in the Early Childhood Education class. These are high school students who are interested in Early Childhood Education as a career. This program began in 1994 and has been very successful. Several students have gone on to be early childhood educators or in the early childhood and care field.

name: Precious Beginnings Preschool
details:
What makes Precious Beginnings so unique? At Precious Beginnings, we know every child is a special gift, and our goal is to nurture the unique spirit of each child while providing the best early education in a loving, safe environment where children can learn, grow and explore to enable them to reach their full potential.

Hands-on activities that are based on the knowledge of how children grow and what they can do, allowing children to grow socially, emotionally, cognitively, and physically.

name: Pelham After School Program
details: The Pelham After School Program strives to continue with the warm family atmosphere already established at Pelham School. Siblings and friends can play or work in a safe, supervised environment. Activities range from indoor to outdoor play, quiet or active projects, and a chance to be alone or in a group situation. There are opportunities for exploring creative materials, making decisions, accepting responsibility and learning cooperation. Most of the school’s facilities, as well as the community library, are also available to the program.

name: Little People's Playhouse
details:
While you are away, or at work, we strive to provide the best quality education and developmental programs for your child. Children are at a delicate time in their lives where they are set to learn new things, start meaningful social interactions with other children and begin their academic careers.

Put the emphasis on education and development – one child at a time.
    Music
    Arts and crafts
    Computer skills
    Learning tools

name: Ninth Street Day Nursery
details:
The Ninth street Day Nursery, Inc. functions as a day care and educational center. It is a United Way of Greater Fall River agency and operates under licensure from the Department of Early Education and Care. The school charges reasonable tuition on a sliding scale for the services rendered to the children.

Ninth Street Day Nursery, Inc. exists to help the parents in the Greater Fall River Community place their children of preschool age (2 years, 9 months - 6 years) in an environment conducive to happiness, good health, education, recreation, good citizenship, and a positive sense of self.

Ninth Street Day Nursery, Inc. is a charitable corporation established in 1956. It is a continuation of a Nursery project conceived in 1910 by a group of women from the American Association of University Women to care for children of working parents.

The purpose of the Ninth Street Day Nursery is to promote the health and welfare of enrolled children of the city of Fall River and surrounding communities. The Nursery School, founded in 1910, was relocated to its current location at 533 Highland Avenue in Fall River in 1974. In addition to its educational program, the school provides recreational facilities and healthy snacks as part of the school day.

The purposes of the school have expanded over the years to meet the social changes and requirements of the community by adding educational facilities and expanding the staff to include teachers qualified in Early Childhood Education.

The school is open 52 weeks per year, Monday - Friday, from 6:45 A.M. – 5:00 P.M. There is not only an educational school-year program, but also a well-planned summer recreational program.

name: Martin Luther King, Jr. Community Center School Age Program
Next Generation Children's Center
details:
Welcome to Next Generation Children’s Centers! Your child’s journey to new learning experiences and friendships starts with a nurturing environment in your home and extends to the enriching childcare programs at Next Generation.

I opened the first Next Generation Children’s Center in Natick, Massachusetts back in 1993 after searching—and not finding—a suitable daycare solution for my first grandchild. That search made me realize there was a tremendous need for quality childcare for working parents. I am proud of the ten locations we currently have across eastern Massachusetts. Our growth over the years is due in large part to our unwavering commitment to provide parents and their children with the highest possible care and educational experience.

In our unrelenting commitment to excellence, Next Generation Children’s Centers will continue to be innovative in the design of our childcare centers and enhance our already rich curriculum for all age groups. Our curriculum integrates the top early childhood philosophies and teaching methodology including Piaget, Montessori and Reggio Emilia.

Next Generation is a Massachusetts based, family-owned business, made up of hundreds of professional educators and thousands of families. The entire team at Next Generation is passionate about providing a safe and stimulating environment for your child to develop a life–long love of learning through play and other enriching experiences. This passion extends to our own families—I am proud to say that our top management team has children enrolled in or who have graduated from our schools.

It is our privilege and our goal to make our schools the very best for our children as well as yours. We hope that you enjoy your visit with us. Please feel free to contact us with any questions you might have about our schools and programs. We look forward to getting to know you and your child.

name: Little People's Country Day Care
details: Our childcare center offers programs for infants, toddlers and preschoolers. Our philosophy is to provide high quality childcare through goal setting. These goals will assist in the development of self-expression, communication skills, and a positive self-image through group interaction.

name: Waltham Day Care Center
details: The mission of Waltham Day Care Center is to provide high quality child care services for children 12 months to Pre-K in a caring, stimulating environment and at a reasonable cost to families in the Waltham area.

name: Our Redeemer Child Care Center
details: Our Redeemer Child Care Center is a Christian childcare center that celebrates the whole child and nurtures the body, mind and spirit in a creative and secure developmental environment. Our philosophy is that the child develops to his/her full potential when given the opportunity to experience and explore age-appropriate activities with guidance, love and the support of dedicated skilled early childhood educators.

name: KID'S CLUB AT SANBORN
details:
The Henry C. Sanborn School, built in 1962 and renovated in 1996, was named for a former school superintendent. A neighborhood school, Sanborn has 350 students. The professional staff of 17 full-time classroom teachers is highly educated and continues to take advantage of professional development opportunities. The faculty and staff are supplemented by additional part-time individuals in order to provide various support services.

The core curriculum includes up-to-date resource materials. Beyond the core academic areas, students participate in physical education, music, visual arts, media, and computer literacy classes. All third-graders learn to read music through playing the recorder. All fourth- and fifth-graders are invited to join an in-school chorus. Student Council is a voluntary activity for all fourth- and fifth-graders on a rotating basis and emphasizes social responsibility.

name: Willow Path Childcare
details:
Founded in 2003, Willow Path Childcare is an independent Boston-area childcare center serving kids from 5 weeks to 7 years of age, and is conveniently located near Centre Street at the West Roxbury / Jamaica Plain / Roslindale line.

Our mission at Willow Path Childcare is to teach children to be caring compassionate, and to accept others’ differences. We allow each child to develop at his or her own pace, promote independence, and strive to foster feelings of self confidence, success, and accomplishment while making positive contributions to the community which we serve.

name: MetroWest YMCA OST Program @ Brophy
details:
Being licensed through the EEC, we are required to maintain one staff member for every thirteen children. We staff to maintain a ratio of one-to-ten.
Each program offers a healthy snack and drink. All snacks are peanut-free. Any other allergies will be addressed per specific child’s needs.  The program runs from 7am-school start and then school closing to 6pm.

We offer a vacation day program that provides activities on most of the Framingham Public School‘s closure days.  Vacation days rotate at four of our School's Out Sites. The vacation program runs 7:30am to 6:00pm. Every vacation day has a theme and most include a field trip or a visitor. About three weeks before each vacation day, a sign-up sheet will be available at all six sites to provide location and activities. All families must complete this form in order to participate even if your child is enrolled in the vacation package. Field trips are included in the cost of the vacation day.

details:

details:
Being licensed through the EEC, we are required to maintain one staff member for every thirteen children. We staff to maintain a ratio of one-to-ten.
Each program offers a healthy snack and drink. All snacks are peanut-free. Any other allergies will be addressed per specific child’s needs.  The program runs from 7am-school start and then school closing to 6pm.
