About three weeks before each vacation day, a sign-up sheet will be available at all six sites to provide location and activities. All families must complete this form in order to participate even if your child is enrolled in the vacation package. Field trips are included in the cost of the vacation day.

name: Maples Little Angels at MRNC
details:
Located in the heart of the Maples Rehabilitation and Nursing Center, Maples Little Angels is an early education and care program providing quality education and care for a maximum of 29 children ages 8 weeks through 6 years old.

Our children are grouped into two family-like mixed age groups: Infants and Toddlers (8 weeks to 2 years 9 months) and Preschoolers (2.9 to 6 years old). The curriculum for each group provides appropriate activities which foster early language and math understanding, as well as social, emotional, and physical growth opportunities. Throughout the day, children make choices, learn to problem solve, resolve conflicts and build self-help skills.

Maples Little Angels AT MRNC is accredited by the National Association of Education for Young Children. The primary goal of this national accreditation is to assure the high standards of quality care and education that all children deserve. For more information on NAEYC accreditation visit their website at www.naeyc.org.

Additionally, we are licensed by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care.

name: Triumph Inc., Quinn Center Head Start
details: Triumph, Inc. is an independent non-profit 501c3 agency incorporated in 1965. TRIUMPH is an acronym that stands for "Taunton Responds in Unison Many People Help". This spirit of community support remains an integral part of Triumph's work today. Initial funding came in the form of a federal Head Start grant during the summer of 1965 as part of President Lyndon Johnson's War on Poverty. Forty-eight years, later the Head Start program remains a central focus of the agency. Triumph's exceptionally high quality programming focuses on children under the age of five. We are deeply committed to the belief that parents are a child's first and most important teacher. We work in close partnership with families and offer a range of programs and opportunities that support families in growing strong and successful children. The agency is committed to ensuring that children and families of all socio-economic levels in the city of Taunton and town of Raynham, Massachusetts have access to the very best early childhood experiences.

name: West Boylston Community Nursery School
details:
West Boylston Community Nursery School is a Non-Profit Nationally Accredited Preschool Program serving infants to 7 years. We are housed in and owned by the First Congregational Church. this program has served the young children and families from area communities for over 45 years.
 
Community Nursery School is licensed by the Department of Early Education
and Care. We are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children. This voluntary national program recognizes excellence in early Childhood programs.
 
Through the  professional staff of the teachers and varied support professionals, we strive to help each child reach his/her personal potential. The goal and objectives are to meet the children's physical, emotional, cognitive and gross motor skills. We will provide an environment that encourages creativity, social skills, self-esteem, an appreciation of the arts and respects diversity.
 
Classes are kept to a low student-teacher ratio and often fill up quickly.

name: Love to Learn Preschool & Daycare Center, Inc.
details:
Our program's philosophy
The goal of Love to Learn Preschool & Daycare Center is to provide a welcoming learning environment.  Love to Learn makes every effort possible to care for the individual needs of all learners.  We believe that each child is a unique individual.  We are sensitive to a child’s social, emotional, intellectual, and physical needs.  We provide developmentally appropriate curriculum that focus on the process of learning and help children enjoy successful experiences.  We encourage not just learning, but also the LOVE OF LEARNING!

name: The Tot Spot
details:
Tot Spot offers programs specially designed to meet the needs of all children. Programs are available for infants, toddlers, preschoolers, and school-age children up to 13 years old.

Infants: At Tot Spot, our staff provides a safe, "home away from home" environment where your infant can learn, play and grow. We provide an abundance of personal attention and interaction that will help them develop basic cognitive and social skills. They learn by experiencing the environment through their senses by physically moving around and through social interaction.

Toddlers: Our classrooms are equipped to support safe exploration so your child has room to discover, build motors skills, and improve coordination. Our program enables your toddler to grow in confidence and learn to walk tall in their world.

Preschool: Our preschool program focuses on preparing your child for kindergarten and are designed to help build self-confidence. Independence and respect are practiced and encouraged. We promote literacy, language, math, science, creative skills, physical development, and learn through hands on activities.

School Age Children: Our before and after school care offers homework time and free choice of learning centers to interact in. Building friendships and learning to respect one another is a skill that is encouraged year round. We also offer transportation to school. During the summer months, we offer swimming lessons and go on many field trips.

name: Meridian Gymnastics and Youth Fitness Preschool
WCCC After School Program - Fisk School
details: The Wellesley Community Children’s Center is a private, non-profit corporation, operated by a Board of Directors, administrative staff, and professional teaching staff. In 1971, WCCC began by enrolling preschoolers and kindergartners. We now serve more than 400 children from infancy through middle school in our Early Childhood and After School Programs.

name: South End Head Start
details:
Building a foundation for educational success.  ABCD’s Head Start and Early Head Start programs helps over 2,200 young children and their families each year, prepare for success in school and life by providing high-quality early education.

Children ages 3-to-5-years-old attend 23 Head Start sites across the city. Infants, toddlers and pregnant mothers get the support they need at Early Head Start Centers in Dorchester, East Boston and the South End. Year-round, extended-day programs enable parents to go to school or work.

These programs help children learn during the most important years for brain development. They offer comprehensive support for parents and children—including health services, nutrition and social services to keep families strong.

Because Head Start knows that parents are the most important teachers, parents are deeply involved in the program. Parents are leaders in making policy and guiding programs, volunteering in the classroom and advocating for the needs of young children.

ABCD’s Head Start program is at the forefront of cutting-edge work in early education—from fighting childhood obesity, to involving fathers, to building school readiness, to training teachers to meet high standards. Partners include Boston’s leading hospitals and universities.

Use the "Find Services" button on the top right of this page to search for near-by locations and find maps and directions.

name: Young At Heart Learning Center
details: Young at Heart is a warm and loving preschool environment where your child will enjoy learning through play! We build social skills as well as academics.

name: Positive Action Day Care
details: Committed only to excellence, Positive Action Daycare Center of New Bedford, MA is your trusted developmental learning center. We guarantee our professionalism because we consider your satisfaction our top priority. We always strive to exceed all expectations.

name: Salem Community Child Care
details:
Advantages of Our Centers
Our child to teacher ratio is as low as 1:7, so your child will always receive personal and individual attention.
All of our teachers are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children, and we thoroughly follow Massachusetts state guidelines for child education and care.
We also make sure to keep our prices low while never sacrificing high-quality, professional care, so both your finances and your mind can rest easy.

Our History
Owner Christin Hatch has 36 years of experience in child care and education. She started her business as a private non-profit with a parent board of directors, who demanded a child care center with high standards.

name: The Salvation Army Kids Club - Chelsea
Perkins Child Development Center
details:
The Perkins Child Development Center provides an enriched and engaging environment for infants, toddlers, and preschoolers that encourages their imagination, challenges their thinking skills, and enhances their social and language development.

We believe that play which fosters exploration is essential to learning.  We are sensitive to the cultural, social, and economic needs of the families we serve and place significant value on their involvement.

Our Center values the experience your child has in our care:
    Our staff is keenly aware of, and responsive to, the needs of individual children.
    Our environment is inviting for children, staff, and parents.
    Our activities are child-directed and open-ended to encourage creativity, problem-solving, social interaction, and success.
    Learning is integrated throughout the day.
    We believe play is central to each child’s experience.

name: Steppingstones School, Inc.
details: Steppingstones students discover that learning is fun and that school is an exciting place to be.  Our small teacher/child ratio enables each child to progress at his/her own pace and to benefit from the hands-on, exploratory nature of the programs. The daily program includes indoor and outdoor free playtime, individual and group learning experiences, child-initiated and teacher-initiated activities.  Our programs create a learning environment that fosters individual creativity, builds self-esteem and encourages children to respect themselves and others. The staff facilitates the development of social skills and encourages a sense of community while valuing the unique individuality of each child. The Steppingstones programs are designed to motivate, challenge and instill a love for learning.  The goal is to create students who approach new situations with an "I can do it" attitude; children whose uniqueness has been valued and who know they are capable of success.

name: Minute Man ARC for Human Services, Inc.
Wilder Memorial Nursery School
details:
Welcome to Wilder Memorial Nursery School. Wilder is believed to be the first cooperative preschool in the United States, and has a long and wonderful history with generations of families involved. Over the years, more than 4,500 children have participated in this program.

Every parent knows just how special his or her child is. We absolutely agree. Our goal is to create a rich environment that your child will explore and find success in every day. For many of the children this will be the beginning of their school experience; a great deal of learning will occur right here.

The Wilder Staff is dedicated to making the children's first school experience a positive one, encouraging them to become active participants in the learning process. We want them to love coming to school!

With a sense of wonder, a sense of humor and a sense of compassion, we offer them a child-centered environment with a small group size of teacher to child ratio. Within the "learning center" approach, children make "center" choices to practice and master new intellectual, social and physical skills. A child has the opportunity to select from one of the following "Center" choices each day ; Dramatic Play, Game Room (math), Lab ( Science), Music and Movement and Art. Uppermost, is our desire to help each child acquire an enthusiastic, positive, and confident attitude toward self, life and learning.

We strive to foster self confidence, independence and self-control while stressing respect for others. The children are encouraged to make choices which are important in learning decision-making and independence as well as responsibility for their own actions. We proudly serve the South Shore towns of Braintree, Quincy, Weymouth, Randolph and surrounding areas.

name: Presentation of Mary Montessori
details:
The Montessori classroom is a child-size world.  Whatever is in the world outside can be incorporated meaningfully in the Montessori classroom.  To a child, the world is unmanageable–it is too big, too complex and too confusing.  By careful selection of materials by the teacher, an environment is set up that allows the child to explore life on a level he/she can understand.  The materials or activities are designed to stimulate independent exploration.  This prepared environment entices the child to proceed at his/her own pace from simple activities to more complex ones.  Through this process the child’s natural curiosity is satisfied and he/she begins to experience the joy of discovering the world.  Materials and curriculum center on Everyday Living, Sensorial, Language, Math, Social Studies, Science, Religion, Art, Music, and Physical Exercises.

As the child develops a sense of pride in his/her “work”, a feeling of confidence, well- being, and joy begins to manifest itself from within.   “I can do it!” gives a child a sense of independence and personal accomplishment.  It can also lead the child to acquire a new sense of responsibility.

The concept of freedom within the classroom is one with limits.  A child is allowed to work freely so long as he/she does not disturb others.  The atmosphere is one of peace and tranquility.  Actually, the children, having the freedom to follow their interests, are generally happy and busy with their work.

The Montessori School is an “approach to learning” and as such has no distinction of class or intelligence.  It has been used successfully in all parts of the world and in all types of preschool programs.

name: Milldam Nursery School
details: Milldam Nursery School, one of the oldest and most established preschools in Concord, is a parent cooperative preschool. Milldam is a developmentally appropriate, play-based program with many opportunities for exploration and discovery. We have been serving Concord families from our classrooms at the First Parish Church since 1969. As a cooperative preschool we have the unique opportunity to be involved and participate in our children's education. Teachers, parents and children learn together, creating a dynamic, enriching experience that transcends the classroom. Our programs begin at 2 years. Tuition assistance is available for qualifying families.

details:

name: P.A.C.E. Head Start
details:
Our mission at P.A.C.E. Head Start is to provide a family centered child development program for eligible children in the Greater New Bedford area. Families are empowered through a range of services which include:

~ an early education experience which builds upon a child’s strengths and engages parents as partners ~
~ child care options that address the diverse needs of families ~
~ meaningful parent involvement opportunities ~
~ advocacy to overcome obstacles and improve quality of life ~
~ collaborations with community agencies ~

Services are provided in an environment that promotes respect, fosters inclusion and celebrates diversity among children, families and staff.

name: The Loft School of Marion
details: The Loft School of Marion, Inc. was founded when a small group of parents recognized the need for a cooperative preschool in Marion. With one teacher and a handful of children, Loft began operations in the loft of an old barn on North Front Street in the fall of 1964. Within a couple of years, increasing class size demanded a more established location, and the program eventually moved to our present home at St. Gabriel’s Church. Times have changed over the years, but the foundation of Loft remains the same. Dedicated professionals and parents working and playing together with wonderful children in a safe and nurturing environment. The cooperative aspect of the program is still a popular and important introduction to the school experience. The continuum of learning and play that exists throughout our programs will remain an important goal for years to come.

name: With All My Heart Child Care Center
Webster Square Day Care Center, Inc.

details:

name: Pine Hill Montessori School
details:
Established in 1971, Pine Hill offers a comprehensive preschool for children ages three, four and five.

The Program integrates Montessori teaching methods with conventional teaching methods in order to foster the optimum development of each child.

Each day, the children are presented with opportunities for discovering and learning. Experiences in music, art, science, literature readiness skills, as well as activities that promote fine and gross motor skill are provided.

These experiences are carefully planned to help each child develop at his/her own pace, socially, emotionally, physically and cognitively. There are approximately 15 children in a class with two qualified teachers. Primary emphasis is placed on a nurturing, kind and respectful environment. Special attention is given to recognizing each child’s uniqueness and encouraging his/her positive self-image.

name: Tiny World Child Care Inc.
details:
Tiny World Child Care Inc. is a bilingual year round daycare center founded by Delia Vildoso and Janet Hung. Both have combined fifteen years of experience as early childhood educators in Brookline, MA.

At Tiny World Child Care Inc. we believe in nurturing each child’s individual interests and strengths. Our early childhood educators encourage children to think for themselves, to make their own decisions, find solutions to problems, and to express their ideas and feelings, all within a safe and structured classroom environment. One of our principal goals is to help each child build his or her self-confidence every day. Our dedicated staff also treasure and love children, they are able to identify the needs of each child and the areas they excel in as well as those that can be improved. They love being a teacher and know they are a second home to the children. Our teachers provide exposure to the Spanish language throughout the day, whether it is by singing a song in Spanish or by simply teaching them words in Spanish such as “agua” (water). We also teach our children Spanish through a special weekly music class.

We strongly believe that children learn better through inquiry and play, and we are committed to creating a healthy, clean and stimulating environment in which every child has an equal opportunity to learn and to grow. All our classrooms provide a structured routine, along with multiple activities that brighten each child’s own choice and expression. We will serve children and their families of all races, nationalities, ethnicities, religions, etc.

Finally, we believe that parents are the critical influences in each child’s life and we pride ourselves on maintaining outstanding communication with families. Whether it is by emails, texts, notes, etc. we strongly believe that communication with families is an important factor that enables children to grow. Our parents are always invited to join us for special celebrations such as; birthday parties, our annual graduation potluck and many more family festivities.

name: MOC Child Care & Head Start Services / Marvin School Early Childh
details: MOC’s Child Care & Head Start (CCHS) provides early education and care and prepares children and families for appropriate growth, development, and school readiness through comprehensive, family-centered services. CCHS supports the success of both parents and children by offering quality center-based and family child care home-based services to area low-income families with children from birth to twelve years of age. Centers are located in Fitchburg, Leominster, Clinton, Gardner, Winchendon, and Athol and at Mount Wachusett Community College.  Family Child Care homes are located throughout MOC’s service area.

name: Piccolo Mondo Child Care and Learning Center
All About Learning
details:
All About Learning, LLC has been in operation for over 26 years. Our staff is experienced and our policies have grown over the years to ensure that all children are successful. We are a caring experienced center that has worked with many personalities. Our success record and our reputation are well established. 
    Our admission interview is very detailed. We give you all the information necessary for you to decide whether we are the center for your family. We believe that you should be aware of all our policies prior to enrollment. 
 AAL staff are trained to become a part of your child's support system in order to learn what makes each child succeed. Our teachers' are certified by the Department of Early Education and Care. Our flexible schedule ensures that each child is learning as well as content. Individualized attention means knowing your child's wants and needs which allows us to give every child a successful first encounter in a school setting. 
    No child is ever alone with one staff member. Our NO OPPORTUNITY POLICY means that there are no negative touching issues at our center. Imagine feeling secure as you work knowing your child is safe in all ways in our care!
    We service infant,toddler and pre school age children with academics through play as an integral part of our curriculum.
    Weekly Progress Reports monitor the growth and development of all students as well as give us our goal for each child!
  In other words NO child is left behind and all succeed!

name: Peirce Playcare and Extended Day
details:
Our motto: Strive to shine: as a student, as a friend!

The Peirce School encompasses a diverse school population: students come from the Peirce district, from other Arlington districts through open enrollment, and from the Boston city schools through the METCO program. While our class sizes are comparable to other Arlington schools, our total student population of approximately 280 students means that we are a close-knit community.

At Peirce, there are two classrooms per grade. Each classroom has one full-time teacher or two job-share teachers; and, depending on class size, may have a teaching assistant. One special education teacher works with the grades K-2 classrooms, one works with grades 3-4, and one with grade 5. The special education teachers co-teach with the classroom teachers. (From 2010-2013, Peirce had one co-taught classroom per grade and special education students from other Arlington districts attended Peirce. From the 2013-2014 school year onward, the co-taught model will be used in all Arlington elementary schools so that students will receive the benefits of co-teaching without having to leave their home schools.)

Our teachers and support staff use proven methodologies and a highly effective curriculum to help children grow academically, socially, and physically. We regularly participate in professional development in order to improve our skills and offer a better learning experience for the children.

Peirce School practices and encourages Peirce Pride: Perseverance, Effort, Integrity, Responsibility, Cooperation and Excellence. At monthly assemblies, different grades present stories based on these themes to reinforce the ideas behind Peirce Pride.

Our mission statement: The Peirce School provides a safe, nurturing and challenging school environment in which students strive for academic excellence. The faculty and staff, with the cooperation and support of parents, prepare students to be caring, responsible, and industrious citizens in a diverse, multicultural world.

name: Striar Hebrew Academy of Sharon
details:
Welcome to Striar Hebrew Academy of Sharon (SHAS), a coeducational, Modern Orthodox day school in South-area Boston, serving students toddler-age through Grade 6. Striar Hebrew Academy is a unified Jewish day school on two campuses: the Yaakov Spellman Early Learning Center at 60 Ashcroft Road houses our early childhood program, for Toddlers through Kindergarten. The elementary grades 1 through 6 are located at 100 Ames Street.  From the youngest to the oldest students, we teach a dual Judaic and general studies curriculum, infused with Torah values, which stresses the importance of showing respect for each other and embracing individual differences. SHAS students receive caring, individualized attention, made possible by our low student-to-faculty ratio and our compassionate teachers.  This intimate environment creates a strong feeling of community, which provides a comfort level in which students thrive socially, emotionally and academically.

Families choose SHAS because they seek a challenging and supportive environment where they can be partners in their child's education. Our integrated curriculum leads students to become confident, critical thinkers with a passion for learning. They emerge as young Jews with a well-defined sense of their own Jewish identity and values. Our guiding principle is the concept of Torah u'Mada (Torah and worldly knowledge). The value of combining a Judaic and general education was the vision behind our school's founding and, today, remains at the core of our educational philosophy.

name: County Road Children's Center
details: It is the goal of the County Road children’s Center to promote social, emotional and educational development by providing children with a loving, nurturing environment. We offer support for parents and children by providing a setting for living and learning together. The center and its staff maintain an atmosphere in which all children will feel secure and cared for. Creativity is strongly encouraged and problem solving is practiced. Our staff is always willing to facilitate with the transition to daycare for both children and parents. Please let us know about any concerns you have so that we may address them. We want you and your child to be happy and excited to come to our center. It is our policy that no family shall be discriminated against based on their race, religion, cultural heritage, national origin, political beliefs, marital status, disability or sexual orientation.

name: Montessori Children's House of Auburn
details: Our programs are based on Dr. Montessori's view that children go through a series of "sensitive periods" with "creative moments" when they show spontaneous interest in learning. It is then that we have the greatest ability to learn, and these periods should be utilized to the fullest so that children learn as much as possible. Our programs provide environments in which this can happen developmentally in three-year multi-age groups with the same certified Montessori teacher and assistant. Self-discipline and the reward one feels when working, naturally take place through the independence of learning. Each program provides stimulating learning experiences that start with concrete principles and move naturally to abstract. This can best be described by the progression of the single gold bead to the ten-bar to the hundred-square to the thousand-cube of which our children use so much during their Montessori education.

details: The Salem YMCA supports families by providing safe and affordable child care programs that give children an opportunity to develop physically, intellectually and socially. We believe that our child care programs are an extension of the home. We provide enrichment programs for children between the ages of 12 months and 5 years. Daily programming is led by the director and supported by a well-trained and nurturing staff.

    Our team exercises and challenges the capacities of the child that are emerging at a given developmental stage.
    We encourage and help the child develop his or her pattern of interests, talents and goals.
    We present learning experiences when the child is developmentally best able to master and retain what they learn and relate it to past and future experiences.

name: Little Wonders Learning & Child Care Center
details:
Our purpose is to provide our community with a high quality preschool implementing a meaningful, enriching, and fun preschool curriculum. Just as important we provide a caring and kind environment where the teachers recognize that each child is an individual and all areas of development are equally important – emotional, social, and cognitive.

Little Wonders has a classroom for our younger friends and a classroom for our Pre K friends. Our preschool day is structured and includes; free exploration, meeting time, fine motor development, movement, books and reading, and much more.

Free Exploration offers Center based, self-directed learning experiences designed specifically for the curiosity of the young mind. Number Concepts, Science Explorations, Home Living. Sand and Water, Creation Station and a Listening Center are just a few of the learning centers offered.

Fine Motor Development provides interesting and engaging opportunities to strengthen and develop fine motor skills. Playdough, stringing beads, cutting and pasting, and
"Fundations®, Wilson Language Basics"; an innovative approach to the introduction of letter writing is offered daily.

Creative Movement offers a time to move our large motor muscles. Balancing, throwing and catching, skipping and jumping, are highlighted developmental skills that are introduced by innovative games, obstacle courses and activities.

Fundations® Little Wonders uses Fundations® introduced by Wilson Language Training. Fundations provides students with a foundation for reading and spelling. The purpose of the instruction is learning to both read and write for meaning, understanding, and joy.

Center Holidays & Closings (Available from our Downloads page.)

Snacks and Lunch!
We provide a healthy snack in the Morning and Afternoon. Parents provide a healthy lunch.

name: Shattuck Child Care Center
details: The Shattuck Child Care is a unique public-private partnership providing high quality childcare to employees of Shattuck hospital and members of the surrounding community.

name: Rise and Shine Academy
details:
Criterion Child Enrichment specializes in developmentally appropriate programs and services for young children and their families. Our mission seeks to support the early development and education of young children and their families. We believe in the strength of the family and its capacity to promote the health and development of children.

We offer community-based developmental enrichment groups, child care, early intervention and newborn home visiting programs.

We emphasize the professional development of staff and other community early childhood providers. Each year, our agency sponsors the Great Beginnings Conference for advanced early childhood professionals.

Founded in 1985, we have grown to be one of the largest providers of child and family development services in the Commonwealth of Massachusetts. Criterion Child Enrichment is a private non-profit corporation. We serve over 5000 families each year with a staff of over 300 professionals at 12 locations throughout Massachusetts.

name: North Street Head Start
details: The program is designed to serve children 3-5 years of age from families who qualify for Head Start services in Somerville and Cambridge. CAAS Head Start helps all children succeed by providing comprehensive services to children through activities that help them grow: socially, emotionally, cognitively, and physically. These services lay the foundation for life long learning and continued school success. Children transition from our program into elementary schools prepared and ready to continue to learn and grow. Parents are encouraged to become partners with the program since CAAS Head Start recognizes you as your child’s first teacher. Working together will allow us to make your Head Start experience more valuable for both you and your child. We offer opportunities for you to become involved in classroom activities direct involvement in the decision making of program planning and operation. The CAAS Head Start program is operated by the Community Action Agency of Somerville, which also provides additional services in the Somerville community.

name: Temple Emanuel Nursery School
details:
Our Temple Emanuel Preschool provides a loving, caring, and supportive environment for young children and their families.  The staff is dedicated to promoting the healthy growth and development of children from two to five years of age.  The teachers respect the unique individuality of each child and have a strong commitment to providing a carefully balanced, child-appropriate and experiential program that integrates the secular and Judaic components through the year.  This nurturing and affirming environment encourages children to learn and grow through exploration and discovery and to develop social and interpersonal skills.  The classroom becomes the center in which children learn about themselves and the world around them.

As a synagogue preschool, we are fully committed to a Judaica program that helps children learn about the Jewish part of their world and life.  The customs and traditions of Shabbat and the holidays are experienced through the young child's senses.  Family participation is encouraged.  An atmosphere of belonging is created through which the children and their families experience the delights of Judaism.

name: Temple Beth Shalom Preschool
details:
At Temple Beth Sholom Preschool we believe in providing children from two to five years old with the opportunity to pursue unknown paths in order to make discoveries.

Recognizing that each child develops at his/her own unique developmental pace, we create an atmosphere where children are given the chance to grow and develop in a safe nurturing environment by building on the concepts of the world around them. Developmentally appropriate activities guide children as they develop socially, emotionally, intellectually, physically and spiritually from their second birthday through the pre-kindergarten year.

Our activities focus on process and emphasize creativity and problem-solving techniques The richness of our traditions and culture blend together with secular activities to provide a balance of experiences for each child. The children experience and learn about customs and culture as part of their preschool experience. Shabbat, Judaism and holidays are explored through music, stories, puppetry and celebration.

Our staff is chosen based on their background in early childhood education and their knowledge about developmentally appropriate practices. It is our belief that children must be nurtured by warm, caring, responsible adults to help them reach their full potential as happy, healthy and competent individuals.

Our program is honored to be among a select group of schools that have been accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children, an organization recognized for developing criteria for high standards in Early Childhood Education.

name: Westover Job Corps Head Start
details:
Our MISSION
Holyoke • Chicopee • Springfield Head Start, Inc. is committed to providing low-income children and their families with a Beacon of Hope and source of support for a brighter future. We strive to do so by providing high quality comprehensive child development services to enrolled children and empowering families to achieve stability in their home environment.

Our CORE VALUES
Excellence • Respect • Diversity • Communication Team Work • Flexibility • Dedication • Shared Vision

Our HISTORY
Since 1965 HCS Head Start Inc. has been providing high-quality early childhood education services for children and families in cities and towns located in Western Massachusetts, including Holyoke, Chicopee, Springfield, Ludlow, Palmer, and Granby. Head Start provides a solid foundation for children to gain necessary skills to enter kindergarten and to be successful in life. Our centers are fully licensed by the MA Department of Early Education and Care. For a complete list of the cities and towns we serve, contact us at (413)788-6522.

details: We are a private, not-for-profit after-school program serving the Ward School community.  Licensed by the State of Massachusetts, our Board of Directors and team of talented teachers strive to offer a creative and comfortable environment for kids to learn and play!

    Individualized Meal Plans
    Health Screenings (Including Dental, Vision and Hearing)

details:
SELF SUPPORTING CORPORATION, WHICH WAS FORMED TO MEET THE CHILD CARE NEEDS OF THE COMMUNITY AND TO OFFER ENRICHMENT TYPE PROGRAMS TO THE SCHOOL AGE CHILDREN OF tOPSFIELD.  STEWARD STATION IS LICENSED BY THE MASSACHUSETTS DEPARTMENT OF EARLY EDUCATION & Care.

our mission is to provide safe, accessible and affordable programs for children in kindergarten through sixth grade.  our intent is to provide a community based enrichment program that does not attempt to replace home or school but complements both.

our programs will consist of activities designed to meet the social, academic, emotional and physical needs of children in a warm and supportive atmosphere.  our goal is for children to have the opportunity to enjoy the time spent with us by participating in activities such as arts & crafts, sports,  games, nature study, science, and quiet time.

details: Martha’s Vineyard Community Services’ mission is to enhance the lives of those it serves by meeting the comprehensive needs of individuals, families, and the community through a partnership of programs that provides accessible education and health and human services of the highest quality. - See more at: http://www.mvcommunityservices.com/about/mission/#sthash.h4KAomS5.dpuf

name: Montessori Country Day School
details: For over twenty-five years, the Montessori Country Day School of Holden has fostered children's desire to learn while delivering individual attention to students as they develop and grow. Located in Worcester County, our mission is to provide preschool students a successful education that will stand as their foundation to build upon throughout life. Welcome to our community!

name: Smith Mills Weekday Nursery
details:
Smith Mills Preschool is a private school in Dartmouth, Massachusetts and has been in operation for over 45 years. Our mission is to provide children with a caring and nurturing environment where they can develop a strong foundation for learning.

Our school is an academic based preschool.  Our curriculum encompasses the alphabet and numerical recognition, shapes and colors, and lays the foundation for early reading.  We use the Handwriting without Tears for handwriting and the Cozy Corner Curriculum by Scholastics for our Literacy component.   All this coupled with our certified and experienced teaching teams, makes for a very busy day of learning!

In addition to our academics, we do not lose sight of the fact our students are still children.  Throughout our day we offer a variety of "hands on" activities that stimulate play and imagination.  This balance promotes opportunities for all types of learners to explore and find success. Additionally, we work with children on understanding the art of sharing, taking turns, and developing the self help skills needed as they mature.

All our preschool programs begin at age 2.9 years where you can choose from 2, 3 or 5 half school day (8:45 - 12pm) options. We also offer Pre-Kindergarten programs for children 4 years old as of September 1st.  Parents have the option of a 4/5 day (Tues- Fri) Half School Day program or a 4/5 day (8:45-2:30pm) Full School Day Program.  Our Pre-Kindergarten program offers a Spanish compliment at no additional cost.

In addition to our Preschool Program, Smith Mills offers a FULL DAY Private Kindergarten.  Our Kindergarten has been in operation for over 10 years.  Smith Mills Kindergarten provides children with a strong foundation of learning.  Our low teacher to child ratio provides the one on one direction that kindergarteners need to become confident readers, writers and most importantly LEARNERS!

name: Woodside Sch & CommResource Ctr
details: Woodside School has been created as an interactive learning environment for children to develop an understanding of the larger meanings of life and the importance of stewardship.

name: Step Ahead Kindergarten
details:
Step Ahead is an innovative science based program located at First Congregational Church in Braintree and in downtown Quincy.  Step Ahead incorporates a comfortable environment that eases the child into an academic situation that includes a strong phonics agenda and an effective math program.  Other activities range from daily art and crafts, number games, reading readiness skills, story telling, role playing, poetry, dance, sports, and music.  Definitely something for everyone!

Step Ahead Preschool and Kindergarten has two locations: one in Braintree and one in the heart of downtown Quincy.  Both locations have a preschool for students 2 years 9months and older, and a transitional kindergarten for students who do not meet the kindergarten age cut off date. Also for those needing a boost before entering kindergarten. Braintree has a full day kindergarten with and extended day hours for the working parent. Braintree also has early drop off at 7:30 am.

details: We encourage laughter and smiles, offer consistent positive reinforcement, and strive to help your children feel good about who they are and who they have the potential to become.

details:
The us taekwondo education foundation
is a non-profit organization that was established in 2007 by founder Grand Master Kyung Won Kim.With the mission of instilling strong moral principles through mental and physical discipline into the mainstream of our public school system. name: Old Colony Y/Kingston Intermediate
address: KINGSTON INTERMEDIATE SCH 65 SECOND BROOK ST
details:
Before and After School Care is a great option for children of parents who need care which fits with both work and school schedules.  Children can choose from a wide variety of activities including arts & crafts, reading, sports, games, plus field trips, themed special events, team building activites, and more!
 
The Old Colony YMCA believes that each child is special, with his or her own personality, talents, and skills.  Our approach to child care reflects the YMCA's core values of caring, honesty, respect, and responsibility, as well as our commitment to building strong kids, strong families and strong communities.
 
We offer so many wonderful activities and programs - all in a safe, nuturing, developmentally appropriate environment!

name: Vine St. Community Centers - SACC Program
Wonder Years, Inc.
details: At Wonder Years Our goal is to provide the best quality care to children. We do this by providing  a caring, nurturing and safe educational environment. We believe our program has achieved the  proper balance between academics and play. We believe in playing for the simple fun of it, as  part of the child's overall learning experience. We understand the stress of working parents and ensure that your child is well cared for in a safe and happy environment.

name: So Shore Community Center Nurs Sch
details: The SSCC Nursery School offers three levels of programs to meet the needs of children age's three to five. The morning programs run from 9 to 11:30 AM. The afternoon programs run from 12:30 to 3 PM. There are many extended day options for children enrolled in our school including ART EXPLORER, SOMETHING MORE, COMPUTERS & LUNCH, YOGA, FRIDAY FUN and GYMNASTICS & SPORTS classes. Our youngest program, The Nursery Program is for children who will be three years old by November 1st. The Pre-Kindergarten Program is for children who will be four by November 1st. We also offer a very special Enrichment Program for those children who have already had two years of school. This program is designed for older fours and fives whom are looking for a challenging year before they enter Kindergarten. The Nursery School Program’s goal is to provide a happy, safe environment where children will develop trust and have a positive “school” experience. The children will have the opportunity to recognize their own talents and abilities and they will be encouraged to approach new experiences with a spirit of enthusiasm and self-confidence. We follow the Guidelines for Preschool Learning Experiences created by the Early Childhood Advisory Council to the Massachusetts Board of Education. It is based on the standards set up for the Massachusetts Curriculum Frameworks. The Nursery School is also NAEYC accredited.

name: Raynham Before & After School Child Care
Pioneer Valley Montessori School
details:
Pioneer Valley Montessori School is an independent, nonprofit, coeducational day school offering Montessori early childhood and elementary education to children between the ages of 18 months and 12 years. The school is governed by a Board of Trustees, composed of parents of current PVMS students, community members and alumni parents.

PVMS enrolls students from 21 towns in Massachusetts and Connecticut, with approximately half of our students living in the city of Springfield. The next largest percentage of students come from Wilbraham. Students from many other towns attend PVMS, such as East Longmeadow, Longmeadow, Monson, Westfield, West Springfield, Ludlow, Belchertown and Chicopee. The school admits students without regard to race, color, national or ethnic origin or religious affiliation.

name: School is Cool Child Care
details: Our Philosophy is learning by activities and fun, educational interactions. We assist children to develop the skills and attitudes needed to become successful in school. We also validate and assist children to develop respect and appreciation for all the languages and cultures represented in our Programs.

name: VOC - Cabot Manor Child Care
details: VOC operates five childcare centers in Holyoke and Chicopee. Our goal is to assist parents who are working, in training leading to employment, or have other special needs. We provide a complete education program, meals, and opportunities for parent involvement.

name: Center for Early Education and Care - UMass/Amherst
TLC Play and Learn Campus, Inc
Self Help Head Start - Sachem
details:
The Head Start Program is based on the premise that all children share certain needs and that children of low income families, in particular, can benefit from a comprehensive developmental program to meet those needs. The Head Start approach make the following assumptions:

A child can benefit from a comprehensive, interdisciplinary program to foster development.

Because the family is the principal influence on the child's development, the child's family, as well as the community, must be involved in the program.

The overall goal of the Head Start Program is to bring about a greater degree of social competence in children of low-income families. Social competence means the child's everyday effectiveness in dealing with both the present environment and later responsibilities in school and in life. Social competence takes into account the interrelatedness of cognitive and intellectual development, physical and mental health,nutritional needs as well as other factors. To achieve social competence, Head Start objectives and performance standards provide for:

    Improvement of the child's health and physical abilities, including appropriate steps to correct physical and mental health problems and to enhance every child's access to an adequate diet.
    Improvement of the family's attitude toward future health care and physical abilities.
    Encouragement of self-confidence, spontaneity, curiosity and self-discipline that will assist the child's social and emotional health.
    Enhancement of the child's mental processes and skill, with particular attention to conceptual and communication skills.
    Establishment of patterns and expectations for success for the child that will create a climate of confidence for present and future learning efforts and overall development.
    Enhancement of the ability of the child and the family to relate to one another and to others.
    Development of a sense of dignity and self-worth within the child and his family.
business hours: 8:30 am to 4:30 pm, Monday through Friday

ABCD responds to the needs of our community through our decentralized, city-wide network, which includes 14 unique neighborhood centers.

name: Massasoit CommCollege-Children's Ctr
details:
Massasoit Community College Children's Center is a licensed campus facility.
We service the children of our students, faculty, and staff. We provide a safe, quality learning environment in which to grow. Our classroom is designed to be consistent with our philosophy for learning. Its child-oriented design is conducive to creative learning.

Keeping in mind the child's cognitive, physical, social, and emotional capabilities, the curriculum is constantly being adjusted to suit the needs of the individual child. Children are required to be 2.9 years of age through 5 years of age. Day care slots are available to suit the student's course schedules.

name: Village Green Preschool and DCC
details: Village Green is a kindergarten, preschool, and day care center located in Seekonk, MA. Backed with over 40 years of experience we offer a broad range of programs for children of ages 2.9 to 8. To learn more about us, our programs, and our unique facilities, please explore the links above.

name: Nashoba Valley Children's Center
details:
The Nashoba Valley Children's Center philosphy begins with the commitment to provide the best care for your children through new ideas and the most qualified and experienced staff.

Nashoba Valley Children's Center has been in business for over forty years.  Our personalized programs give our teachers the ability to meet the individual needs of every child.   

 We offer a variety of Programs to meet the needs of you and your children. Our Preschool offers a three and four year old preschool program and Four and Five year old Preschool Programs. 

In addition we offer a Playgroup Program for children 2.9 months through 3 years old.  We offer two programs running simultaneously in a warm and caring atmosphere.

 The three and four year old preschool program offers a two or three day option and a early drop off and Afternoon Adventures program,  The four and five year old program offers three or four day options and an early drop off and Afternoon Adventures program.   

 We are constantly trying to service the needs of all of our families if you need alternative times to meet your schedule please speak to us directly.   
 
Your children will discover that learning is fun, while making new friends and building long term relationships with teachers who guide you in your child's education.

name: Treetops Montessori
details: Opportunities to develop a child’s intellect are never as abundant as they are in the first six years of life. Treetops Montessori classrooms are especially designed to enhance your child’s growth and interests. Our nurturing teachers supply the necessary stimuli, materials, and thought-provoking curriculum to encourage thought, exploration, experimentation and creativity. We follow the “Montessori Method,” which emphasizes education of the whole personality by fostering the physical, emotional, spiritual, and intellectual growth of each child.

name: Magic Seasons Early Childhood Center School-Age Program
Margaret Fuller Neighborhood House After School Program
Spruce Street Nursery School
details:
Spruce Street Nursery School serves children ages 2-5 and is located in the heart of downtown Boston. At Spruce we recognize that children learn about the world  through active exploration and play.  Teachers here develop curriculum to honor and explore each child's potential.  Classrooms are designed to offer many opportunities for a child to learn at his or her own pace.  Art, music, and children's literature are essential elements of our program.  Concepts and skills are presented at appropriate developmental stages and then expanded upon through both structured activity and imaginative play.

Many children begin attending on a part-time schedule which allows both the child and family to achieve a comfort level with school and the separation process. Scheduled days increase in subsequent years as your child becomes acclimated to school, allowing greater continuity of curriculum as your child grows and develops.

We feel that children of all ages should come together to learn from and with each other.  Although our classrooms are grouped and defined generally by age, all of the children have ample opportunity to work with other teachers and age groups as well.  By encouraging interchange between classrooms a greater feeling of community is experienced as children both younger and older come to know and appreciate one another.

The city provides the school with many opportunities for concrete experiences that broaden the children’s understanding of the world around them.  Cart rides along city streets and trips to the park contribute to an essential understanding of what it means to be part of a larger community.  The many resources available in the city are invaluable teaching tools.  The richness and diversity of the urban environment both informs and enriches our educational mission.

Spruce Street Nursery School admits students of any race, color, and national origin to all the rights, privileges, programs and activities generally accorded or made available to students of the school.  Spruce Street Nursery School does not discriminate on the basis of race, cultural heritage, national or ethnic origin, marital status, religion, political beliefs, disability or sexual orientation in the administration of its educational policies, admissions policies, and other school administered programs.

name: T.L.C. Country Day School, Inc
details: We, at TLC Country Day School believe that Preschool and Pre-Kindergarten are essential in the fundamental development stages of a child's early life. TLC offers each child an opportunity to take those first steps by implementing an effective environment, which is loving, pleasant, inviting, colorful and creates a comfortable (cozy) atmostphere. Our staff presents a positive, exciting program that will start your child off with a healthy and enthusiastic outlook towards school.  Our goal at TLC is to encourage creativity, teach good listening skills, and develop an awareness of beauty in nature, music and the arts. We encourage children to interact positively by proper use of language and communication. We provide an age appropriate, challenging atmophere that creates an increased sense of curiosity and individual development. We encourage parent involvement and participation through school related activities. We also offer an expansive, beautiful palyground with plenty of room to run and climb.

name: Wee Care, Two
details: In the beginning, Wee Care started as a dream of Kim and Dolores to provide a caring, nurturing place for Alex, Kim’s daughter. Knowing what makes quality early education and care, doing it “right” was the driving force. In 1994, Wee Care was born at Main Street Southborough. A small, home-like center providing excellence in care and education, and support for families. Wee Care expanded to Breakneck Hill in Southborough two years later to meet the high demand for the quality care Wee Care provided. Kim and Dolores are still as committed to the care and education of children as we were in the beginning. They are still as hands-on today, providing a supportive place for children, parents, and staff.  Wee Care for little people is committed to provide a place where children and families receive responsive, individualized care every day. Our environment is clean, safe, loving, and facilitates learning, play, and a sense of wonder everyday. Our staff is professional, informed, and supportive to the ever-changing needs of children and families in our care everyday. Childhood happens everyday. Wee are here to make sure it is enjoyed, celebrated, and respected for the once-in-a-lifetime event that it is.

name: Pathways for Learning Preschools
details:
Respect is the foundation of everything that we do. The teachers respect each other as professionals and work together as a team. This respect is modeled for the children and in turn they are respectful toward each other. We also teach respect for the environment, our classroom and the world around us. The children may not be able to define respect in words but they will experience it.
 
Teachers play a vital role in the growth and school experiences of each child by acting as both a facilitator and model. They facilitate your child’s ability to resolve challenges, both social and educational. They model language and problem solving. These approaches allow your child to observe, practice, and receive feedback which all lead to his or her success.
 
The multi-age classroom provides an opportunity for the children to celebrate their differences and to be leaders. We know that each of our children are unique and special. In an environment where that is acknowledged and honored, the children can take pride in who they are and what they do. The range of developmental stages is not just reflected in chronological age. This range allows children to take leadership roles under circumstances where they have strengths independent of their age. 
 
Children who receive positive reinforcement are proud of their accomplishments, but more importantly, are proud of themselves. When children have confidence in who they are and believe in their own intelligence, they will be strong individuals who will learn from everything they do.

name: Methodist Nursery School
details: The Methodist Nursery School began in 1974 as an outreach of the Plymouth United Methodist Church. We have been serving the community for many years and now see former students enrolling their own children in our program. We are housed in the Plymouth United Methodist Church and value the good relationship we have with the church. We maintain an independent program that is governed by our board of Directors.  Our purpose is to provide a warm, loving, creative and stimulating environment in which Pre-school children can grow, play and learn together. Socially, your child will be encouraged to play and interact with his/her peers. Through this interaction, the importance of accepting others and their views along with the concept of sharing will be practiced. We believe that it is our job to stimulate the curiosity of your child as he/she begins the journey of being a life-long learner. We strive to open up the doors, letting your child progress without pressure at his/her own pace. We believe each child matures at a different rate and this must be taken into consideration, both in the area of curriculum as well as the presentation of materials. It is our job to prepare your child by giving him/her a sound foundation so that he/she may find his/her introduction into kindergarten a pleasant and rewarding experience.

name: MOC Child Care & Head Start Services Center / Hosmer
details: MOC’s Child Care & Head Start (CCHS) provides early education and care and prepares children and families for appropriate growth, development, and school readiness through comprehensive, family-centered services. CCHS supports the success of both parents and children by offering quality center-based and family child care home-based services to area low-income families with children from birth to twelve years of age. Centers are located in Fitchburg, Leominster, Clinton, Gardner, Winchendon, and Athol and at Mount Wachusett Community College.  Family Child Care homes are located throughout MOC’s service area.

name: Westboro Area Jewish Community Center Preschool
details: OUR MISSION:  We provide children with a nurturing, warm environment, which focuses on each child's individual development. While encouraging cognitive, social and, educational development, our NAEYC accredited program focuses on the whole child.  We help each child build the self-esteem, confidence, and skills necessary to succeed in school and in life.

name: Wellesley Community Children's Center
details: The Wellesley Community Children’s Center is a private, non-profit corporation, operated by a Board of Directors, administrative staff, and professional teaching staff. In 1971, WCCC began by enrolling preschoolers and kindergartners. We now serve more than 400 children from infancy through middle school in our Early Childhood and After School Programs.

name: Mashpee Creative Children's Center
details:
The goal of The Mashpee Creative Children's Center is to nurture happy, intelligent, well-adjusted children. Here you will find a nurturing and caring educational-social environment for  preschool children  ages 3 to 6 years. Our dedicated early childhood teachers are educated and experienced in child development and our curriculum  is designed to meet the varying developmental needs of the children. Teachers are facilitators of  the learning process and encourage children to learn and grow in their own  special way.
We celebrate the child and nurture individual strengths. Toilet training is not a pre-requisite for preschool , however, following simple directions, accepting and complying with teacher instruction, listening and attending skills and being able to participate in  small group activities are indicators of preschool readiness skills. We have 28 years of experience in Early Childhood Education and make accommodations to meet the needs of every child, however, there are times when a child does not have preschool readiness skills to be in a structured preschool program and may need the gift of time to develop these skills and/or additional intervention services, that are not services our program can  provide. These services are provided through the your town's Dept. of Special Education.
Our programs offer a variety of half day preschool options. 
We recognize that each child has unique talents, learning styles and personalities. Our highly-qualified and dedicated teachers are committed to working within each child's comfort zone to ensure optimal social, emotional and educational results. At The Creative Children's Center, all children are unique and special and we encourage each child to develop his/her own talents and  interests.

details:
Where children explore their own big ideas
Our five Technology Childcare Centers (TCC) have been developed in the spirit of MIT. Our skilled teachers view every child as an individual with a unique learning style and way of responding to the world. MIT created this parent resource as part of a larger mission to support the work-life needs of its faculty, post-doctoral scholars, students, and staff.

name: West End Day Nursery of New Bedford
details: he West End Day Nursery of New Bedford, Inc. is a non-profit, charitable institution organized in 1941 by Elnora M. Williams, the first Executive Director, to provide proper care and supervision for children including family service, child development, education, health, recreation and nutritional programs. We provide child care services for children from one month to 13 years. The West End Day Nursery is an educationally oriented program focusing on every aspect of the child's total development and welfare. Qualified staff members supervise all children. Each classroom bases its teachings and informal learning experiences on the age and developmental levels of children enrolled.

name: Lutheran Church Nursery School
details: The Lutheran Nursery School is a non-profit, self-supporting program conducted as a community service project and sponsored by the Lutheran Church of the Cross. Our aim is to nurture spiritual and ethical ideals in the child, building within him/her a sense of security, a realization of his/her own worth and possibilities. We consider the children entrusted to our care a great responsibility and we work toward guiding them into satisfying, positive relationships with other children and adults…always keeping in mind that each child is an individual. We firmly believe that the greatest gift we can give to our children is time, and therefore, it is the essence underlining our program.

name: Pudding Hill Preschool
details:
Our mission at Pudding Hill Preschool is to provide an enrichment program for young children in Marshfield and the surrounding communities.  We are concerned with the intellectual, emotional, physical, and developmental growth and well being of each child. We endeavor to recognize each child’s needs and interests in an environment that offers varied activities and meaningful relationships with other children and adults.

Our aim is to foster self-esteem in each child while recognizing and challenging individual needs. We maintain an environment that fosters creative response through self-initiated play, and encourages social confidence/competence. Children learn to express themselves through many content areas: art, movement, music, cooking, drama, science, nature, story telling, writing, group circle, literature, whole language, dramatic play and field trips to name a few.

Our curriculum incorporates all key components of a child's learning and development, such as cognition, music, drama, art, language and literacy, early math readiness skills and concepts, science, gross and fine motor coordination, and of course, socialization.

Our program is committed to providing a nurturing environment that fosters the growth and development of each child, challenges the potential of each child's individual abilities, respects the uniqueness of each child, and provides the tools for her/him to grow to her/his his full potential.

The philosophy of our school is based on a well proven educational theory that a child interacting in a developmentally appropriate environment will develop socially and emotionally while learning cognitive readiness skills, which are the foundation for later learning experiences.

We offer small class sizes staffed by highly creative and well-experienced early childhood teachers who regularly engage in furthering their professional development. As a result, the developmental programs used in our school are based on sound knowledge and the most up-to-date early childhood education techniques.

Our curriculum is supported by an environment that provides opportunities for each child to explore all the learning centers, each maintained with a variety of materials, appropriate for the age and stage of development. Our commitment is to facilitate a child’s learning through process-based, rather than product-based, experience.

name: Williams Afterschool Club
details: The Williams After School Club, Inc. (WASC) is a parent operated 501(c)(3) not-for-profit child care provider that has been providing a superior school-age child care program in Auburndale, Massachusetts since 2002. Our program is licensed and insured, and operates under the policies and guidelines of the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care.  We specialize in offering a safe and secure, academically rich, afterschool recreational program that promotes academic and social development through fun, stimulating, enriching activities for the children in our care. We follow a daily planned schedule of developmentally appropriate activities.

name: Shining Wonders Preschool
details: Shining Wonders Preschool is an early childhood program located in the Eastondale section of Easton, Massachusetts. It is set in a cozy one-level building built in 1931 that once housed the Eastondale Post Office, a variety store, a ceramic studio, and a piano studio.  The program’s philosophy centers on the innate and infinite possibility that is inherent in the wonder of each child. The belief that each child shines in his or her own light and is enriched by the surrounding positive environment provided by dedicated teachers and a curriculum that fosters the many intelligences of the individual. The discovery-oriented, open-ended, and hands-on activities are intended to call attention to all developmental areas including verbal, visual, motor, critical thinking, self-help, and social skills. Our bright, clean, two-room schoolhouse is designed to provide a variety of fun and developmentally appropriate learning opportunities in a setting of mixed age groups, serving children 3 years to 6 years and offering a vareity of different enrollment schedules.

name: Vineyard Montessori School
details:
The Vineyard Montessori School is a private non profit school, preschool through 6th grade, with a campus located on the beautiful island of Martha’s Vineyard.  For 35 years VMS has provided an educational environment that follows the curriculum and philosophy of Dr. Maria Montessori. We strive to guide each child in attaining fulfillment in education, community, nature, imagination and beyond.

Our daily mission in developing inde-pendent thinkers, fostering a love of learning, and reinforcing the importance of peace and re-spect for the classroom and school community (environment, friends, teachers, neighborhood) is the heart of our vocation.

Situated on a sunny lawn surrounded by trees on a rise above Easthampton Road, Sunnyside has five classrooms, each of which has big windows, child-sized tables and chairs, a reading corner, art supplies and easels, age-appropriate playthings, books, and dress-up clothes. Our roomy indoor playground with play structures allows children to stretch their legs and move about freely, regardless of the weather. On most days, children spend time outdoors in the gated outdoor play areas, and also on teacher led exploration of Sunnyside's eight acres of outdoor space.

details: The Montessori Day School (MDS) honors the uniqueness of each child and recognizes the crucial stages of development of children during the preschool years. name: All About Learning, LLC
details:
ll About Learning, LLC has been in operation for over 26 years. Our staff is experienced and our policies have grown over the years to ensure that all children are successful. We are a caring experienced center that has worked with many personalities. Our success record and our reputation are well established. 
    Our admission interview is very detailed. We give you all the information necessary for you to decide whether we are the center for your family. We believe that you should be aware of all our policies prior to enrollment. 
 AAL staff are trained to become a part of your child's support system in order to learn what makes each child succeed. Our teachers' are certified by the Department of Early Education and Care. Our flexible schedule ensures that each child is learning as well as content. Individualized attention means knowing your child's wants and needs which allows us to give every child a successful first encounter in a school setting. 
    No child is ever alone with one staff member. Our NO OPPORTUNITY POLICY means that there are no negative touching issues at our center. Imagine feeling secure as you work knowing your child is safe in all ways in our care!
    We service infant,toddler and pre school age children with academics through play as an integral part of our curriculum.
    Weekly Progress Reports monitor the growth and development of all students as well as give us our goal for each child!
  In other words NO child is left behind and all succeed!

name: MetroWest YMCA OST Program @ Hemenway
details:
Being licensed through the EEC, we are required to maintain one staff member for every thirteen children. We staff to maintain a ratio of one-to-ten.
Each program offers a healthy snack and drink. All snacks are peanut-free. Any other allergies will be addressed per specific child’s needs.  The program runs from 7am-school start and then school closing to 6pm.

We offer a vacation day program that provides activities on most of the Framingham Public School‘s closure days.  Vacation days rotate at four of our School's Out Sites. The vacation program runs 7:30am to 6:00pm. Every vacation day has a theme and most include a field trip or a visitor. About three weeks before each vacation day, a sign-up sheet will be available at all six sites to provide location and activities. All families must complete this form in order to participate even if your child is enrolled in the vacation package. Field trips are included in the cost of the vacation day.

name: Markman Children's Program
details: Markman Children’s Programs is a private nonprofit 501 (c) 3 child care agency. Our mission is to provide quality, affordable child care to all families. Established in 1972, the agency has expanded services over the years to meet the varied needs of families and currently offer programs for children ages four weeks to seventh grade in two center based sites and a Family Child Care System. Our many years of experience in providing early childhood services is a strength of our agency, giving us expertise in providing a quality program for children, and in developing supportive relationships with our families. Center based programs are open 6:30 a.m. – 6:00 p.m. and operate year round. Transportation to and from homes and area schools is provided based upon need with our agency vans and a mini-bus. Our current capacity is just over two-hundred and sixty children. Markman Children’s Programs is in a Capital Campaign, with the goal of constructing Phase II which will add 11,000 square feet to our new facility at 803 North Main Street, currently 13,000 square feet.  Phase I opened in October 2011 and added capacity for 24 preschool age children as well as housing 25 School Age children.  The Board of Directors has a goal of completing Phase II by 2016, which will allow the relocation of the remainder of our School age classrooms currently housed at 505 North Main Street and provide care for another 150 children. Congressman James McGovern, Representative Betty Poirier, and Senator Scott Brown have attended agency events to learn of our future building plans, and have pledged their support.

name: Brockton Day Nursery
details:
Our Mission:
It is the mission of Brockton Day Nursery to serve the needs of families and children by providing comprehensive child care and support services. 

Impact/Vision Statement:
For over 120 years, Brockton Day Nursery in collaboration with community partners has been  committed to ensuring that every child birth to age 13 in Brockton and surrounding communities has equal access to high quality early childhood education leading to the achievement of academic proficiency and becoming productive citizens.

BDN believes that a good start in the formative years of childhood provides children with a lasting foundation for success throughout their lives. BDN serves approximately 380 children annually (245 at a time).

We are an affiliate of the YWCA USA, the nation’s oldest and largest multicultural women’s organization working for social and economic change.

 
The YWCA is dedicated to eliminating racism, empowering women and promoting peace, justice, freedom and dignity for all.

Our three unique facilities are new, warm and inviting, and were designed and constructed specifically for children Teacher reading to infant.

Our goal is to care for your child at each stage of their development. Our dedicated and caring staff nurture and prepare your infant and toddler for pre-school. The certified teachers in our accredited preschool program will prepare your child for kindergarten. Teacher reading to children in Kindergarten class.

Kiddie Kampus even has its own certified kindergarten so your child can continue developing in our caring, exciting and educational environment. For an in depth look at Kiddie Kampus and to hear what other parents are saying about us, order our FREE DVD “Come Join our Family!” on the FREE DVD page.

We also invite you to come visit Kiddie Kampus, tour our facilities, meet with our staff and see what we have to offer.  Because choosing a child care center will be one of your major life decisions.  And we are here to help you with that decision.  Come, Join Our Family!

Guild of St. Agnes - Grove St Day Care Center
details:
Welcome to the Guild of St. Agnes, a long-standing, educational, private, non-profit child care agency. Founded in 1913 the Guild's mission is to: Provide families with quality, affordable, early childhood education and school age programs in a safe, nurturing, environment for children 4 weeks to 12 years. Today, the Guild is the largest early education and care agency in Central Massachusetts, serving approximately 1,450 children in 7 child care centers, 100+ licensed family homes and 11 school age programs.   All of these services are licensed by the  MA Department of Early Education and Care and our centers are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC), the premier designation in the United  States for identifying high quality child care services.  

The Guild offers developmentally appropriate learning environments for your child. Our programs use Teaching Strategies GOLD, which is an assessment, reporting, and curriculum planning system. This helps us to plan meaningful activities that match your child's strengths, needs, and interests, to track his or her progress on these over time and to build a strong foundation for your child to be ready to succeed in school. The Guild is very proud to have taken a leadership role in educating our teachers. All Lead Preschool Teachers hold a bachelor's degree in Early Education or a related field. Many of our teacher assistants have associate degrees or are currently enrolled in college.

In addition to our child care programs providing children with developmentally appropriate learning environments, the Guild also offers working parents year-round services to supplement  and support the childcare. These important services are: transportation, nutritious meals, and behavioral health services and referrals.  In doing so, we serve the whole child and aid you in your role as you raise your child.

details:
Our center has been serving Massachusetts families from Bedford, Burlington, Lexington, Lincoln, Concord, Carlisle, Billerica and the surrounding area since 1994.

Inch By Inch is committed to providing high quality and educational childcare in a warm and nurturing environment. We welcome children between the ages of 8 weeks to 6 years old to our Group Day Care, and children from 5 to 11 years old to our School Age Program.

Inch By Inch is open Monday through Friday from 7:00am to 6:00pm. Our center is a well maintained facility of over 8,500 square feet, licensed by the Massachusetts DEEC.
