details:
Child Works Discovery Center provides quality childcare, preschool, and after school care to families residing in Holden, MA and the surrounding areas. Children learn daily life skills, manners, and early childhood education that will help them as they grow and further their education.

Our center is dedicated to taking great care of all our children, through an interactive curriculum. Each of our caregivers are certified to take care of children, and provide a nurturing and safe learning environment. We understand how difficult it can be for parents to entrust the care of their child with other people. That is why at Child Works Discover Center, we treat the children we care for as if they were our own.

We take care of children from 6 weeks to 9-years-old. We will do our best to support your family and meet your needs. We make every effort to enhance your child's development by providing the best possible early childhood education and care in both a sensitive and stimulating environment.

details: The Greater Lowell Family YMCA’s mission is to develop and clarify human values for living based on Christian principles. We strive to create an atmosphere where children, families and adults may live to their fullest potential.  It is our goal and commitment to build strong children, families and community within the Greater Lowell area.

name: North Suburban Jewish Community Center
details: The North Suburban Jewish Community Center (NSJCC) is dedicated to developing and implementing programs for the recreational, educational, cultural, physical and social needs of infants to seniors for the Jewish and general community. The NSJCC is guided by the principles of Judaism and democracy and creates an atmosphere essential to Jewish thoughts, beliefs and values. The NSJCC is a member agency of the Jewish Federation of the North Shore.

name: Wee Folk Learning Center
details: Wee Folk Learning Center's philosophy is to provide a loving, nurturing, and safe environment while the children are away from home.

name: The Moppet School and Child Care Center
details: Maple Dene and Moppet School is a school of the 21st century, built upon values and practices found in the traditional country school: where older and younger children work and play together in a spirit of cooperation, and where caring is at the heart of everything we do. Founded by Robert D. Vieira and Patricia Kenneally, the Preschool and Child Care Center opened as Moppet School in 1984. The Kindergarten program was added in 1987, and the Elementary School in 1989. The School and property today are known as Maple Dene in honor of its past name a century ago. For close to three decades, Maple Dene and Moppet School has continued to fulfill the embodiment of their dream, vision, and commitment to provide an enriched, developmental education to children. Bob and Pat received their graduate degrees from Wheelock College, an institution highly recognized and regarded in the field of education and devoted to making the world a better place—especially for children and families. Maple Dene and Moppet School also offers PreSchool, PreKindergarten, Before & After School Care, and Elementary School for students Kindergarten through Grade Six. The school has been providing quality educational services for area families and children since 1984.

name: TOE TO TOE DANCE CENTER, INC.
The Children's Academy of Marion
details: At The Children’s Academy, our programs invite children to learn in ways that they learn best. Through hands-on guided discovery and opportunities to thrive independently, your child’s first school experience will be one that excites him/her to learn more. At The Children’s Academy our teachers provide activities that keep each day exciting and your child will be in a safe environment that he or she looks forward to attending. Children are placed in age appropriate classrooms where activities are designed with your child in mind. Our HighScope curriculum encourages children to be themselves and be individuals, ready to face new experiences head on. Children’s Academy uses the energy of your child and directs it in a positive way for learning and discovery. Our teachers form bonds with each child to establish a strong sense of security. We strive to maintain ongoing communication with families and work as a team to accomplish established goals. The Children’s Academy uses every moment of your child’s day to embrace new learning experiences. With opportunities for outside play, individual discovery, one-on-one bonding time, as well as large and small group interactions, your child will establish the building blocks for a lifetime of achievement.

name: Westfield Child Center

We aim to provide a safe, loving, nurturing, and supportive atmosphere for the children, families, and staff. We strive to build a sense of belonging while respecting each other's individuality, diversity, and uniqueness. We encourage all of the children, families, and staff who walk through our doors to work as a team. We believe that teamwork makes the future brighter.

Side By Side Preschool, Inc.
details: Whether you want your child to socialize with others of the same age or want your kids to get ready for kindergarten, Side by Side Preschool & Child Care Center offers programs you seek for your child. With our personal attention and quality care, you can rest assured that your child receives nothing but the best at our child care center. Side by Side Preschool & Child Care Center in Chicopee, Massachusetts, we provide a small classroom setting to promote personal attention for every child. With the flexible schedules, experienced and caring staff, Side by Side Preschool & Child Care Center is sure to have the program that fits your families needs.

name: Metro North Children's Learning Center, Inc.
details: The Children's Learning Center strives to enhance the cultural, physical, and social well being of preschool and school age children and their families.  Our program is committed to developing a sense of community through teaching values that promote understanding and tolerance.  We make all services available regardless of race, religion, cultural heritage, political beliefs, national origin, disability, marital status or sexual orientation. The Children's Learning Center believes in creating a setting where children flourish as individuals, are actively involved in their learning, and engage in activities that encourage individual growth.  Our teachers create a climate that encourages discovery as well as providing an environment that promotes the learning of all age appropriate skills.  We provide a setting that enhances children's natural curiosity and challenges children's intellectual, physical, and social abilities.  We believe that education is a lifelong process and begins with a strong foundation.  To accomplish this, we provide enriching curriculum with the goal of promoting the well-rounded individual.

name: KidZone, Inc.
details: It is the philosophy of Kidzone Child Care and Educational Center Inc. That early childhood should be a time of fun, warmth, security, exploring and discovery. Kidzone Inc. Will strive to nurture and encourage these qualities in our students.

name: SHED, Inc.
details:
The Before School programs open at 7:00 am. Enrollment is on
a rolling basis throughout the year. Drop in care is available once approved
by the Kid's Club office.
***Drop in care can not be an option on delayed openings because of
staffing ratios or unless approved by the Kid's Club office.
Before School is a quiet, relaxed time to enjoy:
• time with friends & teachers
• planned curriculum guided by teachers
• open exploration & play which includes:  art, building, reading, games, gym time & outdoor time
The children may bring breakfast if they wish.  At some schools, breakfast is available for a fee.  At approximately 8:20am, children may join friends on the playground as they arrive for school.
The overall philosophy, both Before School and After School, is to help children become independent, self-reliant, resourceful, capable of reasoning and thinking, able to problem solve and make good choices.  Kid's Club is a place to learn social skills, conflict resolution and problem solving; to be ready for the challenges that face them as they confront life's issues.

"Kid's Club After School is located at 65 Phillips St. The main childcare rooms are developmental in design, allowing children to make decisions within defined limits. The classrooms include the following areas: reading and group time, computer and homework, art, sensory, sand and water, science and writing, manipulative, games, blocks or construction and dramatic play. Activities outside of these areas are also offered, such as cooking, sports, music, movement, and carpentry. Programming allows for free play, homework choice, quiet time, snack and outdoor play.

The program follows the Andover Public School calendar. Kid's Club is closed during the summer (but has a summer program), most holidays and December vacation week. It is open during February and April school vacation weeks, based on the needs of the current user group. It will remain open on snow days (depending on the severity of the storm) and in-service days.

The Kid's Club program has 200 slots. Actual enrollment is based on the distribution of slots throughout the week. Group size varies depending on the activity; ratios are maintained at approximately 10:1. The staff reflects a diversity of training and experience in early childhood education and childcare. Staff development and training opportunities are offered throughout the year.

The teaching staff offers conference time (at parents request) for a more thorough discussion of a child's progress. Written progress reports will be maintained in each child's record and are available for parental review with a staff member. This communication between parents and teachers is essential in creating a program that not only meets parents' needs, but also provides an enriching and comfortable environment for the children."

name: Hancock Nursery School, Inc.
details:
Hancock Nursery School provides a developmentally and age appropriate preschool experience for the whole child. We promote mastery of social, emotional, physical and cognitive skills according to the individual pace and style of each child. Our teaching goals are aimed at the development of healthy self-esteem, independence, and respect for self and others.

The philosophy of Hancock Nursery School is guided by the belief that young children learn best through play. As such, our curriculum encourages the exploration and discovery of different ideas, feelings, and interests during play and through a variety of media. We promote self-expression and growth through music, movement, arts, crafts, and pretend play.

Overall, the school takes a developmental approach to teaching. There are three main goals for every age group:

    To help children make a happy transition between home and school through nurturance and positive guidance.
    To expose children to a variety of developmentally appropriate experiences and encourage creativity through exploration, questioning, and experimentation.
    To help children begin the process of socialization with peers and other adults and to introduce the child to the art of negotiation and communication.

Another important goal of our curriculum is to help children learn acceptable behavior. No child is ever permitted to harm another, either emotionally or physically, and both self-respect and respect for others are strongly encouraged. We reinforce positive behavior with praise, guide children toward constructive activity with re-direction, and set a few clear limits and rules for safety and respect for others. We work on solving problems together through conversation and compromise and we help children learn to talk over differences to help develop respect and empathy for the feelings of others.

name: Muddy Brook Elementary School Head Start
Ludlow Recreation After School Child Care Program
New England Montessori School
details:
New England Montessori School (NEMS) has been running a successful learning environment since 2001.

Throughout the years, we have implemented traditional influences into our Montessori curriculum. Our classrooms are filled with Montessori materials as well as Traditional Learning materials. NEMS also implements creative monthly themes to help extend the learning experience beyond the basics.

As true Montessorians, we believe in maintaining small ratios of 7 to 1 or fewer, allowing for the individual attention each child needs. In addition, we have "community time" between classrooms. Each classroom has whole group activities and lessons, as well as whole group recess.

The primary goal of NEMS is to meet the needs of love, warmth and security in the young child, by treating them with respect and understanding. Additionally, by setting realistic and consistent limits, the children are given the freedom to explore an environment that meets their developmental needs.

name: The New Nursery Sch of United Church
details: The New Nursery School of the United Church of Christ, Norwell, was founded in 1977. The school is owned by the Church and is operated by a Board of Directors, made up of parents of current students and Church members. This board, which meets monthly, has the responsibility for all matters affecting the development and management of the school; fiscal man-agement, establishing policies, fundraising, Director management and evaluation, school calendar, among other managerial duties. Anyone interested in exploring board membership should speak with the Director or a current board member, whose names appear at the end of this book. The school is licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care (EEC) of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts. The role of New Nursery School is not to instruct children in any particular religious belief, but rather to help them experience what it means to be a unique person with individual talents and gifts. The New Nursery School does not discriminate on the basis of religion, national origin, cultural heritage, race, gender, age, political beliefs, sexual orientation, marital status, toilet training status or disability in its admissions or hiring practices. It is our goal to recognize and respect each person’s unique background.

name: Windmill Country Day School
details:
Windmill Country Day School is a private early childhood school established twenty-five years ago to meet the educational needs of families with young children. It is licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care.

Philosophy - Windmill Country Day School strives for the development of the whole child - intellectual, emotional, social, and physical. Our objective is to help your child achieve "a measure of success each day" in a nurturing, learning environment,. We believe that children learn at different speeds and in different ways. Our programs are adapted to the needs of each individual child. This is achieved in an open classroom setting which is structured enough to set limits, but flexible enough to promote creativity, interest, and challenge.

Role of the Parents - Parents are welcome visitors in their child's classroom. Parents are invited to participate in their child's learning and development by attending family activities, sharing their talents and culture, and taking advantage of daily opportunities to communicate with the staff. There is a resource lending library with books, magazines, and informative hand-outs for parents as well as a bookshelf for children.

name: The Preschool at Temple Emanuel
details: The Preschool at Temple Emanuel has provided children meaning and joy through play for more than 35 years. We create an environment that encourages children to learn through discovery. Our commitment to this growth is seen in our rich, developmentally appropriate play-based curriculum. We provide experiences for children that promote learning in the academic domains of literacy, math and science as well as the more traditional early learning areas of cognitive, social, emotional, physical and language development. We meet all children at their own developmental level, nurture their growth and foster excitement of their discoveries.

name: Little Angels Day Care / LA Adventure Club
Bridgeview Montessori School
details:
Bridgeview Montessori School, guided by the educational philosophy of Dr. Maria Montessori, provides a child-centered learning environment in which students develop a love of learning what will sustain them throughout their lives.

Our goals include: the development of the whole child, emotionally, physically and intellectually through creativity, courage, passion, personal responsibility and respect for self, others, and the world in which we live.

We encourage our students to approach their work and their world with a sense of wonder, curiosity and the excitement of discovery. We value diversity and, above all, we value a compassionate and peaceful community.

name: Knoll-Edge Too!
details:
Parents visiting Knoll-Edge often ask, what is your educational philosophy? People also want to know on which theorists we base our curriculum, our interactions with children, and our style of child guidance.Happy children at Knoll-Edge Knoll-Edge follows the Constructivist Theory of Early Childhood Development. This is best explained by referring to two theorists from whom we draw our thoughts.

Vgotsky believes, and we agree, that children learn better in collaboration with an adult. This does not mean that the adult is teaching a child how to perform a task, but that the process of engagement with the adult enables the child to refine his or her thinking or performance to make it more effective. The development of language and the articulation of ideas are central to learning and development. "Stretch-learners" is a model for this theory. We stretch the mind of the child by exposing him/her to a multitude of curricula presented in an appropriate manner.

We also believe, as J. Bruner theorized, that learning is an active process in which learners construct new ideas based upon their current knowledge. The child selects and transforms information, constructs hypotheses and makes decisions relying on a cognitive structure to do so. Cognitive structure provides meaning and organization to experiences and allows the child to go beyond the information given.

Knoll-Edge draws from the best of these philosophers and therefore is often compared with the Reggio Emilia philosophy, which is a combination of theories. Central to this philosophy is the image of the child being full of wonder and curiosity, and capable of co-constructing, with the teachers, his or her own knowledge. The central act of teachers is to arrange the environment, and offer appropriate materials, so that the child constantly explores, discovers and creates meaning.

The Reggio Emilia motto is "nothing without joy". We at Knoll-Edge have adopted that motto as well!

name: Orchard Head Start
details:
Our MISSION
Holyoke • Chicopee • Springfield Head Start, Inc. is committed to providing low-income children and their families with a Beacon of Hope and source of support for a brighter future. We strive to do so by providing high quality comprehensive child development services to enrolled children and empowering families to achieve stability in their home environment.

Our CORE VALUES
Excellence • Respect • Diversity • Communication Team Work • Flexibility • Dedication • Shared Vision

Our HISTORY
Since 1965 HCS Head Start Inc. has been providing high-quality early childhood education services for children and families in cities and towns located in Western Massachusetts, including Holyoke, Chicopee, Springfield, Ludlow, Palmer, and Granby. Head Start provides a solid foundation for children to gain necessary skills to enter kindergarten and to be successful in life. Our centers are fully licensed by the MA Department of Early Education and Care. For a complete list of the cities and towns we serve, contact us at (413)788-6522.

name: Growing Minds Preschools
details:
At Growing Minds Preschool we believe the proverb states the truth. We want every child to develop a healthy sense of self-esteem and self-image; a positive attitude; and a foundation that will encourage enjoyable learning experiences now and to carry with them into the future.
"We teach our students to learn & understand their material not memorize it..."
~It's about quality; not quantity~

name: Pine Village Preschool
details:
Our Mission is to educate and nurture each child’s individuality within a culturally diverse, bilingual community so that every child develops a true passion for learning and an ability to engage in any environment and community.

Our CORE values define our choices and hold the truths of what is most important to us as an organization. These four elements cannot stand alone within Pine Village.  We need each of them to be present in our schools and our classrooms, as well as within the organization as a whole. When these four elements exist our choices are strong and our approach is clear.

name: Raynham Park & Recreation Dept Before and After School Program
YMCA Pre-K
details:
The YMCA of Greater Westfield offers a variety of child care programs; Preschool and Before and After School Care. All of our child care is state certified.

Our Before School program runs from 7:00AM-9:00AM and includes games, sports, arts and crafts, as well as homework help. Our After School program runs from 2:30PM-6:00PM and includes homework tutoring, STEAM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts and Math activities), sports,  cooking, games, arts & crafts and more!

Full day, half day, snow day and vacation day care is also available. Children currently enrolled in our Before and After School programs receive a discounted rate. Extended care, in the event of two hour school delays and early releases due to inclement weather, is also included in your weekly fee.

name: Prime Time at Crocker Farm Elementary School
Kidbridge Learning Centers, LLC
details:
In the early years of a child's life, the child is forming his self-image and positioning himself to succeed in his exploration of his environment. He is developing social, emotional, physical and intellectual tools for his life long journey. Early childhood education begins with providing children with the self-confidence and the skill sets necessary to explore, process, question, challenge, and extend their environment.

Our vision is to bridge the gap for the parent and child as child transitions from his home environment to a new world.

Our mission is to provide a framework that will support learning new connections and developing new relationships in a safe and nurturing enviornment.

name: Noah's Ark Preschool
details: Noah's Ark Preschool fosters the social, emotional, physical, and intellectual growth of each child within a safe, positive, and consistent environment. Noah's Ark Preschool was established on the foundation that young children learn best through play, and our classroom environment as well as our daily schedule promotes this philosophy. Our program expects to partner with families in providing their children with support, care, and developmentally appropriate learning experiences.

details:
Little Treasures Schoolhouse is a family-like community of learning. We provide Preschool, Pre-kindergarten, Kindergarten Transition and after-school programs serving children from ages 2.9 through 5th grade.

Our excellent teaching staff is what makes Little Treasures the outstanding school it is. The combination of our fabulous teachers, low staff turnover, low student teacher ratio, warm and inviting classrooms, and beautiful outdoor play yard provide your child with the best possible environment in which to nurture their love of learning. We know we are often a child’s first experience with formal education. It is our goal to ensure that each child has a positive school experience, and therefore the best possible foundation for a lifetime of learning.

Children learn through play. Creative, well designed classrooms and lesson plans will encourage your child to explore the world around them, all while having fun. Our teachers thoughtfully provide the opportunities to develop self-confidence, self-esteem, cognitive skills, social skills, gross and fine motor skills. The children engage in all of this while having fun and forming friendships that last a lifetime. The bonds formed here (between teachers and students as well as children with their peers) are serendipity at its sweetest!

Please take some time to browse through our website to see just some of the highlights of our school. Feel free to contact us if you are interested in receiving information or scheduling a tour.

name: MVYMCA A/NA AFTERSCHOOL AT FAITH LUTHERAN
Little Footprints Learning Center
details: Our mission is to create a fully rounded, high quality and truly enjoyable growth experience for young children through hands-on experiences, play, exploration, and discovery. Little Footprints is an environment-based program for care and learning. We believe that the two are inseparable. Children learn from the entire experience the day provides. The way time and space are planned, the furnishings, the equipment and materials, and all the ways adults and children behave, “teach” the child what the world is like, how it works, what the child is capable of, and his/her place in it.

name: S.M.O.C. Child Care
details: Head Start provides comprehensive early education and support services for children ages three to five and their families. In addition to providing center-based and home-based preschool education, the program provides supportive services in the areas of health and dental care, nutrition, special education, parent skill workshops and social services. Children are provided with a daily lunch and breakfast or snack, which meet all federal, and state nutrition guidelines. Door-to-door transportation is provided at many of the centers. Classrooms typically operate from September through May, Mondays through Fridays and from 8:30am to 2pm.

name: College Bound Dorchester Early Education at Dorchester Place
Guild of St Agnes
details:
Welcome to the Guild of St. Agnes, a long-standing, educational, private, non-profit child care agency. Founded in 1913 the Guild's mission is to: Provide families with quality, affordable, early childhood education and school age programs in a safe, nurturing, environment for children 4 weeks to 12 years. Today, the Guild is the largest early education and care agency in Central Massachusetts, serving approximately 1,450 children in 7 child care centers, 100+ licensed family homes and 11 school age programs.   All of these services are licensed by the  MA Department of Early Education and Care and our centers are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC), the premier designation in the United  States for identifying high quality child care services.  

The Guild offers developmentally appropriate learning environments for your child. Our programs use Teaching Strategies GOLD, which is an assessment, reporting, and curriculum planning system. This helps us to plan meaningful activities that match your child's strengths, needs, and interests, to track his or her progress on these over time and to build a strong foundation for your child to be ready to succeed in school. The Guild is very proud to have taken a leadership role in educating our teachers. All Lead Preschool Teachers hold a bachelor's degree in Early Education or a related field. Many of our teacher assistants have associate degrees or are currently enrolled in college.

In addition to our child care programs providing children with developmentally appropriate learning environments, the Guild also offers working parents year-round services to supplement  and support the childcare. These important services are: transportation, nutritious meals, and behavioral health services and referrals.  In doing so, we serve the whole child and aid you in your role as you raise your child.

name: Franciscan Family Child Care Center
details:
The Franciscan Family Child Care Center is located on the Hospital campus with ready access to Hospital resources as needed. The Center serves children ages 8 weeks – 6 years, regardless of race, sex, religion, cultural heritage, political beliefs or disability.

The Center originally opened to serve the child care needs of employees of The Franciscan Hospital for Children, but in 1994, opened its services to all families. Today, we are proud to help children develop the skills they need to prepare for success in school and beyond, while supporting working families striving to balance the demands of work and family. All teachers are certified in First Aid and CPR, and are Criminal Offender Record Information (CORI) checked prior to hiring.

Classes are divided by age group, and curriculum varies based on the children’s developmental stage.

details: We are a proud small center with a low student per teacher ratio. Offering an attentive and nurturing environment. Small Steps is an EEC certified preschool center with qualified teachers and staff.

name: Sunshine School of Groton, Inc.
details:
Sunshine School's goal and purpose is to provide a happy and positive first school experience for every child that attends. To achieve this goal we focus on key developmental areas for growth in early childhood.  ﻿

﻿​We understand that children go through certain stages of growth and development, but each progresses through these stages at his/her own pace and has his/her own strengths & needs. We build on these strengths and meet these needs by providing a wide variety of both teacher-directed and child-driven activities.  Every child is coached and encouraged to reach their full potential.

​Sunshine School has been providing quality preschool programs for children and their families in the central mass area for over 10 years.  We are licensed by the office of Early Education and Care (EEC).  We are privately owned and operated and are housed in the addition of the First Parish Church (1 Powder House Road) on 119 (Main St) next to Lawrence Academy in the village of Groton Ma. (978) 448-6714.

name: Waters Preschool
details:
Waters Early Learning Center was created based on our love for God, our love for children,  love of education and the joy and importance of giving all three to your child.

We offer unique, individualized Learning programs fostering whole child Development from 6 weeks – 6 years of age.

name: Happy Roots Learning Center
details: At Happy Roots Learning Center we work to create a respectful, calm, encouraging environment for each child. We focus on social and emotional growth and development; as well as cognitive development.  It is our goal to help each child develop meaningful relationships, and friendships; learning how to truly connect, and respect one another.  We strive to guide each child toward their full potential, on the path to becoming a productive, supportive, kind, and considerate member of our society, and  our environment.

name: Imajine That University @ Imajine That
details:
The Imajine That Museum is a first of its kind family and child interactive museum where human potential has no boundaries. Our unique 12,000 square foot play space offers an environment where families can create and learn together in a safe and educational manner. Imajine That's Imagination Stations" include a child sized Whole Foods® grocery store, a life-size dinosaur climbing structure, Between the Lions® literacy area, Peep and the Big Wide World® Science Station, Lowell General Circle of Health Doctors Office play area, and an arts and crafts area.

In addition to the museum, Imajine That University (ITU) offers full-day family engagement preschool and Infant/Toddler programs located at the Riverwalk Lawrence and at the Rollins School in Lawrence. Imajine That also offers extended learning day programs in Boston Public Schools.

Massachusetts’s residents can find Imajinators (Imajine That staff) in their local libraries and town events throughout the year where they conduct hands-on activities for children and families to engage in learning and fun.

Imajine That has been awarded #24 of the Pacesetters Growing Private Companies in 2014 with the Boston Business Journal and was ranked #1 with Michael Porters 2014 Inner City 100 Icons of Industry Growth for Arts Entertainment and Recreation.

name: A Childs View Early Learning Center IV
details: A Child’s View Early Learning Center is licensed by the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care. We are a high quality infant, toddler, preschool child day care program with locations in both Quincy and Dorchester. We provide children with a safe, secure, and loving learning environment. A Child’s View Early Learning Center offers full-time child day care for children ages 3 months thru 7 years of age. We are open Monday thru Friday from 7:00 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. We believe it is important for children to be in a consistent, stable and predictable environment. We believe in educating the whole child, and stress physical, emotional social and cognitive development. We provide the foundations necessary for your child to develop the tools to grow and succeed in life. We work together with families to help them deal with everyday problems as well as to celebrate individual milestones with them. We have a good relationship with our parents. Our staff will let parents know how their child’s day was. We also like to hear from parents how the child’s day/night has been. We work together as a team with families to be sure each child is set up to have a successful day.

name: A Dream Come True Learning Centers
details:
A Place To Grow Too Daycare and Learning Centers are based upon the principles of developmentally appropriate practice. Our goal is to give each child a warm environment that encourages the development of socialization skills, independence, and a positive self-image. Our experienced teaching staff embraces the view that each child is a unique person with an individual pattern and timing of social, physical, and intellectual development.

Teachers manifest their respect for children by encouraging them to think for themselves, to make decisions, to work towards their own solutions, and express their own ideas and feelings. We recognize and foster an active partnership between home and school.

name: Active Learners Preschool West
details: Active Learners recognizes the importance of early childhood education, and employs various programs to assist cognitive and social development for children within Norton, Massachusetts, and the surrounding communities. Unlike other private preschools, our facility focuses on the independent learning experience of each child.

name: Alphabet Academy
details:
Our goal is to provide a healthy, safe and learning environment in which children can grow and develop with the nurturing support and guidance of our teachers, staff and parents. It is our commitment to provide the highest quality early education and care program to children and families, regardless of their ethnic or religious background.
Our Philosophy at Alphabet Academy: 
    Focus on your child’s unique abilities and potential
    Provide activities that foster growth socially, emotionally, cognitively, and physically
    Engage qualified staff with a caring, nurturing, loving supportive attitude
    Create opportunities for you to be involved in all aspects of your child’s care

name: Amazing Grace Kids
details: Children learn by doing.  At Amazing Grace Kids, children explore, create, interact and discover, in a thoughtfully prepared environment full of interesting materials.  Using this hands-on, play based approach, literacy, music, art, science, math and social studies are woven into our daily curriculum, which follows the Massachusetts State Guidelines. Children also learn best when they feel safe and loved.  With teacher support, our students learn to communicate and negotiate with peers and adults, equipping them with the social skills that are foundational for a lifetime of interacting with others. Faith in God underlies all that we do – at Amazing Grace Kids, children learn about how God made our wonderful world and that He loves us. Teachers pray for the school and for families on a regular basis.  We work in partnership with our host, Trinity Covenant Church, to provide this Christian preschool experience to families in Lexington and the surrounding towns. Amazing Grace Kids was born of a dream of teachers Amy Hinrichs and Ellie Beatty to offer quality Christian preschool education to Boston area families. Incorporated as a non-profit school in 2010, Amazing Grace Kids began as a “Parents’ Day Out” program offered to children one day a week. By September of 2012 Amazing Grace Kids was licensed by the Mass Department of Early Education and Care as a preschool, offering classes three days a week. Enrollment has grown steadily, and as of September of 2013, we offer two classrooms and are open every weekday.  Amazing Grace Kids admits students of any race, color, gender, creed, cultural heritage, ethnic origin, and disability, to all the rights, privileges, programs, and activities generally accorded or made available to students of the school.

name: The Arbors Kids@Commonwealth Academy
details: Commonwealth Academy is an co-ed college preparatory day and boarding school located on the former campus of the MacDuffie School in downtown Springfield, MA. For the 2013-2014 academic year we will educate 4th-9th graders. Commonwealth Academy provides each student with the opportunity to uncover their passion in life, and shape their future through college preparatory scholarship, community, and entrepreneurial engagement.

name: Bellas Manitas Learning Center
details: Welcome to Bellas Manitas: A Bilingual Learning Center in Somerville, MA. Bellas Manitas was started because we saw a need to serve a wonderful diverse community. At Bellas Manitas, "There is a beautiful place for you and your child", where children explore language, art, music and imagination.At Bellas Manitas, your child will enjoy and learn the Spanish language as well as academics taught in English (Math, Science, Music, Art, Social Studies and Reading). The exposure your child will get through carefully planned lessons will help them to grow cognitively, socially, physically and in language skills. They will love it!Your child is very special, and it is our goal to attend to all of his/her needs - personal and developmental. You are an important part of our community. It is a privilege to be a part of you and your child's lives.

name: Briarwood Child Academy-Seekonk Inc
details:
Our highly-qualified and dedicated team of early childhood professionals care and educate children from six weeks to six years of age.

Through an innovative play-based curriculum and daily enrichment experiences, the Briarwood Child Academy prepares each child to become "tomorrow's leaders."

We know that every parent wants the best of everything for their child. This is what drives our daily interactions, experiences and programs!

name: Brockton Preschool Academy d/b/a Steps Academy
details:
Li'l Steps Academy provides a secure and educational environment for children, a place for kids to be kids all while blooming into responsible, respectful and contributing members of society.

We want each and every child to have the opportunity to grow physically, emotionally, socially and intellectually by playing, exploring, and learning with others in a fun, safe, and healthy environment

name: Cape Cod Conservatory of Music & Arts Preschool at West Barnstabl
Cape Cod Conservatory of Music & Arts Preschool -Falmouth
The Carousel of Learning, Inc.
details:
Thank you for your interest in The Carousel of Learning! Our website is a great first step to learning more about our strengths and commitment to education excellence. The Carousel of Learning accepts students as young as 5 weeks to 8 years old. 

 At The Carousel of Learning we recognize the importance of a quality early childhood experience for all children and we value the partnership with families. We realize that children learn both at home and at school, therefore our program is family focused and facilitates child learning in the development of their language, physical abilities, social/emotional awareness, and content areas like literacy, math, social studies, science, and artistic expression.

name: Champions Extended Learning @ Center Pepin Elementary School
details:
With more than 30 years experience in the design and delivery of engaging out-of-school-time programs, we know that Champions works – for kids, parents and teachers. Our dedicated team of early learning and school-age education experts have applied the very best in educational philosophies to the Champions approach to learning which focuses first on a quality education. Our programs, from our learning environment to our curriculum to our relationships with the kids, also reinforce 21st century learning goals.

We meet all aspects of a child’s development with fun activities like arts, sports, reading and science exploration, all while aligning our programming to meet your district objectives and even individual school goals. By organizing our programs around your needs, we make it easy to collaborate with Champions to deliver the best fun learning environment for families in your local community, while our operational expertise and responsive service gives you a hassle-free experience.

At the end of the day, everybody gets what they need. You can ensure that children continue to learn beyond the school bell, parents get a safe and convenient place for their child while they’re at work, and children enjoy fun activities with friends that help them learn in non-traditional ways.

name: Choi's World Tae Kwon Do, Inc.
details:
The World Tae Kwon Do Training Center will provide a safe and nurturing environment in which students respect and appreciate each other while training together regardless of race, nationality, or religion.  Our students learn and grow intellectually, physically, and emotionally through developmentally appropriate lessons.

An important quality of our programs is the ability to maintain active, open and informative communication between students, parents, and staff.  We will provide parents with notices and/or calendars of upcoming special events, and other pertinent information.

We encourage all students to speak with the instructors if any problems/schedule changes (i.e., illness, appointments, etc.) should arise.  It is especially helpful if there are any significant events taking place in the student¡Ë¢ç?s life (positive or not) that our staff/director is informed so we may respond appropriately to the student¡Ë¢ç?s needs.

College Bound Dorchester out of school time at Holland Elementary
Commonwealth Family Childcare, Inc.
address: c/o Taunton High School 50 Williams Street
details:
CFC Inc. assists families in accessing subsidized child care in licensed Family Child Care (FCC) programs, while promoting quality care through our support of FCC Educators.

CFC also supports FCC Educators sub-contracted with our agency. We value early childhood Educators looking to advance professionally within their career and so we offer assistance with
• EEC Licensing & Regulation assistance
• CDA achievement
• NAFCC accreditation

CFC staffs are fully aware of EEC regulation changes and requirements, the Professional Qualifications Registry, and Quality Rating and Improvement System. Educators contracted with CFC Inc receive ongoing support to comply with all of these efforts.

name: Congregation Beth Elohim Early Learning Center
details:
CBE Early Learning Center is a preschool offering extended, traditional daycare hours in Acton, Massachusetts. Our curriculum encourages intellectual and social-emotional exploration, community-building and mutual respect, as interpreted through the lens of Jewish wisdom and values. Children are encouraged to express their interests and abilities through play, language, music and art. Numbers, letters, science and nature are an integral part of the everyday experience. We celebrate the fullness of living in a multicultural world and celebrate heritage through songs, holidays and festivals, story, dance and language. While proudly Jewish, we welcome families of all faiths and cultures to join our loving and closely-knit community.

The program serves children 15 months through 5 years with part- and full-day childcare options, school-year, school-year extended and summer programs.  The school attracts families from Acton, Boxborough, Maynard, Concord, Westford, and other surrounding communities.

name: Cushing before and after school Care program
Devotion Primary Extended Day II
details:
The Devotion Extended Day Program is a tuition based recreationally focused program for children in grades K-4 who attend the Edward Devotion School in Brookline, Massachusettes. Program hours are from school dismissal until 5:45 pm daily. We operate for longer hours on the 8 early release days as noted on the school calendar. There is also full-day care during some school vacations for which there are separate fees. The program is staffed by a group of experienced early childhood professionals. Programming is developmental and includes arts and crafts, gross motor activities in a gym and outdoors, board games, dramatic play and facilitated peer interactions. There is supervised homework time for third and fourth graders and a curriculum that is appropriate for older children. 

DPEDP is licensed by The Departent of Early Education and Care through the State of Massachusetts. Information on EEC school age regulations can be found on the EEC website.

name: Dipody Doo Child Learning and Development
details: At Dipody Doo we offer child care for Infants, Toddlers, Preschool & School Age. Our experienced educators provide a fun and enriched learning environment. We are committed to providing a supportive atmosphere for you and your child.  We are licensed by The Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care (EEC). The educational program is based on sound principles of child development. Our goals are to give children a sense of self worth by helping them develop at their own individual pace while learning basic skills. We want the children to feel confident and secure enough to explore and grow in a stimulating educational and social environment.

name: Eastern Ave. Head Start
details:
Our MISSION
Holyoke • Chicopee • Springfield Head Start, Inc. is committed to providing low-income children and their families with a Beacon of Hope and source of support for a brighter future. We strive to do so by providing high quality comprehensive child development services to enrolled children and empowering families to achieve stability in their home environment.

Our CORE VALUES
Excellence • Respect • Diversity • Communication Team Work • Flexibility • Dedication • Shared Vision

Our HISTORY
Since 1965 HCS Head Start Inc. has been providing high-quality early childhood education services for children and families in cities and towns located in Western Massachusetts, including Holyoke, Chicopee, Springfield, Ludlow, Palmer, and Granby. Head Start provides a solid foundation for children to gain necessary skills to enter kindergarten and to be successful in life. Our centers are fully licensed by the MA Department of Early Education and Care. For a complete list of the cities and towns we serve, contact us at (413)788-6522.

name: Family Service Association-Letourneau After School Day Care
details: Every child deserves access to a healthy, safe, productive and nurturing environment. We believe that day care services must be administered by qualified personnel who promote positive social behavior through developmentally appropriate and stimulating activities that meet the educational, social, emotional and recreational needs of our families.

name: Flying Swings Daycare, LLC
details: Here at Flying Swings Daycare we reinforce each child’s individual growth through fun, playful activities to promote cognitive development, language and communication skills, emotional and social development, and fine and gross motor skills.

name: The Growing Room of Berlin
details:
Growing Room offers an inviting school environment that is comfortable, secure and clean. We offer full and part time care for children ages 4 weeks through 8 years old. Call us today for a tour! 978-838-0009

Our “Growing up on our Block” language-based curriculum includes weekly themes, letters, colors, concepts, skills, computer instruction, phonics, reading, writing, hands-on math and science instruction, the best in children’s literature, family-style dining, and self-help skills encouragement.

Our children are loved and treated with respect and nurtured through personal relationships with professional, loving teachers who have a genuine interest in educating children.  Our teachers are certified by the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care and are trained in CPR/First Aid.

Growing Up on our Block” curriculum prepares your child for success in elementary school by using the whole-child approach to education.  We strive to provide the best educational experiences that will foster each child’s language, cognitive, physical, and social-emotional health.

name: Hatherly Before and After School Care Program
Hill Institute Kindergarten
details: Hill Institute has been on the cutting edge of education since its inception in 1876 as the first free Kindergarten in the United States. Over the years it has progressed to keep in tune with the latest thinking and offers a curriculum that keeps it at the forefront of early childhood education. While still providing a half-day Kindergarten program, the classroom at Hill Institute is a treasure of academic offerings. We provide an integrated curriculum where reading and writing occur across subjects. Science, mathematics, language arts and social studies are balanced with exploratory play to provide an atmosphere where children grow and learn. Science and math exploration are at the core of our program and involve continuous hands-on discovery lessons. Children are exposed to a wide variety of literature. As they develop their literacy skills they take their first steps as readers and writers, writing and illustrating many books throughout the year. An outside specialist comes to Hill Kindergarten weekly and brings with her an extensive expertise in music. Our Kindergarten provides a dynamic atmosphere with multi-levels of teaching to keep classroom learning moving at a steady pace.  In addition to our interactive science-based curriculum we offer smaller class sizes and individualized personal attention. If you are seeking a program that will give your child the best foundation possible for their continued education, we invite you to consider exploring our historic yet progressive, well-established and respected institution.

name: Imajine That @ Condon Elementary School

The Imajine That Museum is a first of its kind family and child interactive museum where human potential has no boundaries. Imajine That's Imagination Stations" include a child sized Whole Foods® grocery store, a life-size dinosaur climbing structure, Between the Lions® literacy area, Peep and the Big Wide World® Science Station, Lowell General Circle of Health Doctors Office play area, and an arts and crafts area.

Latchkey at the Arlington School
details:
Throughout our history, we have maintained an ideal of supporting children and their families within a larger circle that includes their neighborhoods, schools, cultural groups, and employers along with local, state, and federal agencies. We strive to provide the highest quality of education and care for children by:
    offering rich programming that addresses the intellectual, social, emotional, and physical development of children.
    assessing the development of children in all programs; developing individual goals based on the results.
    implementing special services on-site as needed; speech/language therapy, occupational therapy, physical therapy, and mental health therapy are available.
    employing nurturing, highly qualified teacher-caregivers and providing ongoing professional development.
    holding ourselves to the highest standards of competency by holding licenses for all programs, including family provider homes, from the Massachusetts Department of Early Education and Care and operating accredited preschool/kindergarten centers.
    sharing best teaching practices within Community Day Learning and with our award-winning affiliates, Community Day Charter Public Schools.

name: Laugh Learn and Grow School Age Care
The Learning Tree Daycare Preschool LLC
details: The Learning Tree Daycare & Preschool is comprised of passionate staff members whose goal is to provide your children with the highest education, care, and safety. We keep our children busy with learning and fun activities throughout their day! We have two playgrounds outside and will have an indoor playground in February 2015! All teachers have a background in teaching children and are certified through the state of Massachusetts, CPR and First Aid Trained, and have to fulfill 20 hours of additional training each year.

name: Little Bear Learn and Care
details:
Little Bear Learn & Care provides high quality childcare in the Greater Easthampton Area. Our program offers a warm, family and school community atmosphere.

Our educators inspire learning through play, and build valuable social and emotional skills for successful learning. Young children develop healthy communication skills through basic sign language, modeling, and role playing.

Families and staff of Little Bear value the importance of the critical brain-building first five years of life.

name: Little Busy Bodies Child Care Center LLC
Little Red Schoolhouse
details:
The Little Red Schoolhouse is a family owned and operated preschool for children ages 2.9 - 5 years of age. 

Our goals for learning at The Little Red Schoolhouse:

-  A flexible learning environment for children of mixed ages and various levels of development.

-  A setting where children can learn both individually and group through center choices, teacher directed activities and free play.

-  Kindergarten Readiness program to develop math, science, language and social skills .

-  Circle time - Puzzles - Arts/crafts - Outdoor play - Story time - Creative play - Water/Sand Play

We have our program structured in a way that it is beneficial to both the young learner and the pre-kindergartener.

name: Magical Beginnings Academy
details:
At Magical Beginnings Inc. we encourage children to explore and express their creativeness to help strengthen a child’s positive self-image. Children will interact with each other while learning to share, take turns, and cooperate through play. Our goal is to provide a daycare where parents feel comfortable leaving their children and to encourage parents to be involved in their child’s day.

We invite our neighbors in Stoneham, Lynn, Lynnfield, Reading, Topsfield, Boxford and nearby communities in MA to visit our Magical Beginnings child care centers in Peabody, Middleton or Wakefield.

name: The Magical Years Early Learning Center Inc
details:
Our purpose is to provide the highest quality early childhood programs in a secure, nurturing and stimulating environment. The Magical Years serves the physical, emotional and intellectual needs of the child and their families. We meet these goals with our age-appropriate curriculum, our highly qualified staff, state-of-the-art facilities, the highest standards of cleanliness, and our ongoing communication with parents.

All of the dedicated, caring staff at The Magical Years want to be certain that your child has the very best early childhood experience possible. We want to thank you for entrusting us with that privilege and responsibility. Please take the time to read all the following information to help you better understand our programs and philosophy.

name: Mighty Oaks Montessori School
details:
Founded in 2011, Mighty Oaks Montessori (MOM) offers an exceptional Montessori education to children ages 15 months to six years old. MOM focuses on seven curriculum themes: Practical Life, Sensorial Exploration, Language, Mathematics, Self-Expression & Art, Music, and Culture.

MOM educates the whole child. Each student is guided to develop social, emotionally, physically, and academically.

name: Mountainside Childrens Center - Marlborough
details:
At Mountainside Children’s Center, we provide your child with a solid foundation for learning. With stimulating materials and challenging activities, we’ve created a learning center that encourages participation in science, art, block building, math, sensory play, dramatic play, and language arts. Our spacious center includes state-of-the-art curricular materials, well appointed classroom spaces, a 2000 sq ft indoor gross motor room, a full size kitchen, and a huge outdoor natural playscape.

The mission of Mountainside Children’s Center is to meet the child care needs of working families in the Framingham Technology Park and surrounding area. We believe Mountainside is a place where children are loved and cared for; not just taken care of. As a staff, our desire is to reach the heart and mind of each child, providing them with a solid foundation for future learning by enhancing their social, fine/gross motor and cognitive skills and by promoting and modeling values such as love, respect, honesty, and kindness. We honor religious preferences and respect individual beliefs.

name: Needham Children's Center Inc.
details:
We offer a quality program for children and their families which recognizes the holistic development of young children. We promote their cognitive, social, emotional, and physical growth and provide a stimulating environment with positive, nurturing care and a developmentally appropriate curriculum. NCC provides a variety of experiences and activities designed to encourage children to learn about themselves, their friends, and their surroundings. These include small and large group experiences, quiet times, and active play, as well as indoor and outdoor activities in keeping with NAEYC criteria and the Massachusetts Core Competencies for early childhood education.

Our outdoor play areas are spacious and designed with safety as a primary consideration. Our equipment is continually updated to meet the developmental needs of our children. It allows children to develop and test their skills with graduated challenges that are appropriate for our children’s ages and stages. The playgrounds’ designs accommodate our children’s needs for gross motor skills activity.

Our commitment to good nutrition is reflected in the mid-morning and midafternoon snacks served to the children. We work closely with our health care consultant and a nutritionist to meet the needs of growing children.

name: New Horizons Daycare, Inc.
details: New Horizons Daycare is dedicated in providing an atmosphere that promotes Christian values along with high quality early education for families from all backgrounds.  Our philosophy is focused on Kingdom based children that will grow up in an environment that promotes leadership. New Horizons Daycare takes pride in their trained care givers, safeguards, and strategically designed learning environment that inspire, and support development conditions, resulting in long term benefits within children ages 15 month to 5 years old, their families and our community.  Our goal is to work in partnership with parents in supporting a child’s emotional, social, physical, and intellectual growth by connecting each child with passion for God’s design for them. Parents will be assured of a safe, affordable, and nurturing childcare. Our environment will foster biblical foundational truths that will promote self-expression, social growth and development. We will guide children through positive discipline, reflective listening, logical consequences, and peaceful alternatives to make responsible decisions. Our program will offer a variety of developmentally appropriate creative, physical, and intellectual activities, maintaining a balance of quiet, active, and self-directed time. New Horizons Daycare, Inc. is committed to transforming our generations by lifting up children that are bold about their faith and their relationship with God

name: New Sunrise Preschool
details:
NSP philosophy is that each child is a unique and capable individual.  We strive to provide a program which fosters creativity and encourages curiosity and love of learning.  Our program provides children a rich cultural preschool experience, utilizing the Spanish language as the vehicle for instructions and experiences.

We offer a safe and loving environment, comprehensive child centered curriculum and a professional and experienced staff.  The curriculum is designed for optimum growth and development in the following areas; social-emotional, oral language, physical health, fine motor, creativity and cognitive skills.  These areas are addressed in a positive learning environment which promotes feelings of self-worth and success.  We also offer art, science, music and dramatic play and activities.

name: Old Colony Y - Kingston
details:
Before and After School Care is a great option for children of parents who need care which fits with both work and school schedules.  Children can choose from a wide variety of activities including arts & crafts, reading, sports, games, plus field trips, themed special events, team building activites, and more!
 
The Old Colony YMCA believes that each child is special, with his or her own personality, talents, and skills.  Our approach to child care reflects the YMCA's core values of caring, honesty, respect, and responsibility, as well as our commitment to building strong kids, strong families and strong communities.
 
We offer so many wonderful activities and programs - all in a safe, nuturing, developmentally appropriate environment!

name: Our Future Learning Center 2
details: If you are looking for a great daycare or preschool for your child in the Boston area, look no further than Our Future Learning Center, with locations in Allston, Brighton, and Marlborough, Massachusetts. We’ll not only take care of your child and make sure he or she feels comfortable and safe, but we’ll also engage him or her in flexible curriculum and enrichment learning programs, such as language skills, math, science, arts & crafts, music, computers, reading, storytelling, drama, puppet shows, gymnastics, and more. With programs developed especially for infants, toddlers, preschool, and pre-kindergarten children, our teachers are dedicated to making sure your child feels like they belong.

name: P Tits Bouts
details: At efgb, our mission is to provide high quality affordable French education that responds to the needs of Boston Area francophone families. Through our programs and events, we dedicate ourselves to the social, physical and emotional development and well-being of all of our students - in class and beyond - by living our values: Community, Respect, Language and Excellence.

name: Panda Cub Academy
details:
Panda Cub Academy introduces children 3 months to 5 years of age to Chinese language and culture through play, art, music, dance, and lessons. All classes are led by our native Mandarin speaking teachers who are also proficient in English, experienced in early childhood education, and state certified.
 
Our classrooms and curriculum are built on the belief that children learn best through interactive experience and purposeful play.  By combining the Montessori educational philosophy with Chinese language immersion, we offer children the best of both worlds.  We believe students will naturally and effortlessly acquire Mandarin during these early years, when the mind is primed to learn language.  

Our mission is to provide a creative, safe and nurturing environment where children can delight in growing and learning.
  
Our goal is to help develop happy, kind, self-confident, and successful children. We hope to instill and inspire in our students an understanding, love, and kindness towards themselves as well as the people and world around them.

name: PINEBROOK CHILDRENS CENTER
details: Pine Brook Children’s Center sits at the foot of Mt. Sugarloaf in South Deerfield, Massachusetts.  Sugarloaf Brook winds through our six acres of woods and meadows, providing a rich and varied natural space for children to explore, experience and learn. Opportunities to climb, sled, run, dig, observe and pretend,  invite creative, vigorous and genuine play. The air-conditioned school building was designed specifically for children.

name: Ponds Child Care Center
details:
The Ponds Child Care Center and Preschool has been licensed by the department of early education and care since 1990. The center is conveniently located in the Ponds of Plymouth development in South  Plymouth. We offer multiple programs for children ages six weeks to eight years old. Our goal is to provide a fun and safe learning environment for your child, while encouraging social, emotional, intellectual, and physical development. Your child will receive quality personal and individualized care in a warm and loving environment, where they can feel safe and happy and can begin to build confidence and a positive self image.

Our center is designed to provide a nurturing atmosphere along with spacious, stimulating class rooms for the children to actively learn and play in; equipped with safe and fun age appropriate materials giving each child an exciting world full of opportunities to explore, learn, and grow. Furthermore, we maintain a state regulated low teacher to child ratio. Therefore, your child will receive the kind of close attention he or she deserves, nurturing a foundation for development and helping to enable your child to reach their full potential.

We have several large fully fenced in outdoor play areas, equipped with fun and safe play equipment. For children of all ages we incorporate lots of fun activities into their daily schedule that include arts and crafts, free-play, structured-play, music, song and dance, painting, coloring, various creative and educational projects, science and history exploration and much more. Additionally, for children ages 2.9 through five, we offer three individual structured preschool and Pre K programs as well as vacation and summer programs for school age children. Because of these points, we feel we are able to provide the best of both worlds (learning and fun, all in one).

name: Quincy YMCA @ Bethel Church
details:
Our Norwell Afterschool Programs include before and after school care for students grades K through 6 at Vinal Elementary School and Cole Elementary School as well as an after school program for students at South Shore Charter Public School.
Our Scituate programs include before and after school care for students at Cushing Elementary School, Hatherly Elementary School, Jenkins Elementary School and Wampatuck Elementary School.

name: The School For Early Excellence
details:
The School for Early Excellence (SEE) provides a safe, welcoming, and nurturing environment where children are comfortable and inspired to learn. Our classroom environment promotes educational learning, lays the foundation for your child to become independent and gives your child the opportunity to be creative through play.

We have designed a purposeful and challenging curriculum that promotes creativity, exploration, and discovery. Our curriculum centers on the children's current interests, which encourages independence, fosters self-esteem, and builds confidence. We believe in showing progress through fun, simple assessments as your child grows and gains new skills.

As a community, it is our goal to expand upon social skills and encourage friendships to develop and flourish. We also believe that it is important for parents to be involved in their child’s early education – volunteering and being part of regular activities is encouraged to strengthen the parent-child bond and our community.

name: Smart Kids Child Care Ctr.
details: Smart Kids Child Care Center specializes in child care. The business includes but is not limited to early childhood education for infants, toddlers, preschool age, kindergarten, and school age children three months to eight years of age.

name: Smiles Day Nursery  Early Learning Center
details:
Smiles Day Nursery and Early Learning Center is a place where learning is based on trust, comfort and nurture while attending to individual needs of children.

We provide care and education for children from 3 months to 5 years of age. Our age appropriate curriculum offers variety of routine based and fundamental activities for Infants, Toddlers and Preschoolers. We are committed to giving a strong foundation to each child's future.

name: South Shore YMCA School age Program
details: The South Shore YMCA Quincy Branch Afterschool Program welcomes children grades K through 6 from elementary and middle schools throughout Quincy. Our Early Education and Care licensed program strives to provide a safe, supportive environment for all of our children where they can continue to learn & grow while meeting new friends and creating lasting memories.

name: South ShoreYMCA@Broad Meadows Middle School
details: The South Shore YMCA Quincy Branch Afterschool Program welcomes children grades K through 6 from elementary and middle schools throughout Quincy. Our Early Education and Care licensed program strives to provide a safe, supportive environment for all of our children where they can continue to learn & grow while meeting new friends and creating lasting memories.

name: Square One @ Family Square
details:
King Street is a well-established early education and care center located near Springfield College. Our staff is diverse with many bi-lingual and bi-cultural teachers. A brand new, beautiful playground was installed in 2012 -- it is a large, fabulous play space with an outdoor water spray, bicycle track and a large gardening area.  At this time, we are active participants in the Department of Early Education and Care's Quality Rating Improvement System and have just recently submitted for our NAEYC (National Association of Young Children) accreditation with an anticipated site visit in the Fall. This accreditation is like the Good Housekeeping seal of approval in our world!

We have a cooperative Program with Putnam Vocational Academy.  Juniors and seniors enrolled in Putnam’s early childhood tract alternate weeks between  Square One and their academic program @ Putnam providing all Square One children with additional attention and care.

Our curriculum is based on national outcome expectations and all our children are regularly assessed to ensure they are reaching their full educational, emotional and social potential. Literacy is a big component of our work with story books and literature incorporated into our daily learning schedules. Field trips are taken regularly to local museums, farms and other exciting attractions.

We would look forward to hosting you for a tour and look forward to supporting your child's educational success.

name: Square One @ Putnam Vocational Technical Academy
details:
King Street is a well-established early education and care center located near Springfield College. Our staff is diverse with many bi-lingual and bi-cultural teachers. A brand new, beautiful playground was installed in 2012 -- it is a large, fabulous play space with an outdoor water spray, bicycle track and a large gardening area.  At this time, we are active participants in the Department of Early Education and Care's Quality Rating Improvement System and have just recently submitted for our NAEYC (National Association of Young Children) accreditation with an anticipated site visit in the Fall. name: Stars of Tomorrow Early Learning Center LLC
details:
Welcome to Stars of Tomorrow Early Learning Center.  We are a daycare and early learning center that offers full-time and part-time, year round, quality care and education, to children ages 6 weeks to 14 years.  We offer Kindergarten, before and after school programs for school aged children, as well as vacation and summer programs, created to enhance the growth of all children.  All of our programs are commensurate with the MA Frameworks.  Below, are some of the things that distinguish us from other daycare and early learning centers.  We believe that children learn through hands-on experience that enhances the development of each child’s whole self: physical, intellectual, creative, social, and emotional.  As each of these facets develop at different rates, the children seek activities and experiences that meet their individual needs.  In addition, children have many opportunities to stimulate each other’s thinking, and encourage pro-social behaviors amongst themselves.
We believe that children form an extension of their families and the community at large; therefore, we are committed to providing the highest quality of care possible to children and their families, in an environment as close to home like as possible, incorporating our families’ pictures and cultures in the different rooms throughout the center.

name: Step by Step Chinese Learning Center
Terri's Little Pumpkins
details:
We’d like to welcome you and your family into our circle of families. At Terri’s Little Pumpkins, we strive to offer the very best high quality child care possible for children six weeks – 10.9 years of age.

    Our care giving philosophy is based on the belief that children are unique and respond best in an environment which fosters individuality, creativity, and growth.
    Our stimulating curriculum allows children to learn through the process of discovery and play while being guided by nurturing and professional staff. You will find our philosophy reflected in the quality and focus of our programs.
    The center’s modern facility was designed specifically with the children in mind and provides a safe, friendly, and warm environment where children can explore freely.
    Our convenient locations and extended hours meet the needs of today’s busy parents.

name: The Toddler Corner
details:
Community Teamwork offers three center-based Head Start/Early Head Start early learning programs that include the Community Teamwork James Houlares Early Learning Center, the Children’s Village at the Mill and the Children’s Corner.

Community Teamwork also offers the home-based Home Visiting Program for Early Head Start and Head Start where the focus of service delivery is in the home. The Early Learning center-based programs are part of the national Head Start program that promotes school readiness by providing quality education services to children in a nurturing, safe environment and comprehensive community-based services to children and families. Eligible children and families receive services in the areas of education and care (including individualized curriculum in all learning areas), health, child literacy, nutrition, and social-emotional development. The center programs also offer other services, if needed, based on the Family Needs Assessment. These programs are licensed by the Department of Early Education and Care (EEC) and accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC).

name: Vinal Before and After School care program
Wampatuck Before and After School Care Program
Wellesley Community Children's Ctr.- Upham
details: The Wellesley Community Children’s Center is a private, non-profit corporation, operated by a Board of Directors, administrative staff, and professional teaching staff. In 1971, WCCC began by enrolling preschoolers and kindergartners. We now serve more than 400 children from infancy through middle school in our Early Childhood and After School Programs.

name: YMCA After School Program @ MacArthur Elementary
details: Parents love YMCA After School, our family-centered program that nurtures the whole child by inspiring academic success, healthy movement and social and emotional development. Our staff of caring, trained educators are role models who lead activities that promote cooperation and character development. Parents can be productive at work knowing their children are in a safe and stimulating after school environment.

name: YMCA Childrens Center at the WR VA
details: Everyone deserves the chance to discover who they are and what they can achieve. At the West Roxbury YMCA, we want youth and teens to have the opportunity to learn, grow and thrive. Time at the Y spent playing, learning and socializing helps kids of all ages to grow character values, skills and relationships that lead to positive behavior, better health and educational achievement.

name: YMCA Schools Out @ Brunton
details: The YMCA of Greater Springfield provides a safe, fun environment for children to continue learning and developing during out-of-school periods. During Before-School programs, the YMCA provides a safe environment for children from 6:30 until the start of the school day.  Breakfast is provided and children can choose from a variety of activities.  During Afterschool Programs, we provide snack and homework assistance.  We also provide age appropriate activities each day, including sports, outdoor play, arts and crafts, science, cooking, story time, and much more. This program begins at the end of the full school day and runs until 6:00 pm. - See more at: http://www.springfieldy.org/our-focus/for-youth-development/early-education-school-age-care/school-age/springfield-area-programs/#sthash.GQQqmpFE.dpuf
